<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Get Average Lending Duration Per Book</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Librarian</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Librarian requests for the average lending duration per book by making a GET request to /api/lendings/average-per-book.</step>
        <step id="S2">LendingController activates to handle the request.</step>
        <step id="S3">LendingController calls LendingService's getAverageLendingDurationPerBook() method.</step>
        <step id="S4">LendingService activates to calculate the average lending duration per book.</step>
        <step id="S5">LendingService queries LendingRepository to find the average lending duration per book.</step>
        <step id="S6">LendingRepository provides a list of Object[] results to LendingService.</step>
        <step id="S7">LendingService uses LendingAvgPerBookViewMapper to map the results to LendingAvgPerBookView objects.</step>
        <step id="S8">LendingAvgPerBookViewMapper activates to map the results.</step>
        <step id="S9">LendingAvgPerBookViewMapper iterates over each result to create LendingAvgPerBookView.</step>
        <step id="S10">LendingAvgPerBookViewMapper provides an Iterable<LendingAvgPerBookView> views to LendingService.</step>
        <step id="S11">LendingService provides Iterable<LendingAvgPerBookView> views to LendingController.</step>
        <step id="S12">LendingController deactivates and responds to the Librarian with HTTP 200 OK along with Iterable<LendingAvgPerBookView> views.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Retrieve Subscription Configuration</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Gateway</actor>
        <actor>Keycloak</actor>
        <actor>Subscription</actor>
        <actor>Mongo Database</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User requests subscription configuration.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Valid JWT is presented and subscription configuration is successfully retrieved from the database.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>JWT is absent or invalid, resulting in a 401 or 403 status code.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>GET /api/v1/subscriptions</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User initiates a request to retrieve subscription configuration.</step>
        <step id="S2">Gateway receives the request and forwards it to Keycloak for JWT verification.</step>
        <step id="S3">Keycloak verifies the JWT and responds back to the Gateway.</step>
        <step id="S4">Gateway checks the validity of the JWT.</step>
        <step id="S5" actor="User">JWT is valid.</step>
        <step id="S6" actor="Gateway">Gateway forwards the request to Subscription service.</step>
        <step id="S7" actor="Subscription">Subscription service queries Mongo Database for user subscription configuration.</step>
        <step id="S8" actor="Mongo Database">Mongo Database retrieves the user's subscription configuration.</step>
        <step id="S9" actor="Subscription">Subscription service receives the configuration from the database.</step>
        <step id="S10" actor="Gateway">Gateway sends the subscription configuration to the User.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Retrieve User Subscription Configuration</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Gateway</actor>
        <actor>Keycloak</actor>
        <actor>Subscription Service</actor>
        <actor>Mongo Database</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>The user sends a GET request to retrieve subscription information.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>The subscription configuration is successfully retrieved and sent back to the user.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>The user does not provide a valid JWT or the JWT is not valid.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>User requests subscription information by calling the API endpoint.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User sends a GET request to the gateway to retrieve subscription information.</step>
        <step id="S2">Gateway forwards the request to Keycloak to verify the JWT.</step>
        <step id="S3">Keycloak verifies the JWT and responds to the gateway.</step>
        <step id="S4">If the JWT is valid:</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S4">
            <step id="A1S1">Gateway sends a GET request to the subscription service to retrieve subscriptions.</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Subscription service queries the Mongo database to get the user's subscription configuration by user id.</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Mongo database retrieves the subscription configuration and sends it back to the subscription service.</step>
            <step id="A1S4">Subscription service forwards the subscription configuration to the gateway.</step>
            <step id="A1S5">Gateway sends the subscription configuration back to the user.</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S5">If the JWT is absent, gateway returns HttpStatus 401 to the user.</step>
        <step id="S6">If the JWT is not valid, gateway returns HttpStatus 403 to the user.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<?xml version="1.0"?>
<!ELEMENT useCase (name, description?, actors?, preconditions?, successEndConditions?, failureEndConditions?, trigger?, mainSequence, alternativeSteps?, errorSteps?)>
<!ATTLIST useCase id CDATA #REQUIRED>

<!ELEMENT name (#PCDATA)>
<!ELEMENT description (#PCDATA)>
<!ELEMENT actors (actor+)>
<!ELEMENT actor (#PCDATA)>
<!ELEMENT preconditions (precondition+)>
<!ELEMENT precondition (#PCDATA)>
<!ELEMENT successEndConditions (condition+)>
<!ELEMENT condition (#PCDATA)>
<!ELEMENT failureEndConditions (condition+)>
<!ELEMENT trigger (#PCDATA)>
<!ELEMENT mainSequence (step+)>
<!ELEMENT alternativeSteps (asteps+)>
<!ELEMENT errorSteps (esteps+)>


<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Subscription Checking</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>"gateway"</actor>
        <actor>"Keycloak"</actor>
        <actor>"subscription"</actor>
        <actor>"Mongo"</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User requests /api/v1/subscriptions</step>
        <step id="S2">Gateway receives request</step>
        <step id="S3">Gateway verifies JWT</step>
        <step id="S4">Keycloak receives JWT verify request</step>

        <asteps id="A1" start="S5">
            <step id="A1S1">Gateway redirects request to subscription service</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Subscription service queries Mongo for user subscription config by user id</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Mongo responds with user's subscription config</step>
            <step id="A1S4">Subscription service returns subscription config to Gateway</step>
            <step id="A1S5">Gateway returns subscription config to User</step>
        </asteps>

        <asteps id="E1" start="S9">
            <description>JWT is absent or not valid scenarios</description>
            <step id="E1S1">Gateway responds with HttpStatus 401 (Unauthorized)</step>
            <step id="E1S2">Gateway responds with HttpStatus 403 (Forbidden)</step>
        </asteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Package and Import ML Dataset</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Machine Learning Expert</actor>
        <actor>DPIE System</actor>
        <actor>ML Dataset</actor>
        <actor>Data Validation</actor>
        <actor>Data Packaging</actor>
        <actor>ML Platform</actor>
    </actors>
    <trigger>ML Expert requests to package ML dataset</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">DPIE fetches ML dataset from DataSet</step>
        <step id="S2">DataSet returns ML dataset to DPIE</step>
        <step id="S3">ValidationService validates ML dataset</step>

        <asteps id="A1">
            <step id="A1S1">Validation Successful: DPIE initiates packaging process with PackagingService</step>
            <step id="A1S2">PackagingService prepares data package</step>
            <step id="A1S3">DPIE notifies ML Expert that data package is ready</step>
            <step id="A1S4">ML Expert requests DPIE to import data package</step>
            <step id="A1S5">DPIE sends data package to ML Platform</step>
            <step id="A1S6">ML Platform confirms receipt of data package</step>
            <step id="A1S7">DPIE confirms data package import to ML Expert</step>
        </asteps>

        <esteps id="E1">
            <description>Validation Failed: DPIE notifies ML Expert of validation failure</description>
            <step id="E1S1">Validation Failed step</step>
        </esteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
  <name>User Registration</name>
  <description>Register a new user in the system</description>
  
  <actors>
    <actor>User</actor>
    <actor>Registration Page</actor>
    <actor>Auth Control</actor>
    <actor>User Entity</actor>
    <actor>User Database</actor>
  </actors>
  
  <trigger>User enters email and password</trigger>
  
  <mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">User enters email and password on the registration page</step>
    <step id="S2">Registration page sends data to the authentication control</step>
    <step id="S3">Authentication control checks if the email is already registered</step>
    <step id="S4">User entity verifies presence of email</step>
    
    <!-- Alternative Steps -->
    <alternativeSteps id="A1">
      <step id="A1S1">User's email is already registered</step>
      <step id="A1S2">Displays an error message to the user indicating the email is already registered</step>
      <step id="A1S3">User registration fails</step>
    </alternativeSteps>
    
    <alternativeSteps start="A1">
      <step id="S5">User's email is not registered</step>
      <step id="S6">User data is saved into the system</step>
      <step id="S7">User data is stored into the database</step>
      <step id="S8">Confirmation of successful registration</step>
      <step id="S9">Indicate successful registration to the user</step>
      <step id="S10">User gains access to the system</step>
    </alternativeSteps>
  </mainSequence>

</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
  <name>Enable Step Counter Feature</name>
  <actors>
    <actor>Social Caregiver</actor>
    <actor>User(device)</actor>
    <actor>ALFRED Device </actor>
    <actor>ALFRED Software</actor>
    <actor>Health Monitoring Service</actor>
  </actors>
  <trigger>Request to enable Step Counter feature for User</trigger>
  <mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">At the request of the Social Caregiver, ALFRED Device initiates enabling the Step Counter feature for User</step>
    <step id="S2">ALFRED Software activates the Step Counter functionality</step>
    <step id="S3">ALFRED Software confirms the activation of the Step Counter feature</step>
    <step id="S4">ALFRED Device informs the User about the availability of the Step Counter feature</step>
    <step id="S5">User requests to enable the Step Counter feature</step>
  </mainSequence>
  
  <alternativeSteps>
    <asteps id="A1">
      <step id="A1S1">Ongoing Daily Usage steps of the Step Counting feature</step>
      <step>Walking counted as steps are monitored</step>
    </asteps>
  </alternativeSteps>

  <errorSteps>
    <esteps id="E1">
      <description>Error handling due to missing Step Counting Data</description>
      <step id="E1S1">In case Step Counting Data is not available, retrieve failed data or display error message</step>
    </esteps>
  </errorSteps>

</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Create Nametags for Campers</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Administrator</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Administrator selects "Generate Nametags"</step>
        <step id="S2">Camp Management System retrieves all Camper Profiles from Camper Profile Database</step>
        <step id="S3">Camp Management System receives Camper Details</step>
        <step id="S4">Camp Management System sends Camper Details to Nametag Generator</step>
        <step id="S5">Nametag Generator generates Nametags</step>
        <step id="S6">Nametags are sent back to Camp Management System</step>
        <step id="S7">Camp Management System sends Nametags for Printing</step>
        <step id="S8">Printer acknowledges Printing</step>
        <step id="S9">Camp Management System provides Confirmation & Status to Administrator</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Nametag Creation for Campers</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Administrator</actor>
        <actor>Camp Management System</actor>
        <actor>Camper Profile Database</actor>
        <actor>Nametag Generator</actor>
        <actor>Printer</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Administrator selects "Generate Nametags"</step>
        <step id="S2">Camp Management System retrieves all Camper Profiles from Camper Profile Database</step>
        <step id="S3">Camp Management System receives Camper Details</step>
        <step id="S4">Camp Management System sends Camper Details to Nametag Generator</step>
        <step id="S5">Nametag Generator generates Nametags</step>
        <step id="S6">Nametag Generator sends Nametags to Printer for Printing</step>
        <step id="S7">Printer acknowledges Printing</step>
        <step id="S8">Camp Management System sends Confirmation & Status to Administrator</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Inibir um robot</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Gestor de frota</actor>
        <actor>robDroneGo:robDroneGo</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Gestor de frota inibe um robot</step>
        <step id="S2">robDroneGo:robDroneGo requisita que o Gestor de frota selecione um robot</step>
        <step id="S3">Gestor de frota seleciona o robot</step>

    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Sucesso na inibição do robot - robDroneGo:robDroneGo devolve o robot inibido</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Falha na requisição - robDroneGo:robDroneGo devolve mensagem de erro</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Inibir um robot</name>

        <actor>robDroneGo:robDroneGo</actor>

        <step id="S1">O Gestor de frota solicita a inibição de um robot.</step>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Inibir Robot</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Gestor de frota</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">O Gestor de frota inibe um robot</step>

    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">

        <actor>Staff Member</actor>
    </actors>
    
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Staff Member is logged in</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>All pending affidavits have been processed</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    
    <trigger>Staff Member selects to manage affidavits</trigger>
    
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Staff Member accesses the portal</step>
        <step id="S2">User Authentication requests credentials</step>
        <step id="S3">Staff Member provides credentials</step>
        <step id="S4">User Authentication validates credentials</step>
        <step id="S5">User Authentication grants access</step>
        <step id="S6">Staff Member selects Manage Affidavits</step>
        <step id="S7">Staff Dashboard opens Affidavit Management</step>
        <step id="S8">Affidavit Management System queries pending affidavits</step>
        <step id="S9">Database returns pending affidavits</step>
        <step id="S10">Affidavit Management System displays pending affidavits</step>
        
        <asteps id="A1" start="S10">
            <step id="A1S1">Staff selects an affidavit</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Affidavit Management System retrieves details</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Compliance Module checks requirements</step>
            <step id="A1S4">Compliance Module shows compliance status</step>
            
            <alt id="A1A1" start="A1S4" continue="A1S1">
                <step id="A1A1S1">Staff marks affidavit as compliant</step>
                <step id="A1A1S2">Affidavit Management System updates status</step>
                <step id="A1A1S3">Compliance Notice is generated</step>
                <step id="A1A1S4">Notice is saved</step>
                <step id="A1A1S5">Compliance Notice is shown</step>
            </alt>
            
            <alt id="A1A2" start="A1S4" continue="A1S1">
                <step id="A1A2S1">Staff marks affidavit as non-compliant</step>
                <step id="A1A2S2">Affidavit Management System updates status</step>
                <step id="A1A2S3">Staff requests additional information</step>
                <step id="A1A2S4">Affidavit Management System updates request</step>
                <step id="A1A2S5">Info request confirmation is shown</step>
            </alt>
            
        </asteps>
        
        <step id="S11">Staff Member logs out</step>
        <step id="S12">User Authentication confirms logout</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

An attacker has compromised the agent policy registry and locked out Alice. Alice performs agent recovery by completing all steps in Offline Recovery or Social Recovery diagram. Alice generates policy registry address P' and stores it. Alice revokes all her claims that include the old agent policy address P as a blinded attribute and petitions the Issuers to reissue her claims. Alice revokes a claim. Alice's Edge Agent sends revoke claim message. Issuer authenticates Alice. Issuer revokes the claim and adds claim index Si to the non-revocation accumulator SO. Ledger updates accumulator. Ledger forwards the result. Alice's Cloud Agent acknowledges. Alice completes Issue Claim diagram for each claim with new policy address P.

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Garanteed Idempotency Using CorrelationIds</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Client-Service</actor>
        <actor>Client Persistence</actor>
        <actor>Callback</actor>
        <actor>Service</actor>
        <actor>Service Persistence</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Create and store correlationId</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Client-Service creates and stores correlationId</step>
        <step id="S2">Client-Service calls callService with cId1</step>
        <step id="S3">Service receives call with cId1</step>
        <step id="S4">Service finds cId1 in Service Persistence</step>
        <step id="S5">Service checks if cId1 exists</step>
        <step id="S6">Service report cId1 found as yes/no</step>
        <step id="S7">Service informs Client-Service about successful finding</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S8">
            <step id="A1S1">Service stores cId1 into Service Persistence</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Service handles service operations</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S9">Service asynchronously responds to Callback with cId1</step>
        <step id="S10">Callback searches cId1 in Client Persistence</step>
        <step id="S11">Callback returns the state to Callback</step>
        <esteps id="E1" start="S12">
            <description>Action to store cId1 as answered</description>
            <step id="E1S1">Callback sets that cId1 has been answered</step>
            <step id="E1S2">Callback marks the task as done</step>
        </esteps>
        <esteps id="E2" start="S13">
            <description>Action for unknown cId1</description>
            <step id="E2S1">Callback sends 'unknown correlationId' to Service</step>
        </esteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC-001">
    <name>Reconfigure Dataset</name>
    <description>User initiates the reconfiguration of a dataset in the Dataset Management System.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>The user is authenticated and authorized to modify the dataset settings.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>The dataset reconfiguration process is successfully completed.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>The dataset reconfiguration process fails due to an issue with the Explore Table update.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>User initiates a request to reconfigure the dataset.</trigger>
    <mainSequence id="S1">
        <step id="S1.1">User sends a reconfigure dataset request to the Dataset Management System.</step>
        <step id="S1.2">Dataset Management System validates the Explore Table update.</step>
        <step id="S1.3">If Explore Table update is successful, the system proceeds with dataset reconfiguration.</step>
        <step id="S1.4">If Explore Table update fails, the system rolls back any changes made during reconfiguration.</step>
        <step id="S1.5">The system notifies the user about the success/failure of the dataset reconfiguration process.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>User initiates dataset reconfiguration</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1" actor="User request sender">Initiates reconfiguration of dataset in the Dataset Management System</step>
        <step id="S2" actor="Dataset Management System">Validates Explore Table Update using the Database Explore Table</step>
        <step id="S3" actor="Dataset Management System">Proceeds with Dataset Reconfiguration after successful update</step>
        <step id="S4" actor="User request sender">Receives confirmation of successful reconfiguration</step>
        <step id="S5" actor="Dataset Management System">Rollbacks any changes after failed Explore Table Update</step>
        <step id="S6" actor="User request sender">Receives notification of failed reconfiguration</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Reconfiguration of dataset successful</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Failed to reconfigure dataset</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">

    <trigger>User requests to retrieve medical conditions</trigger>

        <asteps id="A1" start="S2">

            </asteps>
            <step id="A1S4">Repository provides a list of medical conditions to AllergyService</step>
            <step id="A1S5">AllergyService returns the list of medical conditions to API_Controller</step>
            <step id="A1S6">API_Controller responds with 200 OK along with the medical condition data</step>
        </asteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
  <name>Login to Library System</name>
  <actors>
    <actor>User</actor>
  </actors>
  <preconditions>
    <precondition>User is not logged in</precondition>
  </preconditions>
  <mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">User clicks on "Login"</step>
    <step id="S2">Library System enters username and password</step>
    <step id="S3">User logs in</step>
    <step id="S4">Library System shows welcome message</step>
  </mainSequence>
  <failureEndConditions>
    <condition>Login details are incorrect</condition>
  </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

    <name>Query Order</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Client</actor>
        <actor>QueryOrderHandler</actor>
        <actor>OrderRepo</actor>
        <actor>OrderDataStore (DashMap)</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Client initiates query for an order</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Order successfully retrieved and sent to the client</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Order not found in the database</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Client queries the order</step>
        <step id="S2">QueryOrderHandler gets the order by table id</step>
        <step id="S3">OrderRepo retrieves the order from OrderDataStore</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S3">
            <step id="A1S1">Order successfully retrieved from the database</step>
        </asteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Query Order</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Client</actor>
        <actor>QueryOrderHandler</actor>
        <actor>OrderRepo</actor>
        <actor>OrderDataStore (DashMap)</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Client queries order</step>
        <step id="S2">QueryOrderHandler gets order by table id from OrderRepo</step>
        <step id="S3">OrderRepo retrieves order from OrderDataStore</step>
        <step id="S4">QueryOrderHandler sends order to Client</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>200 Ok</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>404 Not Found</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Query Order</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Client</actor>
        <actor>QueryOrderHandler</actor>
        <actor>OrderRepo</actor>
        <actor>OrderDataStore (DashMap)</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Client queries order</step>
        <step id="S2">Handler gets order by table id from OrderRepo</step>
        <step id="S3">OrderRepo retrieves order from OrderDataStore</step>
        <step id="S4">Handler sends order to Client</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Handler successfully sends order to Client</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Handler informs Client that order is not found</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Query Order</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Client</actor>
        <actor>QueryOrderHandler</actor>
        <actor>OrderRepo</actor>
        <actor>OrderDataStore (DashMap)</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Client queries order</step>
        <step id="S2">QueryOrderHandler retrieves order by table id</step>
        <step id="S3">OrderRepo fetches order from OrderDataStore</step>
        <step id="S4">QueryOrderHandler sends order to Client</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Order not found</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Query Order</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Client</actor>
        <actor>QueryOrderHandler</actor>
        <actor>OrderRepo</actor>
        <actor>OrderDataStore (DashMap)</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Client queries order</step>
        <step id="S2">QueryOrderHandler retrieves order by table id</step>
        <step id="S3">OrderRepo fetches order from OrderDataStore</step>
        <step id="S4">If 200 Ok:
            <asteps id="A1" start="S4">QueryOrderHandler sends order to Client</asteps>
        </step>
        <step id="S5">If 404 Not Found:
            <asteps id="A2" start="S5">QueryOrderHandler notifies Client that order was not found</asteps>
        </step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>User Sign Up</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>SingUpController</actor>
        <actor>SingUpService</actor>
        <actor>UserRepository</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User sends a POST request to /sign-up</step>
        <step id="S2">Controller executes business logic</step>
        <step id="S3">Service validates if the user exists</step>
        <step id="S4">Repository retrieves the user from the Database</step>
        <step id="S5">Repository validates the response</step>
        <alt id="A1" start="S5" continue="S6">
            <asteps id="A1">
                <step id="A1S1">User already exists</step>
            </asteps>
            <step id="S6">Service responds with an error</step>
            <step id="S7">Controller sends an error response to the User</step>
        </alt>
        <step id="S8">Service creates a new user</step>
        <step id="S9">Repository saves the new user to the Database</step>
        <step id="S10">Repository creates a response</step>
        <step id="S11">Service responds with success</step>
        <step id="S12">Controller responds with the user data</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <description>Use case for a User to sign up for an account</description>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User is not already registered</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>User successfully signs up</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>User already exists</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>User initiates the sign-up process by sending a POST request</trigger>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>User signs up</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User sends POST request to /sign-up</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>User successfully signed up</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <trigger>User wants to create an account</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User sends POST request to /sign-up</step>
        <step id="S2">Controller executes business logic</step>
        <step id="S3">Service validates if user exists</step>
        <step id="S4">Repository gets the user from Database</step>
        <step id="S5">Service validates the response</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S5" continue="S2">
            <step id="A1S1">Service responds with error if user already exists</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S6">Service creates new user in Repository</step>
        <step id="S7">Service generates token</step>
        <step id="S8">Service responds with success</step>
        <step id="S9">Controller responds to User with user data</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
<name>Sign up new user</name>
<actors>
    <actor>User</actor>
    <actor>SignUpController</actor>
    <actor>SignUpService</actor>
    <actor>UserRepository</actor>
    <actor>Database</actor>
</actors>
<trigger>Send POST request to /sign-up</trigger>
<mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">User sends a POST request to /sign-up</step>
    <step id="S2">Controller receives the request and triggers the execution of the business logic</step>
    <step id="S3">Service validates if the user already exists in the database</step>
    <step id="S4">Repository retrieves the user from the database</step>
    <step id="S5">Database returns the user if it exists</step>
    <step id="S6">Service receives the user validation response from Repository</step>
    
    <asteps id="A1" start="S3">
        <step id="A1S1">The system identifies that the user already exists</step>
        <step id="A1S2">Service sends an error response to Controller</step>
        <step id="A1S3">Controller forwards the error response to User</step>
    </asteps>
    
    <step id="S7">Service creates the new user</step>
    <step id="S8">Repository saves the new user data to the database</step>
    <step id="S9">Service generates a token for the new user</step>
    <step id="S10">Repository creates a response for the successful creation of the user</step>
    <step id="S11">Service sends a success response to Controller</step>
    <step id="S12">Controller forwards the success response along with user data to User</step>
</mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Check for Concurrent Edits Before Saving a Record</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Archivist</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Archivist requests to edit Record [X]</step>
        <step id="S2">AMS queries last edit timestamp for Record [X]</step>
        <step id="S3">RSD provides last edit timestamp</step>
        <step id="S4">AMS displays Record [X] and last edit info to Archivist</step>
        <step id="S5">Archivist makes changes to the record</step>
        <step id="S6">Archivist attempts to save changes</step>
        <step id="S7">AMS checks if Record [X] has been edited since the last timestamp</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S6" continue="S7">
            <step id="A1S1">Record has been edited</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Record [X] has been modified; AMS displays an error message to Archivist</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Archivist reviews the changes or retries later</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S6" continue="S7">
            <step id="A2S1">Record not edited</step>
            <step id="A2S2">No changes detected for Record [X]</step>
            <step id="A2S3">AMS updates Record [X] with new data and timestamp</step>
            <step id="A2S4">Record [X] updated successfully; AMS displays success message to Archivist</step>
        </asteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Check for Concurrent Edits Before Saving a Record</name>
    
    <actors>
        <actor>Archivist</actor>
    </actors>
    
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Archivist requests to edit Record [X] from AMS</step>
        <step>Sends a query to RSD to get the last edit timestamp for Record [X]</step>
        <step>Last edit timestamp received from RSD is displayed for Record [X] by AMS to Archivist</step>
        <step>The Archivist makes changes to the record</step>
        <step id="S5">Archivist attempts to save changes in AMS</step>
        <step>AMS checks if Record [X] has been edited since the last edit timestamp in RSD</step>
    </mainSequence>
    
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Record [X] has been modified by another user</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    
    <trigger>Attempt made to save changes to Record [X]</trigger>
    
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Your changes have been saved successfully</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
</useCase>

<?xml version="1.0"?>
<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Check for Concurrent Edits Before Saving a Record</lastname>
    <actors>
        <actor>Archivist</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Request to edit Record [X]</step>
        <step id="S2">Query last edit timestamp for Record [X]</step>
        <step id="S3">Display Record [X] and last edit info</step>
        <step id="S3"> Makes changes to the record</step>
        <step id="S4">Attempt to save changes</step>
        <step id="S5">Check if Record [X] has been edited since the last timestamp</step>
        <step id="S6.1">Error Message: Record has been modified by another user</step>
        <step id="S6.2">Review the changes or retrt later</step>
        <step id="S7">No changes detected</step>
        <step id="S8">Update Record [X] with new data and timestamp</step>
        <step id="S9">Record [X] updated successfully</step>
        <step id="S10">Success Message: Your changes have been saved</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Check for Concurrent Edits Before Saving a Record</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Archivist</actor>
        <actor>AMS</actor>
        <actor>RSD</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Archivist requests to edit Record [X]</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Record [X] updated successfully</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Record has been modified by another user</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Archivist requests to edit Record [X]</step>
        <step id="S2">Query last edit timestamp for Record [X]</step>
        <step id="S3">Display Record [X] and last edit info</step>
        <step id="S4">Archivist makes changes to the record</step>
        <step id="S5">Attempt to save changes</step>
        <step id="S6">Check if Record [X] has been edited since last timestamp</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S6">
            <step id="A1S1">Record [X] has been modified</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S6">
            <step id="A2S1">No changes detected</step>
            <step id="A2S2">Update Record [X] with new data and timestamp</step>
            <step id="A2S3">Record [X] updated successfully</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
    <errorSteps>
        <esteps id="E1" start="S1">
            <step id="E1S1">Error Message: Record has been modified by another user</step>
        </esteps>
    </errorSteps>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Update Canvas</name>
    <description>As a User, I want to be able to update the canvas with changes.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>Users</actor>
        <actor>Client</actor>
        <actor>Canvas</actor>
        <actor>Websocket</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Users make changes to the canvas.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Canvas successfully updated and changes broadcasted.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Session validation fails.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>Changes made to the canvas.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Users change the canvas.</step>
        <step id="S2">Client updates the canvas.</step>
        <step id="S3">Canvas sends changes via WebSocket.</step>
        <step id="S4">WebSocket validates the session.</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S4">
            <step id="A1S1">Session is valid.</step>
            <step id="A1S2">WebSocket broadcasts changes.</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Canvas updates the canvas.</step>
            <step id="A1S4">Canvas shows changes to Users.</step>
        </asteps>
        <esteps id="E1" start="S4">
            <description>Session validation fails.</description>
            <step id="E1S1">WebSocket sends session error.</step>
            <step id="E1S2">Client shows error message to Users.</step>
        </esteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="1">
	<name>Programar tutorías</name>
	<description>Este caso de uso describe el proceso para programar tutorías.</description>
	<actors>
		<actor>Usuario</actor>
	</actors>
	<preconditions>
		<precondition>El usuario ha iniciado sesión y desea programar una tutoría.</precondition>
	</preconditions>
	<successEndConditions>
		<condition>El usuario recibe una confirmación de que la tutoría ha sido programada con éxito.</condition>
	</successEndConditions>
	<trigger>El usuario desea programar una tutoría.</trigger>
	<mainSequence>
		<step id="S1">El actor "Usuario" accede a la sección de programación de tutorías en la vista.</step>
		<step id="S2">La vista solicita al controlador ("ReservaController") el formulario de programación.</step>
		<step id="S3">El controlador envía el formulario de programación a la vista.</step>
		<step id="S4">La vista envía los datos de programación al controlador.</step>
		<step id="S5">El controlador valida los datos de programación recibidos de la vista en la entidad "Reserva".</step>
		<step id="S6">La entidad "Reserva" notifica al controlador que los datos son válidos.</step>
		<step id="S7">El controlador registra la sesión de tutoría en el repositorio de "Reservas".</step>
		<step id="S8">El repositorio de "Reservas" confirma la correcta registración de la tutoría al controlador.</step>
		<step id="S9">El controlador entrega la confirmación de la tutoría programada a la vista.</step>
	</mainSequence>

			<step id="A1S2">El controlador confirma la cancelación al usuario a través de la vista.</step>
		</asteps>
	</alternativeSteps>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Add Event</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User wants to add a new event.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User opens the Add Event Page.</step>
        <step id="S2">User enters event details.</step>
        <step id="S3">User selects associated contact.</step>
        <step id="S4">User submits event form.</step>
        <step id="S5">Add Event Page sends event details to Server.</step>
        <step id="S6">Server validates the details.</step>
        <step id="S7">If details are valid:
            <asteps>
            <step id="A1" continue="S1">Server saves the event details to Database.</step>
            <step id="A2">Database confirms event save operation.</step>
            <step id="A3">Server sends success response to Add Event Page.</step>
            <step id="A4">Add Event Page shows success message to the User.</step>
            </asteps>
        </step>
        <step id="S8">If details are invalid:
            <asteps>
            <step id="A1" start="A1">Server sends error response to Add Event Page.</step>
            <step id="A2">Add Event Page shows error message to the User.</step>
            <step id="A3">Add Event Page prompts User to re-enter event details.</step>
            </asteps>
        </step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Get Translation Case</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Client</actor>
        <actor>API Gateway/Lambda</actor>
        <actor>GetTranslationCaseActivity</actor>
        <actor>TranslationCaseDao</actor>
        <actor>DynamoDB</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Client sends an HTTP Request to API Gateway/Lambda.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">API Gateway/Lambda receives the HTTP Request from the Client.</step>
        <step id="S2">API Gateway/Lambda sends GetTranslationCaseRequest to GetTranslationCaseActivity.</step>
        <step id="S3">GetTranslationCaseActivity calls TranslationCaseDao to getTranslationCase(translationCaseId).</step>
        <step id="S4">TranslationCaseDao loads translationCaseId from DynamoDB.</step>
        <step id="S5">DynamoDB returns translationCase data to TranslationCaseDao.</step>
        <step id="S6">TranslationCaseDao checks for matching customer ID.</step>
        <step id="S7">TranslationCaseDao returns TranslationCase object to GetTranslationCaseActivity.</step>
        <step id="S8">GetTranslationCaseActivity returns GetTranslationCaseResult to API Gateway/Lambda.</step>
        <step id="S9">API Gateway/Lambda returns 200 response with GetTranslationCaseResult data to the Client.</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>TranslationCaseNotFoundException is thrown if translationCase does not exist.</condition>
        <condition>SecurityException is thrown if customer ID does not match.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Retrieve Translation Case</name>
    <description>Actor(Client) initiates a request to get a translation case from the system.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>Client</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>TranslationCase to be available in the system.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>GetTranslationCaseResult with Translation Case data is returned successfully.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>TranslationCaseNotFoundException thrown or SecurityException thrown.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>HTTP Request received through an API Gateway.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">API Gateway/Lambda receives the HTTP Request from the Client.</step>
        <step id="S2-transaction">GetTranslationCaseActivity starts the transaction for getting the Translation Case.</step>
        <step id="S3">Invocation to TranslationCaseDao - getTranslationCase(translationCaseId)</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="E1">
            <step id="A1S1-DynamoNonExist">Database Dynamodb: No translationCase data found.</step>
            <step id="A1S2">GetTranslationCaseActivity receives TranslationCaseNotFoundException.</step>
            <step id="A1S3-failResponse">Return a 400 response to Client.</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A2" start="E2">
            <step id="A2S1-failMatch">Customer IDs do not match in Database.</step>
            <step id="A2S2">GetTranslationCaseActivity receives SecurityException.</step>
            <step id="A2S3-Security-failResponse">Inform Client to return a 400 response.</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
</useCase>

        <step id="S6">TranslationCaseDao checks for matching customer ID</step>
        <step id="S7">TranslationCaseDao returns TranslationCase object to GetTranslationCaseActivity</step>
        <step id="S8">GetTranslationCaseActivity returns GetTranslationCaseResult to API Gateway/Lambda</step>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Claim Mail</name>
    <description>This use case involves claiming mail by a Recipient user.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>Recipient</actor>
    </actors>
    <trigger>Recipient initiates the claim mail process by making a POST request.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">The Recipient makes a POST request to claim mail.</step>
        <step id="S2">The MailController authorizes the request by checking if the Recipient is a Receptionist.</step>
        <step id="S3">The MailController calls the MailService method to claim the mail.</step>
        <step id="S4">The MailService begins a transaction using the Unit of Work (UoW).</step>
        <step id="S5">The MailService retrieves the mail by ID from the MailRepository.</step>
        <step id="S6">The MailService fetches the user details by ID from the UserRepository.</step>
        <step id="S7">The MailService updates the status of the mail in the MailRepository.<step>
        <step id="S8">The MailService creates an email notification in the EmailNotificationRepository.</step>
        <step id="S9">The MailService commits the transaction through UoW.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>View POA Requests List</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Accredited Representative</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Accredited Representative views POA Requests List</step>
        <step id="S2">Frontend sends GET request to Backend for /v0/accredited_representative_portal/poa_requests</step>
        <step id="S3">Backend verifies representative in ar_user_account_accredited_individuals in VAGovDB</step>
        <step id="S4">Backend queries POA Requests with necessary joins in VAGovDB</step>
        <step id="S5">Backend sends JSON Response with POA List to Frontend</step>
        <step id="S6">Frontend displays POA Requests</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC2">
    <name>View POA Request Details</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Accredited Representative</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Accredited Representative selects a POA Request</step>
        <step id="S2">Frontend sends GET request to Backend for /v0/accredited_representative_portal/poa_requests/{id}</step>
        <step id="S3">Backend verifies representative authorization for the request in VAGovDB</step>
        <step id="S4">Backend queries Single POA Request with detailed information in VAGovDB</step>

        <step id="S6">Frontend displays POA Details</step>

</useCase>

        <step id="S2">Frontend sends POST request to Backend for /v0/accredited_representative_portal/poa_requests/{id}/decision</step>

        <step id="S4">Backend submits POA Decision to LighthouseAPI</step>

            <step id="A1S5">Frontend displays Success, Updated Status & Submission Status</step>

        <step id="S3">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot transacts using RunTransactionRequest</step>
        <alt id="A1" start="S3">
            <step id="A1S1">Web3SigningCredential is CACTUSKEYCHAINREF</step>
            <step id="A1S2">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot transactsCactusKeychainRef</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Return RunTransactionResponse</step>
        </alt>
        <step id="S4">Return RunTransactionResponse</step>
        <step id="S5">Check if Web3SigningCredential is MNEMONICSTRING</step>
        <step id="S6">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot transactsMnemonicString</step>
        <step id="S7">Return RunTransactionResponse</step>
        <step id="S8">Check if Web3SigningCredential is NONE and req.transactionConfig.transferSubmittable</step>
        <step id="S9">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot transactsSigned</step>
        <step id="S10">Return RunTransactionResponse</step>
        <step id="S11">Throw Error: Expected pre-signed raw transaction</step>

</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Add a Person to a Deposit Group</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Archivist</actor>
        <actor>User & Group Management</actor>
        <actor>Data Storage</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Archivist adds a person to a deposit group by calling AddPersonToGroup(personId, groupId) on User & Group Management.</step>
        <step id="S2">User & Group Management checks if the group exists by calling CheckGroupExists(groupId) on Data Storage.</step>
        <step id="S3">Data Storage responds with GroupExistsResult.</step>
        <step id="S4">User & Group Management checks if the person is not already in the group by calling CheckPersonNotInGroup(personId, groupId) on Data Storage.</step>
        <step id="S5">Data Storage responds with PersonNotInGroupResult.</step>
        <step id="S6">If the group exists and the person is not already in the group, User & Group Management adds the person to the group by calling AddPersonToGroup(personId, groupId) on Data Storage.</step>
        <step id="S7">Data Storage responds with AdditionSuccess.</step>
        <step id="S8">User & Group Management sends a SuccessMessage("Person added") to the Archivist.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

          \<actor>Tarn\</actor>\

          \<actor>postgresDB\</actor>\
     \</actors>\
     \<preconditions>\
          \<precondition>Knex and Bookshelf dependencies are properly installed\</precondition>\
     \</preconditions>\

          \<step id="S4">node_postgres receives and validates the authentication request\</step>\
          \<step id="S5">postgresDB confirms the successful connection\</step>\
          \<step id="S6">Knex adds multiple connections to the pool using 'Add'\</step>\
          \<step id="S7">Knex creates the knex instance\</step>\
          \<step id="S8">Code includes Bookshelf and passes the knex instance\</step>\
          \<step id="S9">Code fetches all recipes using 'Recipe().fetchAll()'\</step>\
          \<step id="S10">Bookshelf executes query 'knex.from('recipe').select()'\</step>\
          \<step id="S11">Knex retrieves a connection from the pool\</step>\

          \<step id="S13">Knex queries node_postgres for recipe data with obtained connection\</step>\
          \<step id="S4">node_postgres selects recipe data from the database table 'recipe'\</step>\

          \<step id="S16">Knex fetches the data from node_postgres and releases the connection back to the pool\</step>\
          \<step id="S17">Knex retrieves recipes from Bookshelf\</step>\

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Process Video Download</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>REST API Client</actor>
        <actor>API Gateway (Video Service)</actor>
        <actor>Asynchronous Download Lambda</actor>
        <actor>DynamoDB (Video Metadata)</actor>
        <actor>S3 (Video Storage)</actor>
        <actor>External Video Hosting</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">REST API Client posts video URL to API Gateway (Video Service).</scenario>
        <step id="S2">API Gateway requests and fetches video information from External Video Hosting.</step>
        <step id="S3">API Gateway stores video info in DynamoDB and receives a UUID.</step>
        <step id="S4">API Gateway triggers Download Lambda asynchronously with video payload and UUID.</step>
        <step id="S5">Download Lambda updates video status to 'downloading' in DynamoDB.</step>
        <step id="S6">Download Lambda downloads video file from External Video Hosting.</step>
        <step id="S7">Download Lambda uploads downloaded video file to S3.</step>
        <step id="S8">Download Lambda updates video status to 'downloaded' in DynamoDB.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Request Processing</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Gateway</actor>
        <actor>UserSecurityService</actor>
        <actor>ServiceA</actor>
        <actor>ServiceB</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User initiates a request</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User sends a request to the Gateway.</step>
        <step id="S2">Gateway validates user's token with UserSecurityService.</step>
        <step id="S3">UserSecurityService confirms the validity of the token.</step>
        <step id="S4">Gateway forwards the request to the appropriate service (ServiceA).</step>
        <step id="S5">ServiceA processes the request and sends a response to Gateway.</step>
        <step id="S6">Gateway returns the response to the User.</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S2">
            <step id="A1S1">If the token is invalid, Gateway denies access to the User.</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S1">
            <step id="A2S1">If the request is from a service, Gateway checks the x-server-name header.</step>
            <asteps id="A2S2">
                <step id="A2S2S1">If the header is present, Gateway validates the service token.</step>
                <asteps id="A2S3" start="A2S2S1">
                    <step id="A2S3S1">If the service token is valid, Gateway forwards the request to ServiceB.</step>
                    <step id="A2S3S2">ServiceB processes the request and sends the response to Gateway.</step>
                    <step id="A2S3S3">Gateway forwards the response to ServiceA.</step>
                </asteps>
                <asteps id="A2S4" start="A2S2S1">
                    <step id="A2S4S1">If the service token is invalid, Gateway denies access to ServiceA.</step>
                </asteps>
            </asteps>
            <asteps id="A3" start="A2S1">
                <step id="A3S1">If the x-server-name header is absent, Gateway denies access to ServiceA.</step>
            </asteps>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Request Audit Report</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Repoadmin</actor>
        <actor>Audit & Reporting Service</actor>
        <actor>EDRMS Database</actor>
        <actor>Report Generator</actor>
        <actor>Audit Log</actor>
        <actor>Email Service</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Repoadmin requests an audit report.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Audit report is successfully generated and delivered.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Repoadmin requests an audit report from the Audit & Reporting Service.</step>
        <step id="S2">Audit & Reporting Service queries the EDRMS Database for audit data.</step>
        <step id="S3">EDRMS Database provides the audit data to the Audit & Reporting Service.</step>
        <step id="S4">Audit & Reporting Service generates the report using the audit data.</step>
        <step id="S5">Report Generator delivers the audit report to the Audit & Reporting Service.</step>
        <step id="S6">Audit & Reporting Service logs the report request in the Audit Log.</step>
        <step id="S7">Audit & Reporting Service delivers the audit report to Repoadmin.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

   <name>Execute Pomodoro Task</name>
   <description>Allows the user to start a Pomodoro task using the CLI interface</description>
   <actors>
      <actor>User</actor>
   </actors>
   <preconditions>
      <precondition>User initiates the task functionality by executing 'pomogo --task "programuj pomodoro"'.</precondition>
   </preconditions>
   <mainSequence>
      <step id="S1">User executes the command "pomogo --task 'programuj pomodoro'".</step>
      <step id="S2">The CLI registers a new task.</step>
      <step id="S3">The TaskStartHandler saves the new task named "programuj pomodoro" with the start date and other details.</step>
   </mainSequence>
   <alternativeSteps>
      <asteps id="A1" start="#S3">
         <step id="A1S1">The TimeTrigger triggers a refresh.</step>
         <step id="A1S2">Renderer fetches tasks from the database.</step>
         <step id="A1S3">The Renderer renders a beautiful progress bar with animations and unicorns to the User.</step>
      </asteps>
      <asteps id="A2" start="#S3">
         <step id="A2S1">The TaskStateChangeHandler saves a new state (resting) and increments the rest marker. Notifications are triggered via NotificationPlayer.</step>
      </asteps>
      <asteps id="A3" start="#S3">
         <step id="A3S1">The TaskStateChangeHandler saves a new state (deep resting) and zeroes the rest marker. Notifications are triggered via NotificationPlayer.</step>
      </asteps>
      <asteps id="A4" start="#S3">
         <step id="A4S1">The TaskStateChangeHandler saves a new state (resting) and increments the rest marker. Notifications are triggered via NotificationPlayer.</step>
      </asteps>
      <asteps id="A5" start="#S3">
         <step id="AS5S1">The TaskStateChangeHandler marks the task as paused and triggers sound notifications. Eventually, rendering finishes with a message including unicorns displayed to the User.</step>
      </asteps>
   </alternativeSteps>
</useCase>

    </failureEndConditions>

        <step id="S4">DPIE App selects appropriate sources based on reliability & quality</step>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Delete Account</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>API_Controller</actor>
        <actor>Service_Layer</actor>
        <actor>Repository</actor>
        <actor>Logging_Service</actor>
        <actor>Unit_of_Work</actor>
    </actors>
    <trigger>GET /delete-account?email&token</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User requests to delete account</step>
        <step id="S2">API_Controller validates Email and Token</step>
        <step id="S3">API_Controller sends 400 Bad Request if Email or Token is missing</step>
        <step id="S4">API_Controller calls Service_Layer for validation</step>
        <step id="S5">Service_Layer retrieves User by email asynchronously</step>
        <step id="S6">Service_Layer handles exception: "User not found"</step>
        <step id="S7">Service_Layer validates Token</step>
        <step id="S8">Service_Layer sends exception: "Invalid token" if Token is invalid</step>
        <step id="S9">API_Controller requests Service_Layer to delete account</step>
        <step id="S10">Service_Layer retrieves User by email asynchronously</step>
        <step id="S11">Service_Layer removes User from Repository</step>
        <step id="S12">Service_Layer logs Account Deletion</step>
        <step id="S13">Service_Layer commits the deletion in Unit_of_Work</step>
        <step id="S14">Service_Layer responds with SystemUserDto to API_Controller</step>
        <step id="S15">API_Controller sends 200 OK with success message to User</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="1">
    <name>Obtain Most Popular Monthly Dishes Report</name>
    <description>Description: Retrieve and display a report of the most frequently ordered dishes for the current month.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>Manager</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Manager must be logged into the system.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>The report of most popular monthly dishes is successfully displayed to the Manager.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>No data is available for the current month to generate the report.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>Manager requests the "Monthly Popular Dishes" report.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Manager selects the "Monthly Popular Dishes" report.</step>
        <step id="S2">UI Dashboard sends a request for the most frequently ordered food items for the month to the Backend Server.</step>
        <step id="S3">Backend Server queries the ordered food data for the current month in the Database.</step>
        <step id="S4">If data is available:
            <alternativeSteps id="A1" start="#S4" continue="">
                <step id="A1S1">Database returns the ordered food data for the month to the Backend Server.</step>
                <step id="A1S2">Backend Server processes the data to find the most frequently ordered dishes.</step>
                <step id="A1S3">Backend Server sends the report of most frequently ordered food items to the UI Dashboard.</step>
            </alternativesSteps>
        If no data is available:
            <alternativeSteps id="A2" start="#S4" continue="A1">
                <step id="A1S1">Database returns an empty result to the Backend Server.</step>
                <step id="A1S2">Backend Server sends a no data message to the UI Dashboard.</step>
                <step id="A1S3">UI Dashboard displays a message indicating no data is available.</step>
            </alternativeSteps>
</mainSequence>
</useCase>

    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Search for Similar Videos</name>
    <description>User searches for videos similar to a selected video.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Search Interface</actor>
        <actor>Content Identification Service</actor>
        <actor>Database</actor>
        <actor>Content Recommendation Engine</actor>
        <actor>Video Processing Module</actor>
        <actor>User Interface (UI)</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User is logged in and has selected a video to find similar content.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User enters search criteria for similar videos in the Search Interface.</step>
        <step id="S2">Search Interface processes the search criteria.</step>
        <step id="S3">Content Identification Service queries video fingerprints & metadata in the Database.</step>
        <step id="S4">Content Identification Service lists candidate videos based on fingerprinting.</step>
        <step id="S5">Content Identification Service suggests perceptually similar videos to the Search Interface.</step>
        <step id="S6">Search Interface requests recommendations based on candidates from the Content Recommendation Engine.</step>
        <step id="S7">Content Recommendation Engine fetches enhanced metadata & user profiles from the Database.</step>
        <step id="S8">Content Recommendation Engine returns enriched data to the Search Interface.</step>
        <step id="S9">Search Interface requests detailed comparison & segments from the Video Processing Module.</step>
        <step id="S10">Video Processing Module retrieves video segments & features from the Database.</step>
        <step id="S11">Video Processing Module provides detailed segment info for similar videos to the Search Interface.</step>
        <step id="S12">Search Interface displays similar videos and segment details to the User Interface.</step>
        <step id="S13">User Interface shows results & interactive video segments to the User.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Create Tenant</name>
    <description>Create a new tenant in the system.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>TenantsController</actor>
        <actor>TenantService</actor>
        <actor>TenantDbContext</actor>
        <actor>ApplicationDbContext</actor>
        <actor>ITenantContextService</actor>
        <actor>IConfiguration</actor>
        <actor>IServiceProvider</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>No existing tenant with the same Id.</preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>Tenant is successfully created.</successEndConditions>
    <trigger>POST /createTenant endpoint is called with new Tenant data.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User sends a request to create a new Tenant.</step>
        <step id="S2">TenantsController receives a POST request to create a new Tenant with Tenant data.</step>
        <step id="S3">TenantsController validates the model data.</step>
        <step id="S4">TenantsController checks if the Tenant already exists by calling TenantExistsAsync(Id).</step>
        <step id="S5">TenantService validates model and checks if the tenant exists in the TenantDbContext.</step>
        <step id="S6">If the Tenant does not exist:</step>
        <asteps id="A1">
            <step id="A1S1">TenantService creates a new Tenant.</step>
            <step id="A1S2">TenantService inserts the new Tenant into the TenantDbContext.</step>
            <step id="A1S3">TenantDbContext saves changes.</step>
            <step id="A1S4">If Isolated==true:</step>
            <asteps id="A1S4">
                <step id="A1S4S1">TenantService gets the connection string from IConfiguration.</step>
                <step id="A1S4S2">TenantService gets the ApplicationDbContext instance via IServiceProvider.</step>
                <step id="A1S4S3">IServiceProvider resolves an instance of ApplicationDbContext.</step>
                <step id="A1S4S4">ApplicationDbContext sets the connection string.</step>
                <step id="A1S4S5">ApplicationDbContext checks for pending migrations.</step>
                <step id="A1S4S6">ApplicationDbContext applies migrations.</step>
            </asteps>
            <step id="A1S5">TenantService updates the Tenant context.</step>
            <step id="A1S6">ITenantContextService sets the Tenant asynchronously.</step>
            <step id="A1S7">TenantsController returns the newly created Tenant.</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S7">If the Tenant already exists:</step>
        <asteps id="A2">
            <step id="A2S1">TenantService returns an error stating that the Tenant already exists.</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S8">TenantsController responds to the User with "201 Created" indicating the Tenant has been successfully created.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
	<name>Create Tenant</name>

		<step id="S1">User sends a POST request to create a new Tenant with relevant Tenant data.</step>
		<step id="S2">TenantsController validates the submitted Tenant data.</step>
		<step id="S3">TenantsController checks if the Tenant with the specified Id already exists.</step>
		<asteps id="A1" start="S3">
			<step id="A1S1">The Tenant does not exist in the system.</step>
			<step id="A1S2">TenantService creates a new Tenant.</step>
			<step id="A1S3">TenantService inserts the new Tenant into the database.</step>
			<step id="A1S4">TenantService saves the changes to the database.</step>
			<asteps id="A2">
				<step id="A2S1">TenantService retrieves connection string from IConfiguration.</step>
				<step id="A2S2">TenantService gets an instance of ApplicationDbContext from IServiceProvider.</step>
				<step id="A2S3">ApplicationDbContext sets the connection string.</step>				
				<step id="A2S4">ApplicationDbContext checks and applies pending migrations.</step>
			</asteps>		
			<step id="A1S5">TenantContextService updates the Tenant context in the application.</step>
			<step id="A1S6">TenantsController returns the newly created Tenant.</step>
		</asteps>
		<asteps id="E1" start="S3">
			<description>A Tenant with the specified Id already exists.</description>
			<step id="E1S1">TenantService notifies TenantsController that the requested Tenant already exists.</step>
		</asteps>
        <step id="S4">TenantsController informs the User that the Tenant has been successfully created with a 201 Created status.</step>	
	</mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="Expiration Management">
    <name>Expiration Management Use Case</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Collection Curator</actor>
        <actor>Web Interface</actor>
        <actor>EDRMS Server</actor>
        <actor>Repository Database</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Collection Curator selects item(s) for expiration</precondition>
        <precondition>Web Interface allows selection of item(s) with expiration parameters</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Collection Curator selects item(s) for expiration</step>
        <step id="S2">Web Interface sends item(s) and expiration parameters to EDRMS Server</step>
        <step id="S3">EDRMS Server queries and updates item(s) with expiration date in Repository Database</step>
        <step id="S4">EDRMS Server schedules task for item(s) expiration</step>
        <step id="S5">EDRMS Server checks for expired items every night at 12:00 AM</step>
        <step id="S6">EDRMS Server queries for items to hide/delete from Repository Database</step>
        <step id="S7">EDRMS Server updates item(s) status to hidden or deletes item(s) in Database</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Item(s) expiration date set and task scheduled successfully</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <trigger>Item selection by Collection Curator</trigger>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Run Transaction Endpoint</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Caller</actor>
        <actor>PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Caller activates the PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot</step>
        <step id="S2">Caller sends a transact(RunTransactionRequest) to PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot</step>
        <step id="S3">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot checks if web3SigningCredential is CACTUSKEYCHAINREF</step>
        <step id="S4">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot executes transactCactusKeychainRef(RunTransactionRequest)</step>
        <step id="S5">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot returns RunTransactionResponse to Caller</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S3" continue="S4">
            <step id="A1S1">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot checks if web3SigningCredential is MNEMONICSTRING</step>
            <step id="A1S2">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot executes transactMnemonicString(RunTransactionRequest)</step>
            <step id="A1S3">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot returns RunTransactionResponse to Caller</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S3" continue="S6">
            <step id="A2S1">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot checks if web3SigningCredential is NONE</step>
            <step id="A2S2">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot executes transactSigned(RunTransactionRequest)</step>
            <step id="A2S3">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot returns RunTransactionResponse to Caller</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A3" start="S3" continue="S7">
            <step id="A3S1">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot throws Error: Expected pre-signed raw transaction</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A4" start="S3" continue="S8">
            <step id="A4S1">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot throws Error: Unrecognized Web3SigningCredentialType</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
</useCase>

content:
<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Run Transaction Endpoint</name>
    <description>Use case for running a transaction endpoint in Hyperledger Cactus system.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot</actor>
        <actor>Caller</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Activate Caller.</step>
        <step id="S2">Caller calls transact(RunTransactionRequest) method on PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot.</step>
        <step id="S3">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot checks web3SigningCredential.</step>
        <step id="S4" actor="PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot">If web3SigningCredential == CACTUSKEYCHAINREF, PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot executes transactCactusKeychainRef(RunTransactionRequest).</step>
        <step id="S5" actor="PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot">Returns RunTransactionResponse.</step>
        <step id="S6">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot sends RunTransactionResponse to Caller.</step>
        <step id="S7">If web3SigningCredential == MNEMONICSTRING, PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot executes transactMnemonicString(RunTransactionRequest).</step>
        <step id="S8" actor="PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot">Returns RunTransactionResponse.</step>
        <step id="S9">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot sends RunTransactionResponse to Caller.</step>
        <step id="S10" actor="PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot">If web3SigningCredential == NONE:</step>
        <step id="S11">If req.transactionConfig.transferSubmittable is defined:</step>
        <step id="S12">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot executes transactSigned(RunTransactionRequest).</step>
        <step id="S13" actor="PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot">Returns RunTransactionResponse.</step>
        <step id="S14">PluginLedgerConnectorPolkadot sends RunTransactionResponse to Caller.</step>
        <step id="S15">Otherwise, throws Error: Expected pre-signed raw transaction.</step>
        <step id="S16">If web3SigningCredential does not match any condition, throws Error: Unrecognized Web3SigningCredentialType.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

content:
<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Create Keychain Entry</name>
    <description>User A wants to create a new keychain entry in AWS Secrets Manager via Hyperledger Cactus.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>User A</actor>
        <actor>API Client</actor>
        <actor>API Server</actor>
        <actor>AWS SM Connector</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>The API Client is properly configured and ready to send requests to the API Server.</precondition>
        <precondition>The AWS Secrets Manager is accessible and the necessary permissions are granted.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>The key-value pair is successfully set in AWS Secrets Manager.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>An error is encountered during the attempt to set the key-value pair in AWS Secrets Manager.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>User A triggers the transaction by calling the Tx HasKeychainEntryV1 function.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User A requests to create a new keychain entry through the API Client.</step>
        <step id="S2">The API Client forwards the request to the API Server.</step>
        <step id="S3">The API Server initiates a call to set the key-value pair in AWS Secrets Manager.</step>
        <step id="S4">The AWS SM Connector sets the key-value pair by interacting with AWS Secrets Manager.</step>
        <step id="S5">The AWS SM Connector retrieves the AWS client required to describe the secret.</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S5">
            <step id="A1S1">The AWS SM Connector attempts to describe the secret.</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S6">The AWS SM Connector verifies the existence of the secret in AWS Secrets Manager. If successful, continues to response generation, else proceeds to error handling.</step>
        <step id="S7">The AWS SM Connector responds to the API Server that the secret exists, leading to the proper request handling.</step>
        <step id="S8">The API Server forwards the response to the API Client.</step>
        <step id="S9">The API Client formats the received response.</step>
        <step id="S10">The API Client provides the SetKeychainEntryResponse to User A.</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S6" continue="A1S1">
            <step id="A1S2">An error occurs while describing the secret, flows into error handling.</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
    <errorSteps>
        <esteps id="E1" start="A1S2">
            <description>A failure occurs in describing the secret.</description>
            <step id="E1S1">Error: Secrets Manager can't find the specified secret.</step>
            <step id="E1S2">The error situation is managed by AWS SM Connector via an error response to the API Server.</step>
        </esteps>
    </errorSteps>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Has Keychain Entry Transaction</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User A</actor>
        <actor>API Client</actor>
        <actor>API Server</actor>
        <actor>AWS SM Connector</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User A initiates the transaction to set keychain entry</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <trigger>Tx HasKeychainEntryV1</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User A initiates a request to set a keychain entry through API Client</step>
        <step id="S2">API Client forwards the request to API Server</step>
        <step id="S3">API Server interacts with AWS Secrets Manager to set the key-value pair</step>
        <step id="S4">AWS Secrets Manager gets the AWS client</step>
        <step id="S5">In AWS Secrets Manager Connector:</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S5">
            <step id="A1S1">Describe the secret in AWS Secret Manager</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S6">AWS Secrets Manager responds with the secret details</step>
        <step id="S7">API Server sends a response with formatted data to API Client</step>
        <step id="S8">API Client processes the response</step>
        <step id="S9">User A receives a SetKeychainEntryResponse</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>
