<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Check Policy Modification for Object or Component</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>DAMS Manager</actor>
        <actor>DIMS Interface</actor>
        <actor>Policy Management Module</actor>
        <actor>Object/Component Database</actor>
        <actor>Event and Integrity Monitoring</actor>
        <actor>Notification System</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">DAMS Manager requests policy modification status from DIMS Interface</step>
        <step id="S2">Interface queries modification status for object/component from Policy Management Module</step>
        <step id="S3">Policy Module retrieves current policy data from Object/Component Database</step>
        <step id="S4">Database returns policy data to Policy Module</step>
        <step id="S5">Policy Module requests last modification details from Event and Integrity Monitoring</step>
        <step id="S6">Event Monitor returns modification events (manual/automatic) to Policy Module</step>
        <step id="S7">Policy Module provides modification status and details to DIMS Interface</step>
        <step id="S8">DIMS Interface displays policy modification status and details to DAMS Manager</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC002">
    <name>Notification on Policy Change</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Event and Integrity Monitoring</actor>
        <actor>Object/Component Database</actor>
        <actor>Notification System</actor>
        <actor>DAMS Manager</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Event Monitor monitors policy changes in Database</step>
        <step id="S2">Database notifies Event Monitor of policy update event</step>
        <step id="S3">Event Monitor triggers policy change notification to Notification System</step>
        <step id="S4">Notification System sends policy change alert to DAMS Manager</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Adding a Comment to an Article</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>System</actor>
        <actor>Controller</actor>
        <actor>ArticleService</actor>
        <actor>CommentService</actor>
        <actor>ArticleRepo</actor>
        <actor>CommentRepo</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>User is authenticated and on the article page</preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>Comment successfully added to the article</successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>Comment could not be added due to session validation error or an error during the addition process</failureEndConditions>
    
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User navigates to the article page</step>
        <step id="S2">User requests to add a comment</step>
        <step id="S3">Controller retrieves article details</step>
        <step id="S4">ArticleService queries article by slug and retrieves article details</step>
        <step id="S5">Controller receives article details</step>
        <step id="S6">Controller adds comment to the article</step>
        <step id="S7">CommentService saves the comment</step>
        <step id="S8">CommentService sends success response to Controller</step>
        <step id="S9">Controller updates the article page with the new comment</step>
        <step id="S10">System displays the updated article page with the comment to User</step>
    </mainSequence>
    
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S2" continue="S3">
            <step id="A1S1">Error handling for session validation error</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Render error page and display error message "Error saving comment"</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S5" continue="S6">
            <step id="A2S1">Error handling for error during the addition process</step>
            <step id="A2S2">Render error page and display error message "Error saving comment"</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>User application performs station keeping maneuver</name>
    <description>The user application initiates and monitors a station keeping maneuver through various interacting components.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>User application (Main)</actor>
        <actor>Propagator</actor>
        <actor>EphemerisGenerator</actor>
        <actor>BoundedPropagator</actor>
        <actor>AdapterPropagator</actor>
        <actor>Small maneuver</actor>
        <actor>J₂ due to maneuver</actor>
        <actor>StationKeepingMonitorHandler</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User application gets Ephemeris Generator</step>
        <step id="S2">Propagator creates Ephemeris Generator</step>
        <step id="S3">User application propagates</step>
        <step id="S4">User application gets generated Ephemeris from Ephemeris Generator
            <actors>User application</actors>
        </step>
        <step id="S5">Ephemeris Generator creates Bounded Propagator</step>
        
        <!-- Loop for optimization attempts with two nested loops for maneuvers and handling steps -->
        <step id="S6">User application creates Adapter Propagator</step>
        <!-- Nested Loop for maneuvers -->
        <asteps id="A1">
            <step id="A1S1">User application creates Small maneuver</step>
            <step id="A1S2">User application adds direct maneuver effect to Adapter Propagator
                <actors>Adapter Propagator (Applying direct maneuver effect)</actors>
            </step>
            <step id="A1S3">User application creates J₂ due to maneuver</step>
            <step id="A1S4">User application adds indirect J₂ effect to Adapter Propagator
                <actors>Adapter Propagator (Applying indirect J₂ effect)</actors>
            </step>
        </asteps>
        <!-- End of Nested for maneuvers -->
        
        <!-- Continue in Loop Section -->
        <step id="S7">User application registers SK monitor</step>
        <step id="S8">User application propagates through Adapter Propagator-Bounded Propagator chain</step>
        
        <!-- Nested Loops for q steps and for n maneuvers inside each q step -->
        <asteps id="A2">
            <esteps id="E1">
                <step id="E1S1">Activities in each q Example</step>
            </esteps>
            <!-- Nested for n maneuvers -->
            <asteps id="A3">
                <step id="A3S1">Adapter Propagator applies Small maneuver</step>
                <step id="A3S2">Adapter Propagator applies J₂ maneuver</step>
            </asteps>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A4">
            <step id="A4S1">Send final state information to user application</step>
        </asteps>
        
        <step id="S9">User application checks Station Keeping goals</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Checking Planned Provenance & Calculating Submission Fees</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Repository Owner</actor>
        <actor>DMPTool Interface</actor>
        <actor>DMP Database</actor>
        <actor>Provenance Checker</actor>
        <actor>Fee Calculator</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Repository Owner accesses DMPTool through DMPTool Interface.</step>
        <step id="S2">DMPTool Interface retrieves project DMP from DMP Database.</step>
        <step id="S3">DMP Database returns DMP data to DMPTool Interface.</step>
        <step id="S4">DMPTool Interface shows DMP data to Repository Owner including provenance.</step>
        <step id="S5">Repository Owner requests provenance check through DMPTool Interface.</step>
        <step id="S6">DMPTool Interface validates provenance data with Provenance Checker.</step>
        <step id="S7">Provenance Checker accesses relevant metadata from DMP Database.</step>
        <step id="S8">DMP Database provides metadata to Provenance Checker.</step>
        <step id="S9">Provenance Checker returns check results to DMPTool Interface.</step>
        <step id="S10">If Provenance is Valid, Provenance Checker confirms data is within target group to Repository Owner.</step>

<useCase id="1">
    <name>Point Calculation Process</name>
    <actors>User</actors>

        <step id="S1">User moves the map to initiate the process</step>
        <step id="S2">Calculate area in the Frontend with backend support</step>
        <step id="S3">Add the calculated area to the Split Queue</step>
        <step id="S4">Retrieve depth in the added area from the Backend</step>
        <step id="S5">Request Points in depth from the database</step>
        <step id="S6">Receive Points in Area from the database</step>
        <step id="S7">Request for points not already calculated</step>
        <step id="S8">Backend receives request for undefined points in-depth</step>
        <step id="S9">Backend calculates undefined points in depth</step>
        <step id="S10">Updates the Points database with the calculated points</step>
        <step id="S11">Points in depth updated successfully in the database</step>
        <step id="S12">Insert with undefined depth into database Split Map and update with calculated points</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="001">
   <name>Select Road Information</name>
   <actors>User, Application</actors>
   <preconditions>The user connects to the map and selects the area and road type</preconditions>
   <mainSequence>
       <step id="S1">User selects map path and map type in the Application</step>
       <step id="S2">MapEngine triggers data parsing in MapImport</step>
       <step id="S3">MapImport transforms data to data model</step>
       <step id="S4">MapImport inserts map data into Rtree</step>
       <step id="S5">MapImport sends status code response to MapEngine</step>
       <step id="S6">MapEngine sends status code response to Application</step>
       <step id="S7">User requests Road Information by calling getRoads in the Application</step>
       <step id="S8">MapEngine searches and retrieves roads data with searchRoads in MemSearch</step>
       <step id="S9">MemSearch further looks up for the lane information with searchLanes in the Rtree</step>
       <step id="S10">MemSearch sends road pointers to MapEngine via the txRoads method</step>
       <step id="S11">MapEngine delivers road pointers to Application by txRoads method</step>
       <step id="S12">User seeks Road Lane Links Information by requesting getLaneLinks in the Application</step>
       <step id="S13">MapEngine queries and obtains the lane links by executing searchLaneLinks in MemSearch</step>
       <step id="S14">MemSearch transmits lane links information to MapEngine through txLaneLinks method</step>
       <step id="S15">MapEngine supplies lane connections details back to Application via method txLaneLinks</step>
       <step id="S16">User prompts for Objects related to road query through getObjects function in Application</step>
       <step id="S17">MapEngine conducts 3Objects searching in the Rtree with searchObjects usecase that finds road objects</step>
       <step id="S18">MemSearch replies with the road object information upon searching and executes txObjects method onwards for returning</step>
       <step id="S19">MapEngine sends the road object information gathered to Application by implementing txObjects finalized action</step>
   </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Attore faces a challenge and overcomes it</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Attore</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Attore faces a challenge</step>
        <step id="S2">Attore receives a command</step>
        <step id="S3">Command receives input and sends it to Logic</step>
        <step id="S4">Logic starts handling the challenge</step>

        <asteps id="A1" start="S5">
            <step id="A1S1">Logic performs temple riddles</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Command verifies the outcome of the riddles</step>

            <alt id="A2">Outcome: Correct result
                <step id="A1S3">Logic confirms correct solution and grants access</step>
                <step id="A1S4">Command proceeds to the next room</step>
            else Outcome: Incorrect result
                <step id="A1S5">Logic reverses to previous stage of the challenge</step>
            </alt>
        </asteps>
        
        <esteps id="E1" start="A1S3">
            <description>Failure: Access denied due to an incorrect result</description>
            <step id="E1S1">Logic exits the challenge</step>
        </esteps>
        
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Confront challenges in the adventure game</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Attore</actor>
    </actors>
    <description>Facing multiple challenges and making decisions accordingly.</description>
    <preconditions>Being in a challenging scenario with options to consider.</preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>Being able to progress through the game.</successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>Failing to advance further in the game.</failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>Triggers based on the actions taken during the challenges.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">The Attore faces a challenge by activating it programmatically.</step>
        <step id="S2">The Command receives the input command from the specific challenge activated by the Attore.</step>
        <step id="S3">Based on the challenge being an "Enigma," the logic in Command proceeds with solving riddles in the temple.</step>
        <step id="S4">The Command verifies the correctness of the result given by the Attore.</step>
        <step id="S5">As the correct answer is obtained, the Attore gains access to the next room.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Acquire Place</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Labgrid Client</actor>
        <actor>Labgrid Coordinator</actor>
        <actor>Place</actor>
        <actor>Boss Publisher</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User sends 'labgrid-client -p <place> acquire' command to Labgrid Client.</step>
        <step id="S2">Labgrid Client forwards the acquire command to Labgrid Coordinator.</step>
        <step id="S3">Labgrid Coordinator checks the acquire request with Place.</step>
        <step id="S4">Place confirms the request.</step>
        <step id="S5">Labgrid Coordinator notifies Labgrid Client of successful acquisition.</step>
        <step id="S6">User sends 'labgrid-client -p <place> console' command to Labgrid Client.</step>
        <step id="S7">Labgrid Client opens a connection to Boss Publisher.</step>
        <step id="S8">Boss Publisher establishes a session and displays configuration.</step>
        <step id="S9">User subscribes to updates for LED 1 and LED 2 with mode 'only_changes'.</step>
        <step id="S10">Boss Publisher sends an update: 'led_1: active True, color=green time: 1234567'.</step>
        <step id="S11">User polls settings for LED 1 and LED 2 with mode 'poll' and interval 1 second.</step>
        <loop>
            <step id="S12">Boss Publisher sends the current state of LEDs 1 and 2.</step>
        </loop>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Acquiring Place</name>
    <description>User acquires a place using Labgrid client.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Labgrid Client</actor>
        <actor>Labgrid Coordinator</actor>
        <actor>Place</actor>
        <actor>Boss Publisher</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>The Labgrid sequence is not finalized.</preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>User acquires the place successfully.</successEndConditions>
    <trigger>User triggers the acquisition process using Labgrid client.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>

        <step id="S1">User issues command to Labgrid client to acquire a place.</step>
        <step id="S2">Labgrid client asks Labgrid Coordinator to acquire the place.</step>
        <step id="S3">Labgrid Coordinator verifies the acquisition request with Place.</step>
        <step id="S4">Place confirms the acquisition request.</step>
        <step id="S5">Labgrid Coordinator notifies Labgrid client of successful acquisition.</step>
        <step id="S6">User receives confirmation message "Place acquired".</step>
        <step id="S7">User issues command to Labgrid client for console access to the acquired place.</step>
        <step id="S8">Labgrid client opens a connection with Boss Publisher for console access.</step>
        <step id="S9">Boss Publisher establishes a session with the user.</step>
        <step id="S10">User updates settings.</step>
        <step id="S11">User subscribes to changes for specific IDs.</step>
        <step id="S12">Boss Publisher receives the subscription request.</step>
        <step id="S13">Boss Publisher provides the initial configuration updates.</step>
        <step id="S14">User requests polling for specific IDs.</step>
        <step id="S15">Boss Publisher initiates polling.</step>
        <step id="S16">Boss Publisher sends periodic updates every 1 sec.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
  <name>Deposit Dataset to Bath Data Archive</name>
  <actors>
    <actor>Depositor</actor>
    <actor>Web Interface</actor>
    <actor>Pure Integration Module</actor>
    <actor>Dataset Management System</actor>
    <actor>Bath Data Archive</actor>
  </actors>
  <mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">
      Depositor accesses the deposit interface on the web UI.
    </step>
    <step id="S2">
      Web Interface requests authentication from Pure.
    </step>
    <step id="S3">
      Depositor fills in the dataset deposit form on the web UI including metadata and files.
    </step>
    <step id="S4">
      DMS processes the deposit form received from the web UI.
      <actor>Dataset Management System</actor>
    </step>
    <step id="S5">
      DMS checks if dataset metadata aligns with Pure requirements through Pure's integration module.
    </step>
    <step id="S6">
      DMS deposits dataset and metadata into the Bath Data Archive.
      <actor>Bath Data Archive</actor>
    </step>
    <step id="S7">
      Archive confirms the deposit and generates a DOI.
      <actor>Bath Data Archive</actor>
    </step>
    <step id="S8">
      DMS links the dataset DOI with Pure records through Pure's integration module.
      <actor>Pure Integration Module</actor>
    </step>
    <step id="S9">
      DMS confirms the dataset deposit and provides the DOI to the Depositor.
    </step>
    <step id="S10">
      Depositor is informed of the dataset deposit confirmation and the DOI link.
    </step>
  </mainSequence>
</useCase>

        <step id="S1">User sends GET request for medical conditions to API_Controller</step>
        <step id="S2">API_Controller validates the path parameter</step>

            <step id="A1S1">API_Controller responds with 400 Bad Request to User</step>

        <step id="S6">AllergyService sends list of medical conditions to API_Controller</step>
        <step id="S7">API_Controller responds with 200 OK containing medicalCondition data to User</step>
    </mainSequence>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Access Public Repositories</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User enters API token in Token Entry Component</step>
        <step id="S2">Token Service validates the token</step>
        <step id="S3">GitHub Service sends a test query</step>
        <step id="S4">GitHub Service returns validation result to Token Service</step>
        <step id="S5">Token Service returns token validation result to Token Entry Component</step>
        <step id="S6">User navigates to /repositories</step>
        <step id="S7">Route Guard allows navigation to Repository List Component</step>
        <step id="S8">Repository List Component fetches public repositories sorted by stars from GitHub Service</step>
        <step id="S9">GitHub Service returns repository list to Repository List Component</step>
        <step id="S10">Pagination Component renders pagination for repositories</step>
        <step id="S11">User selects a repository from Repository List Component</step>
        <step id="S12">Repository Detail Component navigates to repository detail view</step>
        <step id="S13">Repository Detail Component fetches repository details & issues sorted by creation date from GitHub Service</step>
        <step id="S14">GitHub Service returns repository details & issues to Repository Detail Component</step>
        <step id="S15">Pagination Component renders pagination for issues</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S6" continue="S7">
            <step id="A1S1">Display error message to User</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
    <errorSteps>
        <esteps id="E1" start="S12">
            <description>Click "Change API Token" in Header</description>
            <step id="E1S1">Token Service clears token</step>
            <step id="E1S2">Navigate back to token entry page in Token Entry Component</step>
        </esteps>
    </errorSteps>
</useCase>

    <name>Access GitHub Repository List</name>

                <step id="A1S5">Repository List Component renders pagination for repositories.</step>
                <step id="A1S6">User selects a repository from the list.</step>
                <step id="A1S7">Repository List Component navigates to the Repository Detail Component.</step>
                <step id="A1S8">Repository Detail Component fetches repository details & issues (sorted by creation date) from GitHub Service.</step>
                <step id="A1S9">GitHub Service returns repository details & issues to Repository Detail Component.</step>
                <step id="A1S10">Repository Detail Component renders pagination for issues.</step>
            </asteps>
        </step>
        <step id="S7">If token is invalid:
            <esteps id="E1" start="#S7">
                <description>User is displayed an error message.</description>
                <step id="E1S1">End of error steps.</step>
            </esteps>
        </step>
        <step id="S8">User clicks "Change API Token" button in Header.</step>
        <step id="S9">Header clears the token using Token Service.</step>
        <step id="S10">Header navigates back to the token entry page in Token Entry Component.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="1">
    <name>Perform API CRUD Operation</name>
    <description>File describes the process of handling CRUD operations through an API.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>Client</actor>
        <actor>API</actor>
        <actor>CommandHandler</actor>
        <actor>Repository</actor>
        <actor>Database</actor>
        <actor>DomainEntity</actor>
        <actor>QueryHandler</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>All necessary entities and connections initialized correctly.</preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>All data changes successfully saved in the Database.</condition>
        <condition>Notification sent to relevant components upon operation completion.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>SQL execution failed at any point.</condition>
        <condition>Entity mapping encounters errors during business logic process.</condition>
        <condition>Error in saving entity modifications to the Database.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>Type "create", "read", or "update" received from Client to API.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Client requests for create/read/update operation.</step>
        <step id="S2">API directs command to Command Handler for processing.</step>
        <step id="S3">Command Handler requests entity data from Repository.</step>
        <step id="S4">Repository executes SQL query in Database.</step>
        <step id="S5">Raw data is obtained by Repository from Database.</step>
        <step id="S6">Repository maps raw data to Entity using Factory.</step>
        <step id="S7">Command Handler applies business logic to Domain Entity.</step>
        <step id="S8">Command Handler saves modified entity to Repository.</step>
        <step id="S9">Repository runs entity change detection and converts to SQL.</step>
        <step id="S10">Database saves applied changes and notifies Repository.</step>
        <step id="S11">API receives Notification Object from Command Handler.</step>
        <step id="S12">API exchanges DTO(object) with Query Handler.</step>
        <step id="S13">DTO result obtained by and returned to Client by Query Handler.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Monitoring Weather Conditions</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Utilisateur</actor>
        <actor>Admin</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Users' coordinates are regularly checked in the database.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Alerts are successfully recorded and notifications are sent to users.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>No user coordinates are registered or the weather system is unresponsive.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Controleur checks users' coordinates in the database.</step>
        <step id="S2">BaseDeDonnees returns the geographical coordinates of users.</step>
        <step id="S3">Controleur queries SystemMeteo for weather data.</step>
        <step id="S4">SystemMeteo provides current and forecasted weather conditions to Controleur.</step>
        <step id="S5">Controleur analyzes weather conditions for anomalies or critical situations.</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S5">
            <step id="A1S1">If alert detected:</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Controleur records the alert type, time, and coordinates in BaseDeDonnees.</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Controleur prepares a notification for the user.</step>
            <step id="A1S4">Ecran sends the alert notification to Utilisateur.</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S5">
            <step id="A2S1">If no user coordinates registered:</step>
            <step id="A2S2">Controleur informs Ecran that the user is excluded from monitoring.</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A3" start="S5">
            <step id="A3S1">If weather system unresponsive:</step>
            <step id="A3S2">Controleur displays an error message on Ecran.</step>
            <step id="A3S3">Ecran notifies Admin that the weather system is offline.</step>
        </asteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Consultation des Conditions Météorologiques</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Utilisateur</actor>
        <actor>Admin</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Les coordonnées des utilisateurs sont enregistrées dans la base de données.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Les conditions météorologiques actuelles et prévisionnelles sont consultées avec succès.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <trigger>Le système doit vérifier régulièrement les coordonnées des utilisateurs.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Le contrôleur vérifie régulièrement les coordonnées des utilisateurs dans la base de données.</step>
        <step id="S2">La base de données retourne les coordonnées géographiques des utilisateurs au contrôleur.</step>
        <step id="S3">Le contrôleur interroge le système météorologique pour obtenir les données météorologiques.</step>
        <step id="S4">Le système météorologique retourne les conditions météorologiques actuelles et prévisionnelles au contrôleur.</step>
        <step id="S5">Le contrôleur analyse les conditions pour détecter des anomalies ou conditions critiques.</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Interact with BLE Mailbox Perpherial</name>
    <description>The user interacts with the BLE mailbox central and peripheral devices.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>BLE_Mailbox_Central</actor>
        <actor>BLE_Mailbox_Peripheral</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User initiated the interaction with the BLE mailbox system.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>State changes of locker requested have been completed successfully.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Errors occurred while changing the state of the locker.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User opens the BLE mailbox central.</step>
        <step id="S2">User requests to scan for devices.</step>
        <step id="S3">BLE mailbox central requests user permissions.</step>
        <step id="S4">Permissions granted by the user.</step>
        <step id="S5">BLE mailbox central scans for devices.</step>
        <step id="S6">User selects the desired BLE mailbox peripheral device.</step>
        <step id="S7">BLE mailbox central requests connection with BLE mailbox peripheral.</step>
        <step id="S8">Connection handshaking between BLE mailbox devices.</step>
        <step id="S9">BLE_Mailbox_Central requests the state of the locker from BLE_Mailbox_Peripheral.</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S10">
            <step id="S11">User signs in on the BLE mailbox central.</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S12">
            <step id="S13">User requests to change the state of the locker.</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
    <errorSteps>
        <esteps id="E1" start="S14">
            <description>Error occurred during signin process.</description>
            <step id="S15">Attention prompt: 'Cannot sign in; try again!'</step>
        </esteps>
        <esteps id="E2" start="S16">
            <description>Error in attempting to change the state of the locker.</description>
            <step id="S17">Issue prompt: 'Failed to change locker state; retry!'</step>
        </esteps>
    </errorSteps>
</useCase>

  <actors>
    <actor>Requestor</actor>
    <actor>Approvers</actor>
  </actors>
  <preconditions>
    <precondition>Requestor submits the project</precondition>
  </preconditions>
  <mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">Submit the project</step>
    <step id="S2">Add project</step>
    <step id="S3">Check add permission</step>
    <step id="S4">Validate content</step>
    <step id="S5">Display success page</step>
  </mainSequence>
  <failureEndConditions>
    <condition>Requestor is not authorized or content is invalid</condition>
  </failureEndConditions>
  <alternativeSteps>
    <asteps id="A1" start="S5">
      <step id="A1S1">Display failure page with error info</step>
    </asteps>
  </alternativeSteps>
  <alternativeSteps>
    <asteps id="A2" start="S5">
      <step id="A2S1">Add project with status "approved"</step>
      <step id="A2S2">Return project_id</step>
      <step id="A2S3">Display success page</step>
    </asteps>
  </alternativeSteps>
  <aterrorSteps>
      <esteps id="E1" start="Step5">
        <description>Error message to display</description>
        <step id="E1S1">Add project with status "awaiting_approval"</step>
        <step id="E1S2">Return project_id</step>
        <step id="E1S3">Send email to Approvers</step>
        <step id="E1S4">Display success page with message that project is pending approval</step>
    </esteps>
</aterrorSteps>
</useCase>

<useCase id="Example">
    <name>Checking health status and handling requests</name>
    <description>Ensures that incoming requests from Client are managed and processed.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>Client</actor>
        <actor>HealthMonitorAPI</actor>
        <actor>IpHandler</actor>
        <actor>ServiceRemovalHandler</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Client triggers a health status check for the requested IP address.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>HealthMonitorAPI confirms the health status as acceptable.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>ServiceRemovalHandler denies further request processing due to excessive requests.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>Client requests health check for a specific IP address.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Client initiates a health status check towards the HealthMonitorAPI.</step>
        <step id="S2">HealthMonitorAPI redirects the IP address check request to IpHandler for verification.</step>
        <step id="S3">Authenticated IpHandler registers the incoming request count and sender's IP address for analysis.</step>
        <asteps id="A1">
            <step id="A1S1">Check if the received request count from the sender exceeds the defined throttle limit.</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S4">If request count exceeds the threshold, forward the blocking request to ServiceRemovalHandler.</step>
        <step id="S5">ServiceRemovalHandler denies the requesting service and_ reports the denied message to IP handler.</step>
        <step id="S6">IpHandler notifies HealthMonitorAPI about the denied request and the appropriate validation message.</step>
        <step id="S8">HealthMonitorAPI returns the denial message to the client.</step>
        <asteps id="A2">
            <step id="A2S1">Request count is acceptable. Forward the request '_to acceptRequest functionality.’</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S8">HealthMonitorAPI responds with a health status message to the Client.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

	<name>Update User Information</name>
	<actors>
		<actor>User</actor>
	</actors>
	<preconditions>
		<precondition>The User Update Request must contain valid user data</precondition>
	</preconditions>
	<trigger>User invokes the Update User Information functionality</trigger>
	<mainSequence>
		<step id="S1">User calls UpdateUserRequest to execute with provided JSON data and mutex m</step>
		<step id="S2">UpdateUserRequest activates and requests a MutexLocker(&m)</step>
		<step id="S3">UpdateUserRequest extracts email, account number, and new data from the JSON object</step>
		<step id="S4">UpdateUserRequest receives user data from the JSON object</step>
		<step id="S5">If DB connection is invalid</step>
		<step id="S6">UpdateUserRequest verifies DB connection validity and triggers DB connection error handling</step>
		<step id="S7">If user role data is returned from the database</step>
		<step id="S8">UpdateUserRequest fetches and returns the user role from the database</step>
		<step id="S9">If user is found</step>
		<step id="S10">If user is not an admin</step>
		<step id="S11">If user is an admin, checks the account number</step>
		<step id="S12">If account is found</step>
		<step id="S13">UpdateUserRequest queries and retrieves the user data using the email</step>
		<step id="S14">If email is in use by another account</step>
		<step id="S15">UpdateUserRequest handles the scenario where email is associated with another account</step>
		<step id="S16">If email is available</step>
		<step id="S17">UpdateUserRequest updates the user information in the database</step>
		<step id="S18">If update fails</step>
		<step id="S19">UpdateUserRequest deals with the failed attempt to update user information</step>
		<step id="S20">If update is successful</step>
		<step id="S21">UpdateUserRequest constructs success response and serves it to the User</step>
	</mainSequence>
</ucl:useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Update User Account Information</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User triggers updating user account information</step>
		<step id="S2">Extract user email, account number, and new data from JSON object</step>
	    <alt conditions="DB connection invalid">
	        <step id="S3">Check if Database Connection is valid</step>
			<step id="S4">Create Database Connection Error</step>
			<step id="S5">Return Database Connection Error Response to User</step>
	    </alt>
		<alt conditions="DB connection valid">
		    <step id="S6">Retrieve user role from database</step>
			<alt conditions="User not found">
		        <step id="S7">Create error response for user not found</step>
		        <step id="S15">Return error response for user not found to User</step>
		    </alt>
			<alt conditions="User found">
				<step id="S8">Check if the user is admin</step>
				<alt conditions="Not admin">
					<step id="S9">Create error response for unauthorized user</step>
					<step id="S16">Return unauthorized response to User</step>
				</alt>
				<alt conditions="Admin">
					<step id="S10">Retrieve account data using account number</step>
					<alt conditions="Account not found">
		                <step id="S11">Create error response for account not found</step>
		                <step id="S17">Return error response for account not found to User</step>
		            </alt>
					<alt conditions="Account found">
						<step id="S12">Retrieve user data for new email provided</step>
						<alt conditions="Email in use">
					    	<step id="S13">Create error response for email already in use</step>
	                        <step id="S18">Return error response for email in use to User</step>
	    				</alt>
						<alt conditions="Email available">
							<sequenceCondition start="A1" continue="A1S1"/>
	    					<step id="S14">Update user information with new data</step>
		                    <sequenceCondition start="AS1"/>
		                    <step id="S20">Construct success response</step>
							<step id="S21">Return success response to User</step>
	    				</alt>
	    			</alt>
	    		</alt>
			</alt>
       	</alt>
	</mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC-001">
    <name>Manage File Upload and Licensing</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Cornell Faculty Member</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Cornell Faculty Member has a valid data file to upload</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <trigger>The Cornell Faculty Member decides to upload a file and apply a license to it.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Cornell Faculty Member selects a data file for upload on the browser interface.</step>
        <step id="S2">The Browser interface initiates the file upload process.</step>
        <step id="S3">The File Upload Service stores the data file in the Digital Repository.</step>
        <step id="S4">The Digital Repository saves file metadata, including uploader info to the Database.</step>
        <step id="S5">The Repository confirms the successful storage of metadata.</step>
        <step id="S6">The Repository confirms the successful storage of the data file.</step>
        <step id="S7">The Upload Service notifies the browser interface about the successful file upload.</step>
        <step id="S8">The Upload Service provides the Faculty Member with the file ID and upload confirmation.</step>
        <step id="S9">The Faculty Member chose the licensing option.</step>
        <step id="S10">The Browser interface sends the license choice and file ID to the Licensing Service.</step>
        <step id="S11">The Licensing Service applies the chosen license to the file via the DRM Service.</step>
        <step id="S11">The DRM Service updates the file metadata with the license information.</step>
        <step id="S12">The Repository updates the file record with license metadata in the Database.</step>
        <step id="S13">The Database confirms the successful update of license metadata.</step>
        <step id="S14">The Repository confirms the license application to the file.</step>
        <step id="S15">The License Service updates the Browser interface with the license application success notification.</step>
        <step id="S16">The Faculty Member confirms the license has been set on the file.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>
```

<useCase id="UC1">
  <name>Create Payments and Disbursements</name>
    
  <actors>
    <actor>User</actor>

    <actor>PROGRAM_SERVICE</actor>
    <actor>Expense_Service</actor>
    <actor>MDMS</actor>
    <actor>ORG_SERVICE</actor>
    <actor>IND_SERVICE</actor>
    <actor>BANK_ACC_SERVICE</actor>
    <actor>KAFKA</actor>
    <actor>SCHEDULER</actor>
  </actors>
  
  <preconditions>
    <precondition>User needs to be authenticated and authorized</precondition>

  <mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">User initiates Payment Creation through Scheduler</step>
    <step id="S2">MUKTA_ADAPTER requests for tenants from MDMS</step>

            <step id="A1S6">EntService updates admission status, role type, and contract address in MySQL</step>
            <step id="A1S7">Controller returns the approval result</step>
            <step id="A1S8">Vue receives and returns the approval result to Regulatory Agency</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S7">
            <step id="A2S1">Enterprise queries admission result</step>
            <step id="A2S2">Controller retrieves the admission result</step>
            <step id="A2S3">EntService queries admission contract content using JAVA SDK</step>
            <step id="A2S4">Controller returns the contract content</step>
            <step id="A2S5">Vue receives and returns the contract content to Enterprise</step>
            <step id="A2S6">Enterprise receives the result</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A3" start="S7">
            <step id="A3S1">Controller returns the rejection result</step>
            <step id="A3S2">Vue receives and returns the rejection result to Regulatory Agency</step>
            <step id="A3S3">Regulatory Agency receives the rejection result</step>
            <step id="A3S4">Enterprise queries for re-submission of admission data</step>
            <step id="A3S5">Enterprise submits new admission data to Vue</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>View Book Reviews</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Gateway</actor>
        <actor>Keycloak</actor>
        <actor>Review Service</actor>
        <actor>MongoDB</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User is authenticated and authorized to view book reviews.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>User successfully views the reviews for the specified book.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>JWT is absent or not valid, resulting in HTTP status 401 or 403.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>User requests to view reviews for a specific book.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User sends a GET request to Gateway to retrieve reviews for a specific book.</step>
        <step id="S2">Gateway verifies the JWT token with Keycloak.</step>
        <step id="S3">If JWT is valid:</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="A1S1" continue="S4">
            <step id="A1S1">Gateway forwards the request to Review Service to retrieve reviews for the book.</step>
            <step id="S4">Review Service queries MongoDB to find reviews for the specified book.</step>
            <step id="S5">MongoDB returns the list of reviews to Review Service.</step>
            <step id="S6">Review Service sends the review list back to Gateway.</step>
            <step id="S7">Gateway forwards the review list to the User.</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S8">If JWT is absent:</step>
        <esteps id="E1" start="E1S1">
            <description>Gateway returns HTTP status 401 to the User.</description>
            <step id="E1S1">End of the use case.</step>
        </esteps>
        <step id="S9">If JWT is not valid:</step>
        <esteps id="E2" start="E2S1">
            <description>Gateway returns HTTP status 403 to the User.</description>
            <step id="E2S1">End of the use case.</step>
        </esteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>View Book Reviews</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User is authenticated and authorized to view reviews.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Review list is successfully retrieved.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>HTTP Status 401 or 403 is returned.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>User requests to view reviews for a specific book.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User sends a GET request to retrieve reviews for a specific book.</step>
        <step id="S2">Gateway verifies the JWT token.</step>
        <step id="S3">If JWT is valid:</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S3">
            <step id="A1S1">Gateway forwards the request to the review service.</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Review service retrieves reviews for the specified book from MongoDB.</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Review service sends the review list back to the gateway.</step>
            <step id="A1S4">Gateway returns the review list to the user.</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S4">If JWT is absent:</step>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S4">
            <step id="A2S1">Gateway returns HTTP Status 401 to the user.</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S5">If JWT is not valid:</step>
        <asteps id="A3" start="S5">
            <step id="A3S1">Gateway returns HTTP Status 403 to the user.</step>
        </asteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Retrieve Book Reviews</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User requests to retrieve book reviews with a specific book ID.</step>
        <step id="S2">Gateway receives the request: GET /api/v1/books/{bookId}/reviews</step>
        <step id="S3">Gateway verifies the JWT token with Keycloak.</step>
        <alt id="A1" start="S3">
            <step id="A1S1">JWT token is valid.</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Gateway forwards the request to the Review service for GET /api/v1/books/{bookId}/reviews.</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Review service queries Mongo database to retrieve reviews based on the book ID.</step>
            <step id="A1S4">Mongo database returns the list of reviews to the Review service.</step>
            <step id="A1S5">Review service sends the review list to the Gateway.</step>
            <step id="A1S6">Gateway forwards the review list to the User.</step>
        </alt>
        <asteps id="A1">
            <!-- Asteps definition covered inside the alt block -->
        </asteps>
        <step id="S4">Else, JWT token is absent.</step>
            <step id="S5">Gateway responds with HttpStatus 401 to the User.</step>
        
        <step id="S6">Else, JWT token is not valid.</step>
            <step id="S7">Gateway responds with HttpStatus 403 to the User.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
	<name>View Book Reviews</name>
	<description>As a user, I want to view the reviews of a specific book.</description>
	<actors>User, gateway, Keycloak, review, Mongo</actors>
	<preconditions>The user is logged in and requests to view reviews for a specific book.</preconditions>
	<successEndConditions>The reviews for the specified book are successfully retrieved and displayed to the user.</successEndConditions>
	<failureEndConditions>The user does not have a valid JWT, leading to an HTTP 401 error, or the JWT is invalid, leading to an HTTP 403 error.</failureEndConditions>
	<trigger>The user sends a GET request to view book reviews.</trigger>
	<mainSequence>
		<step id="S1">User sends a GET request to /api/v1/books/{bookId}/reviews.</step>
		<step id="S2">Gateway processes the request and verifies the JWT with Keycloak.</step>
		<step id="S3">Keycloak validates the JWT.</step>
		<step id="S4" actor="review">Gateway sends a GET request to /api/v1/books/{bookId}/reviews to Review service.</step>
		<step id="S5" actor="mongo">Review service fetches reviews for the requested book.</step>
		<step id="S6">Review service provides the review list to Gateway.</step>
		<step id="S7">Gateway sends the review list to the User.</step>
	</mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Đăng xuất</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Manager</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Người dùng hoặc Quản lý thực hiện đăng xuất</step>
        <step id="S2">Nhấn nút "Đăng xuất" trên Giao diện chính</step>
        <step id="S3">Yêu cầu kết thúc phiên tới Hệ thống Quản lý Phiên</step>
        <step id="S4">Xác thực phiên hiện tại bởi Hệ thống Quản lý Phiên</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Phiên hợp lệ</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Phiên không hợp lệ</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>User hoặc Manager thực hiện đăng xuất</trigger>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Đăng xuất</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Manager</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Người dùng hoặc Quản lý thực hiện đăng xuất</step>
        <step id="S2">Nhấn nút "Đăng xuất"</step>
        <step id="S3">Yêu cầu kết thúc phiên</step>
        <step id="S4">Xác thực phiên hiện tại</step>
        <step id="S5">Xác nhận kết thúc phiên</step>
        <step id="S6">Hiển thị thông báo đăng xuất thành công</step>
        <step id="S7">Thông báo lỗi</step>
        <step id="S8">Hiển thị thông báo lỗi</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Phiên hợp lệ</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Phiên không hợp lệ</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
   <name>Đăng xuất khỏi hệ thống</name>
   <actors>
      <actor>User</actor>
      <actor>Manager</actor>
   </actors>
   <mainSequence>
      <step id="S1">Người dùng hoặc Quản lý thực hiện đăng xuất</step>
      <step id="S2">User nhấn nút "Đăng xuất"</step>
      <step id="S3">Manager nhấn nút "Đăng xuất"</step>
      <step id="S4">MainUI nhận yêu cầu từ User hoặc Manager</step>
      <step id="S5">SessionManager kiểm tra xác thực phiên hiện tại</step>
      <step id="S6">SessionManager xác thực phiên hiện tại</step>
      <alt id="A1">
         <id>S6: Phiên hợp lệ</id>
         <step>Affirm brd session ending to User/Manager</step>
         <step>Show successful logout message to User</step>
         <step>Show successful logout message to Manager</step>
      </alt>
      <alt id="A2">
         <id>S6: Phiên không hợp lệ</id>
         <step>Show error message to User</step>
         <step>Show error message to Manager</step>
      </alt>
   </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Đăng xuất khỏi hệ thống</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Manager</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Người dùng hoặc Quản lý thực hiện đăng xuất</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User hoặc Manager nhấn nút "Đăng xuất"</step>
        <step id="S2">MainUI chuyển yêu cầu đến SessionManager</step>
        <step id="S3">SessionManager xác thực phiên hiện tại</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Phiên hợp lệ</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Phiên không hợp lệ</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S3">
            <step id="A1S1">SessionManager xác nhận kết thúc phiên</step>
            <step id="A1S2">MainUI hiển thị thông báo đăng xuất thành công cho User và Manager</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
    <errorSteps>

<useCase id="UC123">
    <name>Search task or environment</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Environment Page</actor>
        <actor>Search Service</actor>
        <actor>Database</actor>
        <actor>Show Result Page</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User accesses the environment page.</step>
        <step id="S2">Environment Page initiates search.</step>
        <step id="S3">Search Service queries task or environment from the database.</step>
        <step id="S4">If searching for a task:</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S3">
            <step id="A1S1">Database returns task data to Search Service.</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S5">If searching for an environment:</step>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S3">
            <step id="A2S1">Database returns environment data to Search Service.</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S6">Search Service redirects to Show Result Page.</step>
        <step id="S7">User views the search results.</step>
        <step id="S8">User accesses selected task or environment from Environment Page.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="1">
    <name>Compute Delivery Graph</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Caller (anyone or anything)</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Caller requests the computing of the delivery graph</step>
        <step id="S2">CityMap starts mapping routes for Delivery Request</step>
        <step id="S3">CityMap retrieves start waypoint intersection</step>
        <step id="S4">CityMap initializes containers for intersections and timings</step>
        <step id="S5">CityMap defines minimal intersection for updating</step>
        <step id="S6">Determining neighboring Intersections for minimal intersection</step>
        <step id="S7">Checking if the neighbor intersection is not blacklisted</step>
        <step id="S8">Obtaining street section and updating predecessor and duration details</step>
        <step id="S9">Checking if the neighbor intersection is whitelisted</step>
        <step id="S9">Revamping whitelist and identifying new gray intersection counterparts</step>
        <step id="S10">Updating blacklisted intersection information indicating successful update</step>
        <step id="S11">CityMap proceeds with final fill-up of routes information</step>
        <step id="S12">DeliveryGraph creating route maps for tracked destinations</step>
        <step id="S13">DeliveryGraph returns generated delivery graph</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>
```

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Compute Delivery Graph</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Caller (anyone or anything)</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>A City Map is available</precondition>
        <precondition>A Delivery Request object is provided</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Caller computes the Delivery Graph by sending a Delivery Request to the City Map.</step>
        <step id="S2">City Map initializes the mappedRoutes as a new TreeMap<AbstractWaypoint, Map<AbstractWaypoint, Route>>.</step>
        <step id="S3">City Map retrieves startWaypoint intersection for each point in the request.</step>
        <step id="S4">City Map initializes predecessors and durations arrays for intersections.</step>
        <step id="S5">City Map adds startWaypointIntersection to greys list.</step>
        <step id="S6">City Map finds minimalGreyIntersection.</step>
        <step id="S7">City Map finds neighbouring intersections of minimalGreyIntersection.</step>
        <step id="S8">City Map checks if successor is in blacks list.</step>
        <step id="S9">If successor is not in blacks, then street section is obtained and updated.</step>
        <step id="S10">If successor is in whites, it is removed from white list, added to greys, and updated.</step>
        <step id="S11">Greys list is updated based on processed minimalGreyIntersection.</step>
        <step id="S12">minimalGreyIntersection is moved to blacks list.</step>
        <step id="S13">DeliveryGraph is created with mappedRoutes.</step>
        <step id="S14">City Map sends the created DeliveryGraph to the Caller.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="1">
    <name>Join Exchange Diary Room and Verify Code</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Client</actor>
        <actor>API</actor>
        <actor>Database</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User is logged in</precondition>
        <precondition>Client has received JWT token</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User inputs join code for diary room</step>
        <step id="S2">Client sends POST request to join room with code</step>
        <step id="S3">API validates JSON</step>
        <step id="S4">API retrieves room code from database</step>
        <step id="S5">API verifies user input code with retrieved code</step>
        <step id="S6">API inserts user account to RoomMember</step>
        <step id="S7">API appends AccountID to Room.Orders</step>
        <step id="S8">API responds with 201 Created</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>User successfully joins the exchange diary room</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>User is unauthorized to join the room</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Join a Room</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User is logged in</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <trigger>User inputs a room joining code in the diary room</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User inputs a room joining code</step>
        <step id="S2">Client sends POST request to /v1/rooms/<:room_id>/join API</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S3">
            <step id="A1S1">API validates JSON format and retrieves a room code from the database</step>
            <step id="A1S2">API checks if the user-provided joining code matches the retrieved code</step>
            <step id="A1S3">API inserts the account to the RoomMember and appends the AccountID to Room.Orders</step>
            <step id="A1S4">API responds with 201 Created</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>401 Unauthorized</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC002">
    <name>Reset Join Code for a Room</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User has access to change master settings</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <trigger>User clicks on "Reset Join Code" in the room settings</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User accesses master settings</step>
        <step id="S2">User clicks on "Reset Join Code"</step>
        <step id="S3">Client sends PATCH request to /v1/rooms/<:room_id> API</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S4">
            <step id="A1S1">API checks if the user is the master of the room</step>
            <step id="A1S2">API updates the room details</step>
            <step id="A1S3">API responds with 204 No Content</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>401 Unauthorized</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

        <condition>401 Unauthorized</condition>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Adding new edge agent</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Alice</actor>
        <actor>Edge Agent 1</actor>
        <actor>Edge Agent 2</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Alice has chosen existing or add new device from options in Edge Agent Start.</precondition>
        <precondition>Edge Agent 2 has been provisioned as described in the Provision New Agent diagram.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Alice adds a new agent.</step>
        <step id="S2">Edge Agent 2 provides instructions for adding Agent 2 and selecting authorizations.</step>
        <step id="S3">Alice adds agent with selected authorizations.</step>
        <step id="S4">Edge Agent 1 displays provisioning code for adding agent 2.</step>
        <step id="S5">Alice shows the code to Edge Agent 2.</step>
        <step id="S6">Edge Agent 2 sends add request, A_p^2-pk, A_A^2-vk to Edge Agent 1.</step>
        <step id="S7">Edge Agent 1 stores A_A^2-vk in the wallet.</step>
        <step id="S8">Alice confirms agent 2.</step>
        <step id="S9">Edge Agent 1 adds keys and authorizations for agent 2 to the policy registry.</step>
        <step id="S10">Edge Agent 2 receives A_LS, token data, claims from Edge Agent 1.</step>
        <step id="S11">Edge Agent 2 stores data in the wallet.</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <trigger>Alice selects the option to add a new agent.</trigger>
</useCase>

<useCase id="addNewEdgeAgent">
    <name>Add New Edge Agent</name>
    <description>
        Assumptions: Alice has chosen existing or add new device from options in Edge Agent Start. Edge Agent 2
        has been provisioned as described in the Provision New Agent diagram.
    </description>
    <actors>
        <actor>Alice</actor>
        <actor>Edge Agent 2</actor>
        <actor>Edge Agent 1</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Alice adds new agent.</step>
        <step id="S2">Edge Agent 2 provides instructions for adding Agent 2 and selecting authorizations.</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S2">
            <step id="A1S1">Alice adds agent with selected authorizations.</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Edge Agent 1 displays provisioning code for adding agent 2.</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Alice shows the code to Edge Agent 2.</step>
            <step id="A1S4">Edge Agent 2 sends add request and necessary keys.</step>
            <step id="A1S5">Edge Agent 1 stores the keys in the wallet.</step>
            <step id="A1S6">Alice confirms agent 2.</step>
            <esteps id="E1" start="A1S6">
                <description>Agent 1 adds keys and authorizations for agent 2 to policy registry.</description>
                <step id="E1S1">Data is synced to agent 2.</step>
            </esteps>
        </asteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
  <name>Access Private File List</name>
  <actors>
    <actor>User</actor>
    <actor>r_user</actor>
    <actor>api_user</actor>
    <actor>lss</actor>
    <actor>DFS</actor>
    <actor>ss</actor>
    <actor>sa</actor>
  </actors>
  <preconditions>
    <precondition>Login credentials for User are available</precondition>
    <precondition>User has associated data stored in Lookup DFS</precondition>
  </preconditions>
  <successEndConditions>
    <condition>All private files across all user DFS's successfully retrieved</condition>
  </successEndConditions>
  <failureEndConditions>
    <condition>Access denied for private files</condition>
  </failureEndConditions>
  <mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">User requests to get private file list</step>
    <step id="S2">User Router forwards request to User subservice REST API</step>
    <step id="S3">Metadata Service retrieves User 1 data from Lookup DFS</step>
    <step id="S4">Data transfer of private store information from Lookup DFS Service</step>
    <step id="S5">User accesses private storage using provided credentials</step>
    <step id="S6">User keytuple access process in Storage Service</step>
    <step id="S7">Decrypting user keystore for private file listing</step>
    <step id="S8">Keystore decryption using User password for private file path obtaining</step>
    <step id="Access_FS">File services provides files from database as specified in stored locations</step>
  </mainSequence>
  <alternativeSteps>
    <asteps id="Astep1" start="S5" continue="Access_FS">
      <step id="A1S1">For each filesystem, the appropriate files are led in accesor threads through process, decryption subsequently unlocking</step>
    </asteps>
  </alternativeSteps>
  <errorSteps>
    <esteps id="ErrorStep1" start="S6">

data.title: Hyperledger Cactus\nSequence Diagram\nGet Keychain Entry Endpoint

content:
<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Get Keychain Entry Endpoint</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User A</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User A triggers Tx GetKeychainEntryV1.</step>
        <step id="S2">API Client sends a request to API Server.</step>
        <step id="S3">API Server sends a get(key, value) request to AWS SM.</step>
        <step id="S4">AWS SM gets the AWS client.</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S4">
            <step id="A1S1">AWS SM awaits awsClient.getSecretValue().</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S5">AWS SM returns True to API Server.</step>
        <step id="S6">API Server sends a response to API Client.</step>
        <step id="S7">API Client formats the response.</step>
        <step id="S8">API Client sends GetKeychainEntryResponse to User A.</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <errorSteps>
        <esteps id="E1" start="A1">
            <description>Error handling for AWS SM: Invalid response received from AWS SecretsManager. Expected "response.SecretString" property chain to be truthy.</description>
            <step id="E1S1">API Server sends an error message to API Client.</step>
        </esteps>
    </errorSteps>
</useCase>

data.title: Burn notes to linked ERC20 contract

content:
<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Burn notes to the linked ERC20 contract</name>
    <description>The Token Owner wants to burn notes to the linked ERC20 contract.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>Token Owner</actor>
        <actor>ERC20 Token Contract</actor>
        <actor>Zero-knowledge Asset Contract</actor>
        <actor>AZTEC Cryptography Engine (ACE) Contract</actor>
        <actor>Note Registry Contract</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>The Token Owner should have notes to spend for the withdrawal.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>The notes are successfully burned.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>

<useCase id="1">
    <name>Retrieve File from Book</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>gateway</actor>
        <actor>Keycloak</actor>
        <actor>books</actor>
        <actor>Postgres</actor>
        <actor>Minio</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User sends request to get file for a book.</step>
        <step id="S2">gateway forwards request to Keycloak to verify JWT.</step>
        <step id="S3">If JWT is valid, gateway sends request to books.</step>
        <step id="S4">books fetches the file link from Postgres.</step>
        <step id="S5">If file link exists, retrieves file from Minio storage.</step>
        <step id="S6">If file exists in Minio, it is sent back to user with HTTP status 200.</step>
        <step id="S7">If file data does not exist, error status 404 is sent back.</step>
        <step id="S8">If JWT is absent, HTTP status 401 is sent back to user.</step>
        <step id="S9">If JWT is not valid, HTTP status 403 is sent back to user.</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S5" continue="switchOnCondition(1)">
            <step id="A1S1">Execute file exists conditions.</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Retrieve the file.</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Send back file to gateway</step>
            <step id="A1S4">Serve file to user.</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
    <errorSteps>
        <esteps id="E1" start="S7">
            <description>Process file does not exist conditions.</description>
            <step id="E1S1">Handle Not Found error for file data.</step>
            <step id="E1S2">Send HTTP Status 404 as a response.</step>
            <step id="E1S3">User receives HTTP Status 404.</step>
        </esteps>
    </errorSteps>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Retrieve File by ID</name>
    
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>gateway</actor>
        <actor>Keycloak</actor>
        <actor>books</actor>
        <actor>Postgres</actor>
        <actor>Minio</actor>
    </actors>
    
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User requests to retrieve a file by ID</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>User receives the requested file successfully</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    
    <trigger>GET /api/v1/books/{bookId}/files/{fileId}</trigger>
    
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User sends a GET request to gateway to retrieve a file by ID</step>
        <step id="S2">Gateway forwards the request to Keycloak to verify JWT</step>
        
        <asteps id="A1" start="S2">
            <step id="A1S1">Gateway receives a valid JWT</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Gateway sends a GET request to books to retrieve the file</step>
            
            <asteps id="A2" start="A1S2">
                <step id="A2S1">Books fetches the file link from Postgres by ID</step>
                <step id="A2S2">Books requests the file from Minio by the obtained link</step>
                
                <asteps id="A3" start="A2S2">
                    <step id="A3S1">Minio provides the requested file</step>
                    <step id="A3S2">Books sends the file back to gateway</step>
                    
                    <asteps id="A4" start="A3S2">
                        <step id="A4S1">Gateway forwards the file to the user</step>
                    </asteps>
                </asteps>
            </asteps>
            
            <asteps id="E1" start="A1">
                <description>File data for the given ID does not exist</description>
                <step id="E1S1">Books cannot find the file data in Postgres</step>
                <step id="E1S2">Books responds with HTTP Status 404 to gateway</step>
                <step id="E1S3">Gateway forwards HTTP Status 404 to the user</step>
            </asteps>
        </asteps>
        
        <asteps id="E2" start="S2">
            <step id="E2S1">Gateway receives an absent JWT</step>
            <step id="E2S2">Gateway responds with HTTP Status 401 to the user</step>
        </asteps>
        
        <asteps id="E3" start="S2">
            <step id="E3S1">Gateway receives an invalid JWT</step>
            <step id="E3S2">Gateway responds with HTTP Status 403 to the user</step>
        </asteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

        <step id="S6">ORS obtains authentication token</step>
        <step id="S7">ORS verifies Doctor's role using the token</step>
        <step id="S8">API sends a POST request to create the operation request</step>
        <step id="S9">API returns OperationRequestDto</step>
        <step id="S10">ORS returns success to UI</step>
        <step id="S11">UI sets success message</step>
        <step id="S12">UI clears the form</step>
        <step id="S13">UI displays success message to Doctor</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S10">
            <step id="A1S1">Error occurs</step>
            <step id="A1S2">ORS throws an error</step>
            <step id="A1S3">UI sets error message</step>
            <step id="A1S4">UI displays error message to Doctor</step>
        </asteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>add new edge agent</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Alice</actor>
        <actor>Edge Agent 1</actor>
        <actor>Edge Agent 2</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Alice adds a new agent with selected authorizations.</step>
        <step id="S2">Edge Agent 1 displays provisioning code for adding Agent 2.</step>
        <step id="S3">Alice shows the code to Edge Agent 2.</step>
        <step id="S4">Edge Agent 2 scans the code from Agent 1.</step>
        <step id="S5">Edge Agent 2 sends A<sub>p</sub><sup>2-pk</sup> and A<sub>A</sub><sup>2-vk</sup> to Agent 1.</step>
        <step id="S6">Agent 1 stores A<sub>A</sub><sup>2-vk</sup> in the wallet.</step>
        <step id="S7">Agent 1 confirms Agent 2.</step>
        <step id="S8">Agent 1 adds keys and authorizations for Agent 2 to the policy registry.</step>
        <step id="S9">Agent 1 syncs data to Agent 2 (A<sub>LS</sub>, token data, claims).</step>
        <step id="S10">Agent 2 stores data in the wallet.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">

        <step id="S2">Edge Agent 2 provides instructions for adding Agent 2 and selecting authorizations.</step>
        <step id="S3">Alice adds agent with selected authorizations.</step>

        <step id="S5">Alice shows the code to Edge Agent 2.</step>

        <step id="S7">Edge Agent 1 stores A<sub>A</sub><sup>2-vk</sup> in the wallet.</step>
        <step id="S8">Edge Agent 1 confirms agent 2 to Alice.</step>
        <step id="S9">Alice confirms agent 2.</step>
        <step id="S10">Edge Agent 1 adds keys and authorizations for agent 2 to the policy registry.</step>
        <step id="S11">Edge Agent 2 receives A<sub>LS</sub>, token data, and claims from Edge Agent 1.</step>
        <step id="S12">Edge Agent 2 stores data in the wallet.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">

        <actor>Edge Agent 1</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Alice has chosen existing or add new device from options in Edge Agent Start.</precondition>
        <precondition>Edge Agent 2 has been provisioned as described in the Provision New Agent diagram.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Alice adds a new edge agent.</step>
        <step id="S2">Edge Agent 2 provides instructions for adding Agent 2 and selecting authorizations.</step>
        <step id="S3">Alice adds agent with selected authorizations.</step>
        <step id="S4">Edge Agent 1 displays provisioning code for adding agent 2.</step>
        <step id="S5">Alice shows the code to Agent 2.</step>
        <step id="S6">Agent 2 sends add request, A<sub>p</sub><sup>2-pk</sup>, A<sub>A</sub><sup>2-vk</sup> to Agent 1.</step>
        <step id="S7">Agent 1 stores A<sub>A</sub><sup>2-vk</sup> in the wallet.</step>
        <step id="S8">Agent 1 confirms Agent 2.</step>
        <step id="S9">Agent 1 adds keys and authorizations for Agent 2 to the policy registry.</step>
        <step id="S10">Agent 1 syncs data to Agent 2: A<sub>LS</sub>, token data, claims.</step>
        <step id="S11">Agent 2 stores data in the wallet.</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Agent 2 successfully added and authorized.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Execute Transaction Process</name>
    <description>Allow users to start, monitor, and end a charging transaction</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Core</actor>
        <actor>LibOCPP</actor>
        <actor>Database</actor>
        <actor>CSMS</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>All necessary hardware and software components are functioning correctly.</preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>The transaction is successfully completed and closed.</successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>The transaction encounters an error and cannot be completed.</failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>User initiates a charging session by swiping an ID tag.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User swipes the ID tag to start the transaction.</step>
        <step id="S2">Core authorizes the transaction with LibOCPP.</step>
        <step id="S3">User plugs in the cable to begin charging the vehicle.</step>
        <step id="S4">LibOCPP notifies CSMS about the transaction start.</step>
        <step id="S5">Transaction details are inserted into the database.</step>
        <step id="S6">User pauses the charging of the vehicle.</step>
        <step id="S7">LibOCPP updates the charging state upon pausing.</step>
        <step id="S8">LibOCPP notifies CSMS about the charging state change.</step>
        <step id="S9">Transaction details are updated in the database during the charging state change.</step>
        <step id="S10">Power outage or libocpp crash triggers a new transaction construction.</step>
        <step id="S11">If existing transactions in the database are found, LibOCPP re-initializes them.</step>
        <step id="S12">LibOCPP continues normal operations after the transaction reconstruction.</step>
        <step id="S13">User resumes charging after power recovery.</step>
        <step id="S14">LibOCPP handles the resumed charging state.</step>
        <step id="S15">User requests to end the transaction by swiping the ID tag.</step>
        <step id="S16">LibOCPP processes the end transaction request.</step>
        <step id="S17">Depending on transaction support, LibOCPP notifies CSMS about the transaction end or prints a warning.</step>
        <step id="S18">If transaction resuming is supported, database details are updated and the transaction is deleted.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Payment Cancellation with Embedded approach, implicit authorisation mode</name>
    <actors>

        <actor>TPP</actor>
        <actor>XS2A</actor>
        <actor>CMS</actor>
        <actor>SPI</actor>
        <actor>ASPSP</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">PSU cancels payment</step>
        <step id="S2">TPP makes REST Call to cancel payment</step>
        <step id="S3">TPP receives HTTP code 400 "RESOURCE BLOCKED" from XS2A</step>
        <step id="S4">TPP sends message to the customer "Payment can't be cancelled"</step>
        <step id="S5">XS2A starts cancellation authorisation request</step>
        <step id="S6">XS2A receives start cancellation authorisation response</step>
        <step id="S7">TPP sends feedback to the customer "Please enter your User-id & password"</step>
        <step id="S8">PSU provides User-id & password</step>
        <step id="S9">TPP makes REST Call to update PSU data (Authentication)</step>
        <step id="S10">TPP receives message to the customer "Payment cancellation status"</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>
