<useCase id="uc1">
    <name>Epic Transaction Workflow</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Sender</actor>
        <actor>Recipient</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Sender creates transaction UUID for reference and maintaining state.</step>
        <step id="S2">Sender sets lock_height for transaction kernel.</step>
        <step id="S3">Sender selects inputs using desired selection strategy.</step>
        <step id="S4">Sender calculates sum inputs blinding factors (xI).</step>
        <step id="S5">Sender creates change_output.</step>
        <step id="S6">Sender selects blinding factor xC for change_output.</step>
        <step id="S7">Sender creates lock function sF that locks inputs and stores change_output in wallet.</step>
        <step id="S8">Sender calculates tx weight and fee.</step>
        <step id="S9">Sender calculates total blinding excess sum (xS1).</step>
        <step id="S10">Sender selects a random nonce kS.</step>
        <step id="S11">Sender subtracts random kernel offset oS from xS1 and calculates xS.</step>
        <step id="S12">Sender multiplies xS and kS to create public curve points xSG and kSG.</step>
        <step id="S13">Sender adds values to Slate for passing to other participants.</step>
        <step id="S14">Sender sends Slate to Recipient.</step>
        <step id="S15">Recipient verifies fee.</step>
        <step id="S16">Recipient creates receiver_output.</step>
        <step id="S17">Recipient chooses random blinding factor xR for receiver_output.</step>
        <step id="S18">Recipient calculates message M.</step>
        <step id="S19">Recipient chooses random nonce kR.</step>
        <step id="S20">Recipient multiplies xR and kR to create public curve points xRG and kRG.</step>
        <step id="S21">Recipient computes Schnorr challenge e.</step>
        <step id="S22">Recipient computes Recipient Schnorr signature sR.</step>
        <step id="S23">Recipient adds sR, xRG, kRG to Slate.</step>
        <step id="S24">Recipient executes wallet output function rF.</step>
        <step id="S25">Sender finalizes the transaction.</step>
        <step id="S26">Sender verifies sR and computes Sender Schnorr signature sS.</step>
        <step id="S27">Sender calculates final signature s.</step>
        <step id="S28">Sender calculates public key for s.</step>
        <step id="S29">Sender verifies s against excess values in final transaction.</step>
        <step id="S30">Sender creates transaction kernel.</step>
        <step id="S31">Sender posts transaction to mempool.</step>
        <step id="S32">Recipient confirms receiver_output.</step>
        < step id="S33">Recipient changes status of receiver_output to "Confirmed".</step>
        <step id="S34">Sender confirms change_output.</step>
        <step id="S35">Sender changes status of inputs to "Spent" and change_output to "Confirmed".</step>
        <step id="S36">Recipient removes receiver_output from wallet in case of any error.</step>
        <step id="S37">Sender unlocks inputs and deletes change_output in case of any error.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Change Password</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User must be logged in</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Request profile page - User requests the profile page</step>
        <step id="S2">Render profile page - Server renders the profile page</step>
        <step id="S3">Submit password change form - User submits the password change form</step>
        <step id="S4">Check inputs length and match passwords - Server checks input length and password match</step>
        <step id="S5">Fetch the user document - Server fetches the user document from the database</step>
        <step id="S6">Verify current password hash - Server verifies the current password hash</step>
        <step id="S7">Calculate new password hash - Server calculates the new password hash</step>
        <step id="S8">Update the "hash" field in the user document - Server updates the "hash" field in the user document</step>
        <step id="S9">Redirect to profile page with success message - Server redirects to the profile page with a success message</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Hashes do not match - Server renders the profile page with error message</condition>
        <condition>Validation failed - Server returns 422, rendering the login page with error message</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

        <step id="S9">Server redirects to profile page with success message</step>

</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Login And Password Update</name>
    <description>Allow the user to log in and update their password</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Server</actor>
        <actor>Database</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>User must be logged in</preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>User successfully logs in and updates their password</successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>User fails to log in or update password</failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>User requests profile page and password change</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User requests profile page</step>
        <step id="S2">Server renders profile page</step>
        <step id="S3">User submits password change form</step>
        <step id="S4">Server checks input length and matches passwords</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S4">Validation failed</asteps>
        <step id="A1S1">Server renders login page with error message</step>
        <step id="S5">Server fetches the user document</step>
        <step id="S6">Server verifies current password hash</step>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S6">Hashes do not match</asteps>
        <step id="A2S1">Server renders profile page with error message</step>
        <step id="S7">Server calculates new password hash</step>
        <step id="S8">Server updates the "hash" field in the user document</step>
        <step id="S9">Server redirects to profile page with a success message</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
  <name>User updates password</name>
  <actors>
    <actor>User</actor>
    <actor>Server</actor>
    <actor>Database</actor>
  </actors>
  <preconditions>User must be logged in</preconditions>
  <mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">User requests profile page</step>
    <step id="S2">Server renders the profile page</step>
    <step id="S3">User submits password change form</step>
    <step id="S4">Server checks inputs length and whether password and retyped password match</step>
    <asteps id="A1" start="S4">
      <step id="A1S1">Validation failed</step>
      <step id="A1S2">Server returns status 422 and renders login page with error message</step>
    </asteps>
    <step id="S5">Server fetches the user document</step>
    <step id="S6">Server verifies current password hash</step>
    <asteps id="A2" start="S6">
      <step id="A2S1">Hashes do not match</step>
      <step id="A2S2">Server renders the profile page with error message</step>
    </asteps>
    <step id="S7">Server calculates the new password hash</step>
    <step id="S8">Server updates the "hash" field in the user document</step>
    <step id="S9">After Updating the user, server return by redirect the profile page with a success message</step>
  </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>User Login</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User enters username and password</step>
        <step id="S2">User submits login form</step>
        <step id="S3">Login Page sends HTTP POST /login request with credentials to AuthController</step>
        <step id="S4">AuthController authenticates the user</step>
        <step id="S5">AuthService checks the user credentials using UserRepository</step>
        <step id="S6">UserRepository queries Database for user details</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S5">
            <step id="A1S1">User credentials are invalid</step>
            <step id="A1S2">AuthService and AuthController handle and display error message</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Login Page displays error message to the User</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>	
    <successEndConditions>
		<condition>User successfully logged in and redirected to Home Page</condition>
	</successEndConditions>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Compose Message</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>authenticated user</actor>
    </actors>
    <description>Compose a new message draft and send or edit it with optional participants</description>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User is authenticated</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Write a new draft message with or without participants</step>
        <step id="S2">Throttle save</step>
        <step id="S3">Acknowledge message creation</step>
        <step id="S4">Retrieve the created message</step>
        <step id="S5">Edit the draft message with or without participants</step>
        <step id="S6">Throttle save</step>
        <step id="S7">Patch the message</step>
        <step id="S8">Acknowledge patch</step>
        <step id="S9">Retrieve the patched message</step>
        <step id="S10">Render the discussion</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase> 

<useCase id="UC2">
    <name>Reply to Discussion</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>authenticated user</actor>
    </actors>
    <description>Reply to a discussion, edit or send the reply message with optional participants</description>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User is authenticated</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Reply to a discussion</step>
        <step id="S2">Throttle save</step>
        <step id="S3">Acknowledge reply creation</step>
        <step id="S4">Retrieve the created reply message</step>
        <step id="S5">Edit the reply message</step>
        <step id="S6">Throttle save</step>
        <step id="S7">Patch the reply message</step>
        <step id="S8">Acknowledge patch</step>
        <step id="S9">Retrieve the patched reply message</step>
        <step id="S10">Render the discussion</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Compose Message</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Authenticated User</actor>
    </actors>
    <trigger>User writes a new draft message</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User writes a new draft message with or without participants</step>
        <step id="S2">Message is throttled for saving</step>
        <step id="S3">API receives POST request with message_id and optional participants</step>
        <step id="S4">API acknowledges the creation with status 204</step>
        <step id="S5">API retrieves the message</step>
        <step id="S6">API responds with message details</step>
        <step id="S7">Discussion is rendered</step>
        <step id="S8">Discussion UI is shown to the user</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S1">
            <step id="A1S1">User edits the draft message with or without participants</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Draft message is throttled for saving</step>
            <step id="A1S3">API receives PATCH request with current_state object and optional participants</step>
            <step id="A1S4">API acknowledges the patch with status 204</step>
            <step id="A1S5">API retrieves the message</step>
            <step id="A1S6">API responds with message details</asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
</useCase>

```xml
<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Message discussion association</name>
    <actors>
```

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Customer Makes a Reservation</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Customer</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Customer requests Reservation Page</step>
        <step id="S2">Reservation System displays Reservation Form to Customer</step>
        <step id="S3">Customer submits Reservation Details (date, time, number of people)</step>
        <step id="S4">Reservation System checks Availability with Database</step>
        <condition>Space is available</condition>
        <step id="S5">Database confirms Availability to Reservation System</step>
        <step id="S6">Reservation System shows Confirmation Message to Customer</step>
        <step id="S7">Reservation System saves Reservation Details to Database</step>
        <step id="S8">Database sends Confirmation Status to Reservation System</step>
        <step id="S9">Reservation System displays Reservation ID and Details to Customer</step>
        <alternativeSteps id="A1" start="S4">
            <step id="A1S1">Space Not Available in Database</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Database shows Unavailability Message to Reservation System</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Reservation System suggests Different Time/Date to Customer</step>
        </alternativeSteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
  <name>Customer Makes a Reservation</name>
  <actors>
    <actor>Customer</actor>
  </actors>
  <mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">Customer requests the Reservation Page from Reservation System.</step>
    <step id="S2">Reservation System displays Reservation Form to the Customer.</step>
    <step id="S3">Customer submits Reservation details\n(date, time, number of people) to Reservation System.</step>
    <step id="S4">Reservation System checks availability with the Database.</step>
    <alternativeSteps>
      <asteps id="A1" start="D1">
        <step id="A1S1">If space is available:</step>
        <step id="A1S2">Database confirms the availability to Reservation System.</step>
        <step id="A1S3">Reservation System displays Confirmation Message to the Customer.</step>
        <step id="A1S4">Reservation System saves the Reservation Details in Database.</step>
        <step id="A1S5">Database updates the Confirmation Status.</step>
        <step id="A1S6">Reservation System displays the Reservation ID and Details to the Customer.</step>
      </asteps>
      <asteps id="A2" start="D2">
        <step id="A2S1">If space is not available:</step>
        <step id="A2S2">Database indicates unavailability with message to Reservation System.</step>
        <step id="A2S3">Reservation System suggests a Different Time/Date to the Customer.</step>
      </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
  </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>User Profile Management</name>
    <description>Manage user profile data and avatar image</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>UserProfilePopup</actor>
        <actor>Controller</actor>
        <actor>Model</actor>
        <actor>Database</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User is authenticated</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>User profile data updated successfully</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <trigger>User requests to view or update user profile data</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Open User Profile Popup</step>
        <step id="S2">Request User Profile</step>
        <step id="S3">Query user profile data from Database</step>
        <step id="S4">Return user profile data to User</step>
        <step id="S5">Submit updated profile or new avatar image</step>
        <step id="S6">Send updated profile or avatar image to Controller</step>
        <step id="S7">Dispatch Prisma action (update or upload) to Model</step>
        <step id="S8">Update user profile data or Store avatar image in Database</step>
        <step id="S9">Confirm update or upload with Model</step>
        <step id="S10">Return updated profile data or avatar image URL to User</step>
        <step id="S11">Confirm update or return avatar image URL to UserProfilePopup</step>
        <step id="S12">Display success message or new avatar image to User</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <errorSteps>
        <esteps id="E1">
            <description>Handle error scenarios</description>
            <step id="E1S1">Display error message to User</step>
        </esteps>
    </errorSteps>
</useCase>

        <step id="S7">UserProfilePopup displays user profile data to User</step>
        <step id="S8">User submits updated profile or new avatar image</step>
        <step id="S9">UserProfilePopup sends updated profile or avatar image data to Controller</step>
        <step id="S10">Controller dispatches Prisma action to update or upload</step>
        <step id="S11">Model updates user profile data or stores avatar image in Database</step>
        <step id="S12">Model returns updated profile data or avatar image URL to Controller</step>
        <step id="S13">Controller confirms update or returns avatar image URL to UserProfilePopup</step>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Renew Book Loan</name>
    <description>User wants to renew a book loan if eligible</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>Borrower</actor>
        <actor>FrontEnd</actor>
        <actor>LoanController</actor>
        <actor>LoanService</actor>
        <actor>LoanRepository</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>Ensure borrower has an active book loan</preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>Book loan is successfully renewed</successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>Book loan cannot be renewed</failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>User requests book renewal</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Borrower requests book renewal through FrontEnd</step>
        <step id="S2">FrontEnd forwards renewal request to LoanController</step>
        <step id="S3">LoanController processes renewal request using LoanService</step>
        <step id="S4">LoanService checks renewal eligibility with LoanRepository</step>
        <step id="S5">LoanRepository updates loan record if renewal allowed</step>
        <step id="S6">LoanService notifies LoanController about renewal</step>
        <step id="S7">LoanController sends renewal confirmation to FrontEnd</step>
        <step id="S8">FrontEnd displays renewal confirmation message to Borrower</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC123">
    <name>Book Renewal Process</name>
    <description>Allow borrowers to renew a book</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>Borrower</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User must have borrowed a book</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Book renewal successfully processed</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Book renewal not allowed or unsuccessful</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>User requests book renewal</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Borrower requests book renewal through FrontEnd</step>
        <step id="S2">FrontEnd forwards renewal request to LoanController</step>
        <step id="S3">LoanController processes renewal request and reaches LoanService</step>
        <step id="S4">LoanService checks renewal eligibility with LoanRepository</step>
        <step id="S5">LoanRepository provides renewal eligibility status back to LoanService</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps id="A1" start="S5">
        <asteps id="A1S1">
            <step id="A1S1">Renewal is allowed by the system</step>
            <step id="A1S2">LoanService updates the loan record in LoanRepository</step>
            <step id="A1S3">LoanRepository confirms the renewal</step>
            <step id="A1S4">LoanService notifies LoanController about the renewal</step>
            <step id="A1S5">LoanController sends confirmation message through FrontEnd to the Borrower</step>
            <step id="A1S6">FrontEnd displays renewal confirmation message to the Borrower</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S5">
            <step id="A2S1">Renewal is not allowed by the system</step>
            <step id="A2S2">LoanService notifies LoanController about the renewal rejection</step>
            <step id="A2S3">LoanController sends rejection notification through FrontEnd to the Borrower</step>
            <step id="A2S4">FrontEnd displays rejection message to the Borrower</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
</useCase>

```xml
        <step id="S6">XS2A saves authorisation</step>

        <step id="S8">TPP sends feedback to PSU to enter User-id & password</step>
        <step id="S9">PSU provides User-id & password to TPP</step>
        <step id="S10">TPP updates PSU data with authentication</step>
        <step id="S11">XS2A updates payment authorisation</step>
        <step id="S12">PSU provides authentication data</step>
        <step id="S13">TPP initiates transaction authorisation</step>
        <step id="S14">XS2A updates transaction authorisation</step>
        <step id="S15">TPP provides feedback to PSU that payment is authorized</step>
        <step id="S16">TPP gets payment status</step>
        <step id="S17">XS2A updates transaction status</step>
        <step id="S18">TPP gets payment request</step>
        <step id="S19">XS2A updates payment</step>
        <step id="S20">TPP gets authorisation sub-resources</step>
        <step id="S21">XS2A gets authorisations by payment id</step>
        <step id="S22">TPP gets SCA status request</step>
        <step id="S23">XS2A gets payment initiation authorisation SCA status</step>
        <step id="S24">XS2A updates authorisation status</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>
```

    <description>Este caso de uso descreve o processo de alterar os dados de um utente no sistema.</description>

    </failureEndConditions>

    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">O Utente solicita a alteração dos dados do utente.</step>
        <step id="S2">O SistemaRobDroneGo recebe a solicitação para alterar os dados do utente.</step>
        <step id="S3">O SistemaRobDroneGo requisita os dados atuais do utente ao sistema.</step>

```xml
<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>DeleteBook</name>
    <description>Delete book from the database based on its ID</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>Administrator</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Administrator is logged in the system</precondition>
        <precondition>Book ID is provided</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Book successfully deleted</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Error occurred during book deletion process</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>User requests to delete a book by ID</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Administrator inputs book ID for deletion</step>
        <step id="S2">UI sends a DELETE request with book ID to the Server</step>
        <step id="S3">Server searches for the book by ID in the database</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S3">
            <step id="A1S1">Book is found in the database</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Server deletes the book</step>
            <asteps id="A2" start="A1S2">
                <step id="A2S1">Book is successfully deleted</step>
                <step id="A2S2">Server notifies UI about successful deletion</step>
                <step id="A2S3">UI informs the Administrator about the successful deletion</step>
            </asteps>
            <esteps id="E1" start="S3">
                <description>Error occurred during the deletion process</description>
                <step id="E1S1">Server notifies UI about the deletion error</step>
                <step id="E1S2">UI informs the Administrator about the deletion error</step>
            </esteps>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A3" start="S3">
            <step id="A3S1">Book is not found in the database</step>
            <step id="A3S2">Server informs UI that the book is not found</step>
            <step id="A3S3">UI informs the Administrator about the book not found error</step>
        </asteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>
```

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Delete Book</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Адміністратор</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Адміністратор ввів ідентифікатор книги для видалення</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Книга успішно видалена</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Книга не була знайдена або виникла помилка під час видалення</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>Адміністратор вказав на необхідність видалення книги</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Адміністратор вводить _id книги для видалення</step>
        <step id="S2">Веб-клієнт просить сервер видалити книгу по вказаному _id</step>
        <step id="S3">Сервер передає запит видалення книги до бази даних</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1">
            <step id="A1S1">Книга знаходиться в базі даних</step>
            <step id="A1S2">База даних підтверджує, що книга знайдена</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Сервер видаляє книгу</step>
            <step id="A1S4">Сервер повідомляє про успішне видалення книги</step>
            <step id="A1S5">Веб-клієнт відображає, що книга була успішно видалена</step>
            <step id="A1S6">Адміністратор отримує повідомлення про успішне видалення книги</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A2">

            <step id="A2S5">Адміністратор отримує повідомлення про невдале видалення книги</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
  <name>Delete Book</name>
  <description>As an Administrator, I want to delete a book from the database by providing its ID.</description>
  <actors>
    <actor>Administrator</actor>
  </actors>
  <preconditions>
    <precondition>Administrator is logged in the system.</precondition>
    <precondition>The book ID for deletion is provided.</precondition>
  </preconditions>
  <successEndConditions>
    <condition>The book is successfully deleted from the database.</condition>
  </successEndConditions>
  <failureEndConditions>
    <condition>Error occurs during the book deletion process.</condition>
  </failureEndConditions>
  
  <trigger>Administrator provides the book ID to delete.</trigger>
  
  <mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">Administrator enters the book ID for deletion.</step>
    <step id="S2">User Interface sends a DELETE request to the Server with the provided book ID.</step>
    <step id="S3">Server searches for the book in the database using the provided ID.</step>
    <step id="S4">Conditional block: Check if the book is found.</step>
    <step id="S5">Database confirms the book is found.</step>
    <step id="S6">Server deletes the book from the database.</step>
    <asteps id="A1" start="S4" continue="S5">
      <step id="A1S1">Database confirms the book is found.</step>
    </asteps>
    <asteps id="A2" start="S6">
      <step id="A2S1">Database notifies the Server about successful deletion.</step>
      <step id="A2S2">Server sends the success message to the User Interface.</step>
      <step id="A2S3">User Interface informs the Administrator about the successful deletion.</step>
    </asteps>
    <esteps id="E1" start="S4">
      <description>If book is not found in the database.</description>
      <step id="E1S1">Database notifies the Server about the book not found.</step>
      <step id="E1S2">Server sends a message to the User Interface that the book is not found.</step>
      <step id="E1S3">User Interface informs the Administrator about the error.</step>
    </esteps>
  </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Add Assessment</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Admin</actor>
    </actors>
    <trigger>Admin requests to add an assessment of a subject.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Admin requests SubjectController to add the assessment of the subject.</step>
        <step id="S2">SubjectController asks SubjectService to add mark type to Subject.</step>
        <step id="S3">SubjectService invokes SubjectRepository for adding mark type to the Subject.</step>
        <step id="S4">SubjectRepository interacts with the MySQL database to insert the mark type.</step>
        <step id="S5">MySQL database records the mark type for the subject's assessment.</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S4">
            <step>A) If mark type exists in the subject's assessment</step>
            <step id="A1S1">MySQL throws DataIntegrityViolationException.</step>
            <step id="A1S2">SubjectRepository catches this exception and throws ActionNotAllowedException to CustomExceptionHandler.</step>
            <step id="A1S3">CustomExceptionHandler forwards the ActionNotAllowedException to Admin and displays an error message.</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S5">
            <step>D) If the mark type does not exist in the subject's assessment</step>
            <step id="A2S1">MySQL successfully records the mark type for the subject's assessment.</step>
            <step id="A2S2">SubjectRepository retrieves the assessment by the subject id from MySQL and returns a response.</step>
            <step id="A2S3">SubjectService gets and processes the list of tuples from SubjectRepository and returns them to SubjectController.</step>
            <step id="A2S4">SubjectController formats the data into a map of mark type and no marks and returns it to Admin.</step>
            <step id="A2S5">Admin views and evaluates the assessment display.</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Place Order</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Customer</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Customer places an order.</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S1">
            <step id="A1S1">ConfirmOrderPanel confirms the order.</step>
            <step id= "A1S2">SubscriptionService creates the order.</step>
            <step id= "A1S3">IntegrationService publishes the order.</step>
            <step id= "A1S4">Connector publishes the non-interactive event.</step>
            <step id= "A1S5">Connector communicates with ISV via a GET request.</step>
            <step id= "A1S6">Connector receives the response from ISV containing Event info.</step>
            <step id="A1S7">Connector notifies IntegrationService that ISV has been notified.</step>
            <step id="A1S8">SubscriptionService begins generating and paying the invoices.</step>
            <step id="A1S9">JBillingApi begins invoice generation but does NOT complete it due to OrderStatus not being ACTIVE.</step>
            </asteps>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps/>
    <errorSteps/>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Add New Edge Agent</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Alice</actor>
        <actor>Edge Agent 1</actor>
        <actor>Edge Agent 2</actor>
    </actors>
    <trigger>Alice selects to add a new device</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Alice instructs Edge Agent 2 on adding and selecting authorizations</step>
        <step id="S2">Alice adds an agent with selected authorizations</step>
        <step id="S3">Edge Agent 1 displays provisioning code for adding Edge Agent 2</step>
        <step id="S4">Alice scans the code from Edge Agent 1</step>
        <step id="S5">Edge Agent 2 sends the key pairs and data upon request</step>
        <step id="S6">Edge Agent 1 stores Edge Agent 2's verification key in the wallet</step>
        <step id="S7">Edge Agent 1 confirms the addition of Agent 2</step>
        <step id="S8">Edge Agent 1 syncs data to Edge Agent 2</step>
        <step id="S9">Edge Agent 2 stores data in the wallet</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Edge Agent 2 is successfully added with authorizations</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <postconditions>Alice has added Edge Agent 2 successfully with necessary authorizations and configurations</postconditions>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Inicializar y monitorear planta nuclear</name>
    <description>El usuario inicializa los componentes y monitorea la planta nuclear durante la simulacion</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>Usuario</actor>
        <actor>Planta Nuclear</actor>
        <actor>Sensor</actor>
        <actor>Reactor Nuclear</actor>
        <actor>Reportador</actor>
        <actor>Estado Reactor</actor>
        <actor>Operadores</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>Se deben haber iniciado todos los componentes previos</preconditions>
    
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">El usuario inicializa los componentes de la planta nuclear</step>
        <step id="S2">El usuario inicia la simulacion en la planta nuclear</step>
        <step id="S3">El Sensor recibe una peticion de medir la temperatura</step>
        <step id="S4">El Sensor pide el estado mas reciente al Reactor Nuclear</step>
        <step id="S5">El Sensor chequea el estado de la planta</step>
        <step id="S6">El Sensor notifica a los Operadores del estado de la planta</step>
        <step id="S7">Los Operadores manejan la situacion en la planta</step>
        <step id="S8">El Estado del Reactor envia un reporte sobre la situacion al Reportador</step>
        <step id="S9">El Reportador envia un reporte con la temperatura al Dueno</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

```
<useCase id="UC001">
  <name>User sign up</name>
  <description>New user registers for an account</description>
  <actors>
    <actor>User</actor>
    <actor>SignupController</actor>
    <actor>RemoteModelAccess</actor>
  </actors>
  <preconditions>
    <precondition>User is not registered in the system</precondition>
    <precondition>User has filled in valid account information</precondition>
  </preconditions>
  <successEndConditions>
    <condition>User account creation successful</condition>
  </successEndConditions>
  <failureEndConditions/>
  <trigger>User presses Signup button</trigger>
  <mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">User presses Signup button with invalid credentials</step>
    <step id="S2">Signup controller receives the request to handle sign up</step>
    <step id="S3">Remote model access attempts to post the user data (HTTP Post)</step>
    <step id="S4">Server controller receives null from the post</step>
    <step id="S5">Remote model access receives null</step>
    <step id="S6">Signup controller shows an error message to the User</step>
  
    <step id="S7">User presses Signup button with valid credentials</step>
    <step id="S8">Signup controller receives the request to handle sign up</step>
    <step id="S9">Remote model access attempts to post the user data (HTTP Post)</step>
    <step id="S10">Server controller sends back user data</step>
    <step id="S11">Remote model access receives user data</step>
    <step id="S12">Signup controller changes screen to MainMenu for User</step>
  </mainSequence>
  <alternativeSteps/>
  <errorSteps/>
</useCase>
```

```xml
<description>Removing a comment.</description>
<actors>
  <actor>TEST</actor>
</actors>
<preconditions>
  <precondition>User is authenticated.</precondition>
</preconditions>

  <condition>Comment successfully removed.</condition>
</successEndConditions>
<faultEndConditions>
  <condition>Comment not removed due to unspecified error.</condition>
</faultEndConditions>
<trigger>Authorized user triggers the comment removal process.</trigger>
<mainSequence>
  <step id="S1">Actor TEST requests to remove a comment.</step>
  <step id="S2">System validates the member (signId).</step>
  <step id="S3">System validates the comment (commentId).</step>
  <step id="S4">System checks if the user (signId) is the writer of the comment (commentId).</step>
  <step id="S5">System removes the comment.</step>
  <step id="S6">System confirms successful removal of the comment to Actor TEST.</step>
</mainSequence>
</useCase>
```

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Track Game Statistics</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Game</actor>
        <actor>StatsTrackingSystem</actor>
        <actor>StorageManager</actor>
        <actor>StatsTrackerFactory</actor>
        <actor>NumBlocksPlacedStatTracker</actor>
        <actor>EventManager</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>A game is being played.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Game statistics are successfully saved to disk.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <trigger>Game triggers the end event.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Game creates an instance of StatsTrackingSystem.</step>
        <step id="S2">StatsTrackingSystem loads stats from StorageManager.</step>
        <step id="S3">For each stat in statsStorage:</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S3">
            <step id="A1S1">StatsTrackingSystem creates a NumBlocksPlacedStatTracker.</step>
            <step id="A1S2">NumBlocksPlacedStatTracker initializes with eventManager and stat.</step>
            <step id="A1S3">EventManager registers a closure for BlockPlacedEvent.</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S4">EventManager registers a closure for GameEndedEvent.</step>
        <step id="S5">Game plays the game.</step>
        <step id="S6">Game fires the GameEndedEvent.</step>
        <step id="S7">EventManager triggers the GameEndedEvent.</step>
        <step id="S8">StatsTrackingSystem saves stats.</step>
        <step id="S9">StorageManager saves stats to disk.</step>
        <step id="S10">StorageManager converts StatTrackers to StatStorage.</step>
        <step id="S11">StorageManager writes to disk.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Track Game Stats</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Game</actor>
        <actor>StatsTrackingSystem</actor>
        <actor>StorageManager</actor>
        <actor>StatsTrackerFactory</actor>
        <actor>NumBlocksPlacedStatTracker</actor>
        <actor>EventManager</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>A game is being played</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Game stats are successfully saved to disk</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <trigger>Game initiates stats tracking</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Game creates an instance of StatsTrackingSystem</step>
        <step id="S2">StatsTrackingSystem loads stats from StorageManager</step>
        <step id="S3">For each stat in statsStorage:</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S3">
            <step id="A1S1">StatsTrackingSystem creates a StatTracker using StatsTrackerFactory</step>
            <step id="A1S2">NumBlocksPlacedStatTracker initializes with eventManager and stat</step>
            <step id="A1S3">EventManager registers a closure for BlockPlacedEvent</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S4">EventManager registers a closure for GameEndedEvent</step>
        <step id="S5">Game plays the game</step>
        <step id="S6">Game fires GameEndedEvent</step>
        <step id="S7">EventManager triggers GameEndedEvent</step>
        <step id="S8">StatsTrackingSystem saves stats</step>
        <step id="S9">StorageManager saves stats to disk</step>
        <step id="S10">StorageManager converts StatTrackers to StatStorage</step>
        <step id="S11">StorageManager writes to disk</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Submit message</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>MainMessageInput</actor>
        <actor>ChatClient</actor>
        <actor>MessagesService</actor>
        <actor>UserRequest</actor>
        <actor>UnixSocketServer</actor>
        <actor>AiResponse</actor>
        <actor>ResponseArea</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User submits a message</step>
        <step id="S2">MainMessageInput gets messages</step>
        <step id="S3">ChatClient processes messages</step>
        <step id="S4">MessagesService sends user request to UnixSocketServer</step>
        <step id="S5">UnixSocketServer handles user request</step>
        <step id="S6">UnixSocketServer sends message to AiResponse</step>
        <step id="S7">AiResponse receives AI response from UnixSocketServer</step>
        <step id="S8">MessagesService receives AI response from UnixSocketServer</step>
        <step id="S9">ChatClient returns Flux<Object></step>
        <step id="S10">ResponseArea gets messages</step>
        <step id="S11">ResponseArea displays AI response</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Submit message</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User submits a message</step>
        <step id="S2">MainMessageInput gets messages with action REQUEST</step>
        <step id="S3">ChatClient processes messages with action REQUEST</step>
        <step id="S4">MessagesService sends user request to UnixSocketServer</step>
        <step id="S5">UnixSocketServer handles user request</step>
        <step id="S6">UnixSocketServer sends message to AiResponse</step>
        <step id="S7">AiResponse receives AI response from UnixSocketServer</step>
        <step id="S8">MessagesService receives AI response from UnixSocketServer</step>
        <step id="S9">ChatClient returns Flux<Object></step>
        <step id="S10">ResponseArea gets messages with action RESPONSE</step>
        <step id="S11">ResponseArea displays AI response</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Login enduser</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>End user</actor>
        <actor>Envoy (with WASM oicd filter)</actor>
        <actor>ID-provider</actor>
        <actor>TokenDings</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>End user requests a resource</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">End user requests a resource</step>
        <step id="S2">Envoy redirects to ID-provider</step>
        <step id="S3">End user GETs /oauth2/v2.0/authorize with query parameters</step>
        <step id="S4">End user logs in and authorizes the application</step>
        <step id="S5">ID-provider sends callback with authorization_code</step>
        <step id="S6">End user sends authorization code to Envoy</step>
        <step id="S7">Envoy POSTs /oauth2/v2.0/token with authorization_code, client_id, and client_secret/client_assertion</step>
        <step id="S8">ID-provider returns id_token, access_token, and possibly refresh_token</step>
        <step id="S9">Envoy validates id_token according to OpenID Connect</step>
        <step id="S10">Envoy stores session in cache</step>
        <step id="S11">Envoy redirects end user with cookies (id_token, session)</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC2">
    <name>API1 to API2</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>API1</actor>
        <actor>Envoy (with WASM oicd filter)</actor>
        <actor>TokenDings</actor>
        <actor>API2</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Attempt to call API2 from API1</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">API1 attempts to call API2</step>
        <step id="S2">Envoy checks for cached token in cache</step>
        <step id="S3">Cache miss (no token for (API1, API2))</step>
        <step id="S4">Envoy gets token for API2 from TokenDings based on ID-provider token</step>
        <step id="S5">TokenDings verifies token and checks access policy</step>
        <step id="S6">TokenDings issues a new token for API2</step>
        <step id="S7">Envoy caches token for later calls</step>
        <step id="S8">Envoy calls API2 with token from TokenDings</step>
        <step id="S9">API2 verifies token and access control</step>
        <step id="S10">API2 returns information to Envoy</step>
        <step id="S11">Envoy returns information to API1</step>
        <step id="S12">API1 displays information to end user</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Login End User</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>End user</actor>
        <actor>Envoy (with WASM oicd filter)</actor>
        <actor>ID-provider</actor>
        <actor>TokenDings</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>End user requests a resource</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">End user requests a resource</step>
        <step id="S2">Envoy redirects End user to ID-provider</step>
        <step id="S3">End user performs login and gives consent/authorization to the application</step>
        <step id="S4">ID-provider sends callback/redirect with authorization_code</step>
        <step id="S5">End user sends authorization code to defined callback e.g., /callback</step>
        <step id="S6">Envoy posts authorization_code, client_id, and client_secret/client_assertion to ID-provider</step>
        <step id="S7">ID-provider returns id_token, access_token, and optionally refresh_token</step>
        <step id="S8">Envoy validates id_token according to OpenID Connect</step>
        <step id="S9">Envoy stores the session in cache</step>
        <step id="S10">Envoy redirects End user with cookies (id_token, session?)</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC2">
    <name>API1 to API2</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>API1</actor>
        <actor>Envoy (with WASM oicd filter)</actor>
        <actor>TokenDings</actor>
        <actor>API2</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>API1 attempts to call API2</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">API1 attempts to call API2</step>
        <step id="S2">Envoy checks for cached token</step>
        <step id="S3">Envoy gets token for API2 from TokenDings based on ID-provider token</step>
        <step id="S4">TokenDings verifies token and issues a new token for API2</step>
        <step id="S5">Envoy caches the token for later calls</step>
        <step id="S6">Envoy calls API2 with token from TokenDings</step>
        <step id="S7">API2 verifies token and performs access control based on end user</step>
        <step id="S8">API2 returns information to Envoy</step>
        <step id="S9">Envoy returns information to API1</step>
        <step id="S10">API1 displays information to End user</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>View All Projects</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>PL</actor>
        <actor>System</actor>
        <actor>DBMS</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>The PL wants to view all projects.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>The PL receives a list of projects.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <trigger>PL requests to view all projects by providing signId.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">PL requests all projects by calling System's getAllProject(signId) method.</step>
        <step id="S2">System validates the member by calling DBMS's validateMember(signId) method.</step>
        <step id="S3">System retrieves all projects by calling DBMS's getAllProjects(signId) method.</step>
        <step id="S4">System sends the List<ProjectResponseDto containing all projects to PL.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="startTransaction">
    <name>Start a transaction</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Core</actor>
        <actor>Libocpp</actor>
        <actor>CSMS</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User swipes ID tag.</step>
        <step id="S2">Core authorizes the transaction.</step>
        <step id="S3">User plugs in the cable.</step>
        <step id="S4">Libocpp triggers on_transaction_started().</step>
        <step id="S5">Libocpp sends TransactionEventRequest::Started to CSMS.</step>
        <step id="S6">Libocpp inserts transaction details into the database.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="chargingStateChanged">
    <name>Charging state changed (Example)</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Core</actor>
        <actor>Libocpp</actor>
        <actor>CSMS</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User pauses charging of car.</step>
        <step id="S2">Core triggers on_charging_state_changed().</step>
        <step id="S3">Libocpp sends TransactionEventRequest::Updated to CSMS.</step>
        <step id="S4">Libocpp updates transaction charging state in the database.</step>
        <step id="S5">Libocpp updates transaction sequence number in the database.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Carregar Mapa de Piso</name>
    <description>O Gestor de campus carrega o mapa de piso no sistema.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>Gestor de campus</actor>
    </actors>
    <trigger>Requisitar os dados do mapa de piso</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Requisitar os dados do mapa de piso</step>
        <step id="S2">Inserir os dados do mapa de piso</step>
        <step id="S3">Enviar patch(/api/floorMap) para GestaoInfoAPI</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Retornar o mapa de piso criado</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Retornar mensagem de erro</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Carregar mapa de piso</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Gestor de campus</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Requisitar os dados do mapa de piso</step>
        <step id="S2">Inserir os dados do mapa de piso</step>
        <step id="S3">Enviar patch(/api/floorMap) para GestaoInfoAPI</step>
        <step id="S4">Receber status code da API</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Sucesso na requisição: Devolver o mapa de piso criado</condition>

```xml
<useCase id="UC-001">
    <name>Telecommunication Use Case</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Apelant</actor>
        <actor>Correspondant</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Apelant inserts the coins.</step>
        <step id="S2">Standard counts down for 2 minutes.</step>
        <step id="S3">Apelant dials the number.</step>
        <alt>
            <trigger>Number not dialed</trigger>
            <step id="S4">Standard hangs up on Apelant.</step>
        </alt>
        <else>
            <trigger>Number dialed</trigger>
            <step id="S5">Standard connects the line to the Correspondant.</step>
        </else>
        <alt>
            <trigger>Line busy</trigger>
            <step id="S6">Apelant hangs up.</step>
        </alt>
        <else>
            <trigger>Line free</trigger>
            <step id="S7">Correspondant picks up the phone.</step>
        </else>
        <step id="S8">Standard counts the coin consumption.</step>
        <step id="S9">Apelant adds more coins.</step>
        <step id="S10">Apelant and Correspondant talk.</step>
        <step id="S11">Correspondant hangs up.</step>
        <step id="S12">Apelant hangs up.</step>
        <step id="S13">Apelant and Correspondant disconnect the call.</step>
        <step id="S14">Standard returns the remaining coins to Apelant.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>
```

<useCase id="UC1">
  <name>Manage Start of PacMan Game</name>
  <actors>
    <actor>Foo</actor>
    <actor>PacManUser</actor>
    <actor>PacManController</actor>
    <actor>PacManPersistence</actor>
    <actor>FileReader</actor>
    <actor>FileWriter</actor>
  </actors>
  <preconditions>
    <precondition>The user interface allows input of a valid username</precondition>
  </preconditions>
  <successEndConditions>
    <condition>The PacMan game has started successfully</condition>
  </successEndConditions>
  <failureEndConditions>
    <condition>The PacMan game failed to start</condition>
  </failureEndConditions>
  <mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">Foo writes the username in the username input field</step>
    <step id="S2">PacManController updates the GUI</step>
    <step id="S3">PacManController gets the username from the input field</step>
    <step id="S4">PacManController triggers validation of the entered username by PacManUser</step>
    <step id="S5">PacManUser validates the entered username</step>
    <step id="S6">PacManController enables the start button</step>
    <step id="S7">Foo clicks the start button</step>
    <step id="S8">Start button click event is handled by PacManController</step>
    <step>A series of actions take place when the PacMan game commences</step>
    <step>Eventually, the PacManController saves the high score</step>
    <step>PacManPersistence reads scores from FileReader</step>
    <step>The PacManUser displays PacManUser credentials</step>
    <step>PacManPersistence writes updated scores using FileWriter</step>
  </mainSequence>
</useCase>

data.title: draft displaying the possible interAction of the L4 with the L3

content:
```xml
<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Interacting with L4 System</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Health Workers</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Health workers need to search for a patient.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Health workers search for a patient that was created before if needed.</step>
        <step id="S2">User interface searches for the patient.</step>
        <step id="S3">Engine chooses the IG to run.</step>
        <step id="S4">Engine finds available CarePlan using PlanDefinition/$Apply with patient as subject.</step>
        <step id="S5">Engine evaluates the condition of available PlanDefinitions and creates CarePlan for valid Actions.</step>
        <step id="S6">Engine sends a list of CarePlans to user interface.</step>
        <step id="S7">User interface displays available CarePlans.</step>
        <step id="S8">Health workers select a CarePlan.</step>
        <step id="S9">User interface sends the selected CarePlan to Engine.</step>
        <step id="S10">Engine saves the PlanDefinition for guideline-based care, determine diagnosis, dispense medications, and provide counseling based on Actioncode.</step>
        <step id="S11">Engine creates the encounter.</step>
        <step id="S12">Engine applies PlanDefinition/EmCareDXX/$Apply with patient as subject and encounter in the launch context.</step>
        <step id="S13">Engine replies with CarePlan referring to Activity or questionnaire.</step>
        <step id="S14">Engine saves the Action in memory.</step>
        <step id="S15">Engine populates the questionnaire and sends back the pre-filled QuestionnaireResponse.</step>
        <step id="S16">User interface sends the Questionnaire & QuestionnaireResponse.</step>
        <step id="S17">Health workers fill the questionnaire and submit it.</step>
        <step id="S18">User interface sends the questionnaire response to Engine.</step>
        <step id="S19">Engine runs the structureMap on the QuestionnaireResponse.</step>
        <step id="S20">Engine saves the created bundle.</step>
        <step id="S21">Engine applies PlanDefinition/EmCareDXX/$Apply and sends the classification questionnaire.</step>
        <step id="S22">User interface displays the classification questionnaire.</step>
        <step id="S23">Health workers agree or disagree with the classification and add it.</step>
        <step id="S24">User interface sends the questionnaire response to Engine.</step>
        <step id="S25">Engine runs the structureMap on the QuestionnaireResponse and saves the created bundle.</step>
        <step id="S26">Engine applies PlanDefinition/EmCareDXX/$Apply and sends the medication questionnaire.</step>
        <step id="S27">User interface displays the medication questionnaire.</step>
        <step id="S28">Health workers document if the medication is available.</step>
        <step id="S29">User interface sends the questionnaire response to Engine.</step>
        <step id="S30">Engine runs the structureMap on the QuestionnaireResponse and saves the created bundle.</step>
        <step id="S31">Engine applies PlanDefinition/EmCareDXX/$Apply and sends the counseling questionnaire.</step>
        <step id="S32">User interface displays the counseling questionnaire.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>
```

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Construcción de Fase</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Sistema o Usuario</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Iniciar construcción de fase</step>
        <step id="S2">Verificar si se puede costear la construcción</step>
        <step id="S3">Crear construcción tentativa</step>
        <step id="S4">Mover centro a una posición</step>
        <step id="S5">Mover centro a otra posición</step>
        <step id="S6">Finalizar construcción</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>No se puede construir la fase</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

</actors>
<preconditions>
</preconditions>
<successEndConditions>
</successEndConditions>
<failureEndConditions>
</failureEndConditions>
<trigger>
</trigger>
<mainSequence>
  <step id="S1">sistemaOUsuario initiates FaseConstruccion with construcciones.</step>
  <step id="S2">FaseConstruccion starts initiation of construible construction.</step>
  <step id="S3">Construcciones determines if it can bear the cost of the construible.</step>
  <step id="S4">FaseConstruccion receives true from Construcciones.</step>
  <step id="S5">FaseConstruccion creates ConstructionTentativa with construcciones and construible as parameters.</step>
  <step id="S6">ConstructionTentativa receives construction data from FaseConstruccion.</step>

</mainSequence>

</errorSteps>

```xml
<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Construction Phase</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>System or User</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Object to construct is defined</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Initiate construction phase</step>
        <step id="S2">Request start attempt for construction</step>
        <step id="S3">Check if object can be monetarily afforded</step>
        <step id="S4">Confirm object affordability</step>
        <step id="S5">Start construction attempt</step>
    </mainSequence>
    
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Object cannot be constructed</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
  
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S2" continue="S3">
            <step id="A1S1">Notify insufficient funds error to user</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
    
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Object can be constructed</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    
    <errorSteps id="E1" start="S4">
        <description>Show error to the user</description>
        <step id="E1S1">Move chosen construction location</step>
        <step id="E1S2">Attempt to move to a different location</step>
    </errorSteps>
    
</useCase>
```

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Profile Update</name>
    <actors>User</actors>
    <preconditions>User is logged in.</preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>User's profile is updated successfully.</successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>Validation errors are displayed.</failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>User enters updated profile information and submits.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User enters updated profile information.</step>
        <step id="S2">User submits the profile update form.</step>
        <step id="S3">ProfilePage sends HTTP POST request /profile/update with updated info to ProfileController.</step>
        <step id="S4">ProfileController calls UserService to updateUserProfile with updatedInfo.</step>
        <step id="S5">UserService validates the updatedInfo.</step>
        <step id="S6" actor="UserService">Validation succeeds.</step>
        <step id="S7">UserService saves the updated user info to UserRepository.</step>
        <step id="S8">UserRepository updates User data in the Database.</step>
        <step id="S9" actor="UserRepository">Database returns the update confirmation.</step>
        <step id="S10" actor="UserRepository">UserRepository returns the update confirmation to UserService.</step>
        <step id="S11" actor="UserService">UserService returns the update confirmation to ProfileController.</step>
        <step id="S12">ProfileController redirects to ProfilePage.</step>
        <step id="S13">ProfilePage displays the updated profile information to User.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
	<name>Update User Profile</name>
	<actors>
		<actor>User</actor>
	</actors>
	<preconditions>
		<precondition>User wants to update their profile information</precondition>
	</preconditions>
	<mainSequence>
		<step id="S1">User enters updated profile information</step>
		<step id="S2">User submits profile update form</step>
		<step id="S3">ProfileController receives HTTP POST /profile/update with updated info from ProfilePage</step>
		<step id="S4">UserService updates user profile using updateUserProfile method</step>
		<step id="S5">UserService validates the updated information</step>
	</mainSequence>
	<alternativeSteps>
		<asteps id="A1" start="S5" continue="Validation fails">
			<step id="A1S1">UserService returns validation errors</step>
			<step id="A1S2">ProfileController displays validation errors</step>
			<step id="A1S3">ProfilePage displays validation errors</step>
		</asteps>
	</alternativeSteps>
	<errorSteps>
		<esteps id="E1" start="S5">
			<description>Validation succeeds</description>
			<step id="E1S1">UserRepository saves the updated user information</step>
			<step id="E1S2">Database updates the User table with the new information</step>
			<step id="E1S3">UserRepository returns update confirmation</step>
			<step id="E1S4">UserService returns update confirmation to ProfileController</step>
			<step id="E1S5">ProfileController redirects to profile page</step>
			<step id="E1S6">ProfilePage displays the updated profile information</step>
		</esteps>
	</errorSteps>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Criar edificio</name>
    <description>Este caso de uso descreve o processo de criar um edifício no sistema.</description>

        <precondition>O GestorCampus tem permissão para criar edifícios.</precondition>

    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>O edifício foi criado com sucesso.</condition>

    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Falha ao criar o edifício.</condition>

        <step id="S1">O GestorCampus solicita a criação de um edifício.</step>

            <step id="A1S1">Se o envio dos dados for bem-sucedido:</step>

            <step id="A2S1">Se o envio dos dados falhar:</step>
            <step id="A2S2">O SistemaRobDroneGo envia uma mensagem de erro ao GestorCampus.</step>

```xml
<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Criar Edifício</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>GestorCampus</actor>
        <actor>SistemaRobDroneGo</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">O GestorCampus solicita a criação de um edifício ao SistemaRobDroneGo.</step>
        <step id="S2">O SistemaRobDroneGo solicita os dados necessários para criar o edifício ao GestorCampus.</step>
        <step id="S3">O GestorCampus envia os dados do edifício ao SistemaRobDroneGo.</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>O SistemaRobDroneGo envia uma mensagem de sucesso ao GestorCampus.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>O SistemaRobDroneGo envia uma mensagem de erro ao GestorCampus.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>
```

```xml
<useCase id="UC-001">
	<name>View and Change Payment Terms for Defendant Account</name>
	<actors>
		<actor>FAE User</actor>
		<actor>Customer Support</actor>
	</actors>
	<preconditions>
		<precondition>FAE User is logged into the application</precondition>
	</preconditions>
    <trigger>User selects 'Change' button on the Payment Terms tab</trigger>
	<mainSequence id="S1">
		<step id="S1.1">User navigates to the 'Change Payment Terms' page</step>
		<footer>Actors: FAE User</footer>
		<step id="S1.2">FAE User enters the required data and clicks 'Save changes' button</step>
		<footer>Actors: FAE User, Customer Support</footer>
		<step id="S1.3">Call API to change the Payment Terms with Defendant Account ID and JSON Payload</step>
		<footer>Actors: FAE User, Fines API</footer>
	</mainSequence>
	<alternativeSteps id="A1">
		<footer>Alternate StepId: A1, Cases: Opal Mode, Legacy Mode</footer>
		<asteps id="A1.1" start="S3" continue="S1">
			<step id="A1.1.1">Use JPA to create the Defendant Account Payment Terms</step>
			<step id="A1.2" actorName="Fines DB">Retrieve the created Defendant Account Payment Terms</step>
		</asteps>
		<asteps id="A1.2" start="S5" continue="    S1">
			<step id="A1.2.1">Convert JSON data to XML</step>
			<step id="A1.2.2">Create Defendant Account Payment Terms version in XML</step>
			<footer>Actors: GMAS DAC</footer>
			<step id="A1.2.3">Call the Legacy system using XML for creating Payment Terms</step>
			<footer>Actors: GMAS DAC, GOB SP</footer>
		</asteps>
	</alternativeSteps>
	<successEndConditions id="SC1">
	    <condition>No errors occurred during changing Defendant Account Payment Terms</condition>
	    <footer>Actors: All actors</footer>
	</successEndConditions>
	<failureEndConditions id="FC1">
	    <condition>Errors occurred during changing Payment Terms</condition>
	    <footer>Actors: All actors</footer>
	</failureEndConditions>
</useCase>
```

```xml
<useCase id="1">
    <name>DDO Publishing Flow</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>End User</actor>
        <actor>Consumer (Ocean CLI)</actor>
        <actor>Ocean.js</actor>
        <actor>Ocean Node</actor>
        <actor>Smart Contracts</actor>
        <actor>DDO.js</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">End User requests to publish a dataset with selected file.</step>
        <step id="S2">Consumer calls asset creation function.</step>
        <step id="S3">Ocean.js deploys data NFT & datatoken with pricing schema.</step>
        <step id="S4">Smart Contracts emit events.</step>
        <step id="S5">Ocean.js retrieves NFTCreated and DatatokenCreated events.</step>
        <step id="S6">Ocean.js requests encryption for DDO services files.</step>
        <step id="S7">Ocean Node returns 200 OK response if encryption is successful.</step>
        <step id="S8">Ocean.js requests encryption for DDO object.</step>
        <step id="S9">Ocean Node returns 200 OK response if encryption is successful.</step>
        <step id="S10">Ocean.js requests validation for DDO structure.</step>
        <step id="S11">DDO.js validates DDO structure using SHACL schemas.</step>
        <step id="S12">DDO.js response with success if validation is successful.</step>
        <step id="S13">Ocean Node indexes new DDOs.</step>
        <step id="S14">Ocean Node stores DDO in the database.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>
```

<useCase id="AddBook">
   <name>Add Book to Library</name>
   <actors>
      <actor>Librarian</actor>
   </actors>
   <mainSequence>
      <step id="S1">Navigate to BookPage</step>
      <step>A present Librarian initiates the navigation action to the BookPage.</step>
      <step id="S2">Click on Add Book</step>
      <step>Librarian clicks on the option to add a book.</step>
      <step id="S3">Display Add Book Options Pop-up</step>
      <step>The BookPage displays a pop-up with options to add a book.</step>
      <step id="S4">Click on Add Book Option</step>
      <step>Librarian selects to add a book</step>
      
      <alt id="A1">
         <step id="A1S1">Get Details with ISBN</step>
         <step>The librarian selects obtaining details through ISBN.</step>
         <step id="A1S2">Display ISBN Input Popup</step>
         <step>ISBN input popup occurs</step>
         <step id="A1S3">Enter ISBN</step>
         <step>The Librarian enters ISBN for book lookup</step>
         <step id="A1S4">Request Book Information by ISBN</step>
         <step>The book information is requested based on the entered ISBN.</step>
      </alt>

      <else>
         <step>Navigate to AddBookPage</step>
         <step>The system displays addBookPage to enter details manually.</step>
         <step id="S3">Fill in Book Information Form</step>
         <step>The Librarian fills in the form with the book details manually.</step>
         <step>Send Book Information</step>
         <step>The form data with book information is sent for further processing.</step>
      </else>
      
     <step id="S6">Add Book to Database</step>
     <step>The system adds the acquired book details to the Library database.
    </mainSequence>
      <step id="S7">Display Addition Confirmation</step>
    <step>The confirmation of adding the book displays back to librarian to confirm it.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="AddBook">
    <name>Add Book</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Librarian</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Librarian navigates to Book Page</step>
        <step id="S2">Librarian clicks on Add Book</step>

        <step id="S4">Librarian clicks on Add Book Option</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S5">
            <step id="A1S1">Book Page displays ISBN Input Popup</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Librarian enters ISBN</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Request Book Information by ISBN</step>
            <step id="A1S4">Retrieve Book Information by ISBN</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S5">
            <step id="A2S1">Navigate to Add Book Page</step>
            <step id="A2S2">Librarian fills in Book Information Form</step>
            <step id="A2S3">Send Book Information</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S6">Add Book to Database</step>
        <step id="S7">Display Addition Confirmation</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Adding Data File to Dataset</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>apiclient</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">APIClient sends a request to add a data file to a dataset using /add?datafile&datasetId endpoint.</step>
        <step id="S2">Datasets service is triggered.</step>
        <step id="S3">Datasets service invokes AddFileHelper to add the file to the dataset.</step>
        <step id="S4">AddFileHelper calls FileUtil to create data files.</step>
        <step id="S5">FileUtil determines the file type.</step>
        <step id="S6">FileUtil creates a single data file.</step>
        <step id="S7">AddFileHelper receives the Datafile List from FileUtil.</step>
        <step id="S8">AddFileHelper calls ISB to add the files to the dataset.</step>
        <step id="S9">AddFileHelper receives the dataset from ISB.</step>
        <step id="S10">AddFileHelper sends files to ISB for ingestion.</step>
        <step id="S11">ISB ingests the files as tabular data.</step>
        <step id="S12">AddFileHelper returns a JsonObjectBuilder object to Datasets service.</step>
        <step id="S13">Datasets service responds to APIClient with the added dataset details in JSON format.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

```xml
    <actors>

    </actors>

        <step id="S2">El Servicio de Sala de Chat guarda la Sala de Chat en el Repositorio.</step>

    </mainSequence>
</useCase>
```

    <name>Negotiation Pattern Sequence</name>
    <description>Describe the negotiation pattern sequence between Acquirer and Provider</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>Acquirer</actor>
        <actor>Provider</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>

    </successEndConditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Acquirer sends an OFFER to Provider</step>
        <step id="S2">Acquirer requests something from Provider</step>
        <step id="S3">Provider responds with an OFFER</step>
        <step id="S4">Acquirer sends another REQUEST</step>
        <step id="S5">Provider responds with the final <MATTER></step>
        <step id="S6">Acquirer acknowledges the <MATTER> received</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="1">
    <name>Negotiation Pattern Sequence</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Acquirer</actor>
        <actor>Provider</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Acquirer makes an OFFER to Provider.</step>
        <step id="S2">Acquirer requests from Provider.</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S2">
            <step id="A1S1">Provider makes an OFFER back to Acquirer.</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Acquirer requests again from Provider.</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S3">Provider makes an OFFER to Acquirer.</step>
        <step id="S4">Acquirer requests again from Provider.</step>
        <step id="S5">Provider presents the negotiated MATTER.</step>
        <step id="S6">Acquirer acknowledges the reception of the MATTER.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
  <name>Negotiation</name>
  <description>Manage the negotiation process between Acquirer and Provider</description>
  <actors>
    <actor>Acquirer</actor>
    <actor>Provider</actor>
  </actors>
  <preconditions>
    <precondition>An initial offer is strictly required, though it is expected OFFERs will precede a REQUEST.</precondition>
  </preconditions>
  <successEndConditions>
    <condition>An acknowledgement that the MATTER was received.</condition>
  </successEndConditions>
  <trigger>Initiate negotiation process whenever a request or offer is made by either party.</trigger>
  <mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">Acquirer sends an OFFER to Provider.</step>
    <step id="S2">Acquirer requests something from Provider.</step>
    <step id="S3">Provider responds with an OFFER.</step>
    <step id="S4">Provider sends a REQUEST to Acquirer.</step>
    <step id="S5">Acquirer responds with a REQUEST.</step>
    <step id="S6"><MATTER> is discussed and negotiated.</step>
    <step id="S7">Acquirer acknowledges receiving the <MATTER>.</step>
  </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Filling and submitting a resource</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User fills and submits the resource</step>
        <step id="S2">View sends resource create data</step>
        <step id="S3">Component requests the creation of resource</step>
        <step id="S4">Service requests POST</step>
        <step id="S5">POST resources</step>
        <step id="S6">HTTP response</step>
        <step id="S7">Service responds</step>
        <step id="S8">Component receives response</step>
        <step id="S9">Component informs view that the resource was created</step>
        <step id="S10">View displays success</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>The resource creation process was successful</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>An error occurred during the resource creation process</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

```xml
<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Adding User</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Admin</actor>
        <actor>UserController</actor>
        <actor>UserService</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Admin adds a user</step>
        <step id="S2">UserController checks user limit</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S2">
            <step id="A1S1">User addition possible</step>
            <step id="A1S2">UserService saves user to user_data.txt</step>
            <step id="A1S3">UserController informs Admin of successful user addition</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S2">
            <step id="A2S1">Limit reached</step>
            <step id="A2S2">UserController notifies Admin of error: Maximum user limit reached</step>
        </asteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>
```

```xml
<useCase id="UC_001">
    <name>Adding a User</name>
    <description>Use case for adding a user</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>Admin</actor>
        <actor>UserController</actor>
        <actor>UserService</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Admin is logged in</precondition>
        <precondition>User limit has not been reached</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>New user successfully added</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Add User error, user limit reached</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>Admin initiates add user process</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Admin requests to add a new user</step>
        <step id="S2">UserController receives add user request from Admin</step>
        <step id="S3">UserController forwards the request to UserService</step>
        <step id="S4">UserService checks if user limit allows for addition</step>
        <step id="S5">User limit check done.</step>
        <step id="S6" actor="UserService">User successfully added to user_data.txt</step>
        <step id="S7" actor="UserController">Confirmation that user was added sent back to Admin</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S5">
            <step id="A1S1">AR1: User limit reached, cannot add user</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
    <errorSteps>
        <esteps id="E1" start="S6">
            <description>Error while adding the user</description>
            <step id="E1S1">ER1: Error occurs while adding user to database</step>
        </esteps>
    </errorSteps>
</useCase>
```
