        <condition>User successfully added to the database</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>User is not added due to existing username</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>User initiates registration process</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Client fills out registration form:
            <actor>Client</actor> 
            filling out the registration form 
        </step>
        <step id="S2">Client submits registration data: 
            <actor>FE. Registration Form</actor> 
            receiving the user's data 
        </step>
        <step id="S3">FE. Registration Form sends POST request with data (username, password) to BE. Registration Script: 
            <actor>FE. Registration Form</actor> 
            sending data to 
            <actor>BE. Registration Script</actor> 
        </step>
        <step id="S4">BE. Registration Script checks for user existence in DB: 
            <actor>BE. Registration Script</actor> 
            communicating with 
            <actor>DB. Database</actor> 
        </step>
        <step id="S5">DB. Database processes the DB check result (exists/does not exist): 
            <actor>DB. Database</actor> 
            returning the check result back to 
            <actor>BE. Registration Script</actor> 
        </step>
        <step id="S6">User added scenario:
            <alt id="A1" start="S6">
                <step id="A1S1">BE. Registration Script inserts user data into DB: 
                    <actor>BE. Registration Script</actor> 
                    adding user to 
                    <actor>DB. Database</actor> 
                </step>
                <step id="A1S2">BE. Registration Script confirms successful user insert to the FE. Registration Form: 
                    <actor>BE. Registration Script</actor> 
                    sending confirmation to 
                    <actor>FE. Registration Form</actor>
                </step>
                <step id="A1S3">FE. Registration Form confirms user registration to the Client: 
                    <actor>FE. Registration Form</actor> 
                    notifying 
                    <actor>Client</actor> 
                </step>
            </alt>
        </step>
        <step id="S6">User not added scenario:
            <alt id="A2" start="S6">
                <step id="A2S1">BE. Registration Script informs FE. Registration Form on existing username: 
                    <actor>BE. Registration Script</actor> 
                    sending notification to 
                    <actor>FE. Registration Form</actor>
                </step>
                <step id="A2S2">FE. Registration Form informs Client of the error: existing username: 
                    <actor>FE. Registration Form</actor> 
                    warning 
                    <actor>Client</actor> 
                </step>
            </alt>
        </step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC_REGISTRATION">
    <name>User Registration</name>
    <description>Allow users to register in the system.</description>

        <actor>Client</actor>
        <actor frontstage="Intermediate" maintenance="Back-end Registration Script"></actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>The registration form is available.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Registration completed successfully.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Registration failed due to existing user.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>Form submission for user registration.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User fills out registration form.</step>
        <step id="S2">User submits registration data.</step>
        <step id="S3">Front-end sends data to Back-end Registration Script.</step>
    </mainSequence>

    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1">
            <step id="A1S1">Verify user data against existing records in the database.</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Add user into the database.</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Inform user of successful registration.</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>

    <errorSteps id="E1">
        <description>Alert user on error conditions and provide guidance.</description>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Process mobile payment</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Member</actor>
        <actor>Front End Application</actor>
        <actor>Payment Service</actor>
        <actor>Database</actor>
        <actor>Mobile Banking System</actor>
   </actors>

    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Member selects a payment option in the front end</step>
        <step id="S2">Front End Application initiates a payment request to the Payment Service</step>
        <step id="S3">Payment Service forwards payment processing request to Mobile Banking System</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S3">
            <step id="A1S1">Mobile Banking System processes the transaction for the Member</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Mobile Banking System sends transaction authentication to the Member</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Member authorizes the transaction on the Mobile Banking System</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S4">Payment Service confirms transaction success to Mobile Banking System</step>
        <step id="S5">Payment Service updates the payment status in the Database</step>
        <step id="S6">Database confirms the update to the Payment Service</step>
        <step id="S7">Payment Service displays a success message on the Front End Application</step>
       <step id="S8">Front End Application shows confirmation to the Member</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Authorization</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Alice</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Alice requests temporary object store credentials from Anonlink.</step>
        <step id="S2">Anonlink creates restricted credentials in the Object Store.</step>
        <step id="S3">Anonlink sends the Credentials Response to Alice.</step>
        <step id="S4">Anonlink provides Alice with temporary object store credentials.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>
<useCase id="UC2">
    <name>Upload Encodings</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Alice</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Alice uploads Binary Encoding Data to the Object Store.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>
<useCase id="UC3">
    <name>Trigger data pull</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Alice</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Alice uploads data via "/clks" to Anonlink, optionally providing blocks.</step>
        <step id="S2">Anonlink sends the Upload Receipt to Alice.</step>
        <!-- Some time later -->
        <step id="S3">Anonlink pulls/copies encoding data from the Object Store.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="001">
    <name>Authentication Login</name>
    <description>Allows Receptionist to authenticate using a username and password</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>Receptionist</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>Receptionist needs login credentials</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>User successfully logs in and accesses the dashboard</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>User fails to log in due to incorrect credentials</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>User wants to log in to the system</trigger>

    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Receptionist enters login credentials (username, password).</step>
        <step id="S2">UI submits a POST request to /login along with the entered credentials.</step>
        <step id="S3">Router directs the request to the AuthController which calls the UserRepository to validate credentials.</step>
        <step id="S4">Repository fetches the user by username through UserModel which queries the database.</step>
        <step id="S5">Controller computes if the entered password matches the user's password.</step>
        
        <asteps id="A1" start="S5">
            <step id="A1S1">If login is successful, Controller informs UI of success</step>
            <step id="AuthUserAccess">UI displays a success message to the Receptionist and directs Router to fetch dashboard</step>
            <step id="A3">Router fetches dashboard data from Repo, helping Controller access and display dashboard to UI.</step>
          
            <esteps id="E1" start="S5">
                <description>The case where login fails with incorrect credentials</description>
                <step id="E1PresentErrorMessage">User sees unauthorized message on the UI upon login error</step>
            </esteps>            
        </asteps>        
        
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="1">
    <name>Authentication Use Case</name>
    <description>This use case describes the authentication process for the Finance App.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Finance App</actor>
        <actor>Database</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>1. User is authenticated to access the Finance App.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>1. User successfully logs in with valid credentials.</condition>
        <condition>2. User successfully receives forgot password OTP.</condition>
        <condition>3. Server is available within the provided timeout limit.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>1. User fails to authenticate with incorrect credentials.</condition>
        <condition>2. User does not receive forgot password OTP.</condition>
        <condition>3. Server does not respond within the timeout limit.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>HTTP request is sent by the User to start the authentication process.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User sends an HTTP request to the Finance App.</step>
        <step id="S2">Finance App sends an SQL request to the Database.</step>
        <step id="S3">Database responds with an SQL response to the Finance App.</step>
        <step id="S4">Finance App sends an HTTP response back to the User.</step>
        <step id="S5">User sends an Authentication request to the Finance App.</step>
        <step id="S6">If valid credentials, Finance App sends an Authentication success response to the User. Otherwise, an Authentication failure response is sent.</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" continue="S6">
            <step id="A1S1">User requests forgot password from the Finance App.</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Finance App sends a forgot password OTP to the User.</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A2">
            <step id="A2S1">If the server times out, attempt to ping the server three times.</step>
            <step id="A2S2">Once the server is available, continue with the authentication process and send the response to the User.</step>
        </asteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Rate a Book</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Gateway</actor>
        <actor>Keycloak</actor>
        <actor>Catalog</actor>
        <actor>Postgres</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User is authenticated and authorized to rate a book.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>The book rating is successfully updated.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>The book does not exist or the user is not authorized to rate the book.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>PUT /api/v1/books/{id}/rate</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User initiates a request to rate a book.</step>
        <step id="S2">Gateway forwards the request to Keycloak to verify the JWT.</step>
        <step id="S3">Keycloak verifies the JWT.</step>
        <step id="S4">If JWT is valid:</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S4">
            <step id="A1S1">Gateway forwards the request to Catalog to update the book rating.</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Catalog searches for the book in the database.</step>
            <step id="A1S3">If the book exists:</step>
            <asteps id="A1S4" start="A1S3">
                <step id="A1S4S1">Catalog saves or updates the user's rating for the book in the database.</step>
                <step id="A1S4S2">Catalog responds with HttpStatus 200.</step>
                <step id="A1S4S3">Gateway forwards HttpStatus 200 to the User.</step>
            </asteps>
            <step id="A1S5">If the book does not exist:</step>
            <asteps id="A1S6" start="A1S5">
                <step id="A1S6S1">Catalog responds with HttpStatus 404.</step>
                <step id="A1S6S2">Gateway forwards HttpStatus 404 to the User.</step>
            </asteps>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S5">If JWT is absent:</step>
        <step id="S6">Gateway responds with HttpStatus 401 to the User.</step>
        <step id="S7">If JWT is not valid:</step>
        <step id="S8">Gateway responds with HttpStatus 403 to the User.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

        <step id="S3">If JWT is valid:</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S3">
            <step id="A1S1">Gateway forwards the request to the catalog service.</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Catalog service finds the book by ID in the database.</step>
            <step id="A1S3">If the book exists:</step>
            <asteps id="A1S3A1" start="A1S3">

        <step id="S4">If JWT is absent:</step>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S4">
            <step id="A2S1">Gateway responds with HttpStatus 401 to the user.</step>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S5">If JWT is not valid:</step>
        <asteps id="A3" start="S5">
            <step id="A3S1">Gateway responds with HttpStatus 403 to the user.</step>
        </asteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="1">
    <name>Rate a book</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>A User is authenticated and authorized to rate a book.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>The user successfully rates the book.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>The user is not able to rate the book due to invalid JWT or book not found.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User initiates rating a book by sending a PUT request to the gateway.</step>
        <step id="S2">Gateway verifies the JWT from Keycloak.</step>
        <step id="S3">If the JWT is valid,</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S3">
            <step id="A1S1">Gateway forwards the request to the catalog service to rate the book.</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Catalog service finds the book by ID in the PostgreSQL database.</step>
            <step id="A1S3">If the book exists in the database,</step>
            <asteps id="A1A1" start="A1S3">
                <step id="A1A1S1">Catalog service saves or updates the user's rating for the book in the PostgreSQL database.</step>
                <step id="A1A1S2">Catalog service responds with HttpStatus 200 to the gateway.</step>
                <step id="A1A1S3">Gateway responds with HttpStatus 200 to the user.</step>
            </asteps>
            <step id="A1S4">If the book doesn't exist in the database,</step>
            <asteps id="A1A2" start="A1S4">
                <step id="A1A2S1">Catalog service responds with HttpStatus 404 to the gateway.</step>
                <step id="A1A2S2">Gateway responds with HttpStatus 404 to the user.</step>
            </asteps>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S4">If the JWT is absent, gateway responds with HttpStatus 401 to the user.</step>
        <step id="S5">If the JWT is not valid, gateway responds with HttpStatus 403 to the user.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

            <step id="A1S3">If the book exists:</step>

                <step id="A1S4S3">The gateway forwards the HTTP Status 200 response to the user</step>
            </asteps>
            <step id="A1S5">If the book does not exist:</step>
            <asteps id="A1S6">
                <step id="A1S6S1">The catalog service responds with HTTP Status 404</step>
                <step id="A1S6S2">The gateway forwards the HTTP Status 404 response to the user</step>
            </asteps>
        </asteps>
        <step id="S4">If the JWT is absent, the gateway responds with HTTP Status 401</step>
        <step id="S5">If the JWT is not valid, the gateway responds with HTTP Status 403</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">

    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Repository Manager initiates the update.</step>
        <step id="S2">DIMS Interface submits the update request.</step>

        <step id="S5">Central Repository Info Management confirms the update success to DIMS Interface.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

        <step id="S1">DIMS Interface triggers the synchronization.</step>
        <step id="S2">DAMS Sync Service retrieves the updated information from DAMS.</step>
        <step id="S3">DAMS Sync Service propagates updates to relevant areas in DAMS.</step>
        <step id="S4">DAMS Sync Service confirms the propagation completion to DIMS Interface.</step>
        <step id="S5">DIMS Interface confirms the update and propagation to Repository Manager.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

    <name>Change Image Resolution Configuration</name>
    <description>User configures the image resolution for the device through the Mobile App.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Mobile App</actor>
        <actor>Server</actor>
        <actor>ESP32</actor>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Recover Document Type</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Frontend</actor>
        <actor>Backend</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>User is authorized with ADMIN role.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <trigger>POST /api/doctype/{id}/recover</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User sends a request to recover a document type.</step>
        <step id="S2">Check if the user has appropriate ADMIN role.</step>
        <step id="S3">Validate the request.</step>
        <step id="S4">Recover document type by ID.</step>
        <step id="S5">Find the document type in the database by ID.</step>
        <step id="S6">Check the state of the document type.</step>
        <step id="S7">Set document type state to ACTIVE.</step>
        <step id="S8">Save the updated document type in the database.</step>
        <step id="S9">Return success response with the recovered document type.</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <failureEndConditions>
        <condition>User doesn't have ADMIN role.</condition>
        <condition>Request is invalid.</condition>
        <condition>Document type is not found.</condition>
        <condition>Document type state is ACTIVE.</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
  <name>Login Process</name>
  <description>User logging into the system using their username and password</description>
  <actors>
    <actor>User</actor>
  </actors>
  <preconditions>
    <precondition>System must be up and running</precondition>
  </preconditions>
  <successEndConditions>
    <condition>User successfully authenticated</condition>
  </successEndConditions>
  <failureEndConditions>
    <condition>User fails authentication process</condition>
  </failureEndConditions>
  <trigger>User initiates the login process</trigger>
  <mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">User enters their Username and Password</step>
    <step id="S2">System sends Username and Password to the server</step>
    <step id="S3">Server validates the credentials with the main portal</step>
    <step id="S4">If the credentials are valid:</step>
    <step>AUTHENTICATION RESULT: 'Ok'</step>
    <step id="S5">Save user details and assign default Authorities</step>
    <step id="S6">If the credentials are not valid:</step>
    <step>AUTHENTICATION RESULT: 'nicht angemeldet'</step>
    <step>Notify the user 'Bad credentials'</step>   
  </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>User Login</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Spring</actor>
        <actor>Lewensportal</actor>
        <actor>DB</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User opens TimeReport</step>
        <step id="S2">User enters Username (FnNn) and Password</step>
        <step id="S3">Spring forwards Username and Password to Lewensportal</step>
        <alt>
            <preconditions>User's credentials are valid</preconditions>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>View List of Customers</name>
    <description>User opens the customers list page and requests to view all customers.</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>UI</actor>
        <actor>Router</actor>
        <actor>Controller</actor>
        <actor>Repository</actor>
        <actor>Model</actor>
        <actor>DB</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>User is logged in and has access to the customers list page.</preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>The list of customers is successfully displayed to the user.</successEndConditions>
    <trigger>User opens the customers list page.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User opens customers list page.</step>
        <step id="S2">UI displays loading message.</step>
        <step id="S3">User requests all customers.</step>
        <step id="S4">UI sends GET request to Router for /customers.</step>
        <step id="S5">Router calls getAllCustomers() in Controller.</step>
        <step id="S6">Controller calls findAll() in Repository.</step>
        <step id="S7">Repository calls find() in Model.</step>
        <step id="S8">Model fetches all customers from DB.</step>
        <step id="S9">DB returns all customers to Model.</step>
        <step id="S10">Model returns all customers to Repository.</step>
        <step id="S11">Repository returns all customers to Controller.</step>
        <step id="S12">Controller responds with 200 OK (all customers) to Router.</step>
        <step id="S13">Router responds with 200 OK (all customers) to UI.</step>
        <step id="S14">UI displays list of customers to the User.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

Retrieve Monthly Lending Information As a Librarian, I want to retrieve information on monthly lendings from the system to view and analyze them. Librarian Librarian wants to view monthly lending information The Librarian sends a GET request to the LendingController for /api/lendings/monthly-lending The LendingController activates and calls the ReaderService's method to getAllReaders() The ReaderService accesses the ReaderRepository to findAll() readers For each reader, the ReaderService requests the ReaderRepository to get the monthly lending information The ReaderService appoints the ReaderLentsViewMapper
to structure Iterable of ReaderLentsView objects The LendingController delivers HTTP 200 OK response
with Iterable of ReaderLentsView objects
back to the Librarian

<useCase id="1">
  <name>Creación de identidad</name>
  <actors>
    <actor>User</actor>
  </actors>
  <mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">Instalación de la aplicación Alastria en el móvil.</step>
    <step id="S2">Solicitud del token de sesión.</step>
    <step id="S3">Entrega del token de sesión.</step>
    <step id="S4">Quiero darme de alta en alastria id.</step>
    <step id="S5">Preparación de objeto JSON con el alta en alastria.</step>
    <step id="S6">Envío de la url de recuperación del JSON con el token de sesión.</step>
    <step id="S7">Push de la url de recuperación del JSON.</step>
    <step id="S8">Recuperación de la clave pública para verificar la información recuperada.</step>
    <step id="S9">Solicito la recuperación de la clave pública de la aplicación.</step>
    <step id="S10">Aceptación de la llamada.</step>
    <step id="S11">Reenvío al proxy.</step>
    <step id="S12">Recupero la clave pública del usuario.</step>
    <step id="S13">Clave pública del alastria_id asociada a la aplicación.</step>
    <step id="S14">Clave pública de alastria_id asociada a la aplicación.</step>
    <step id="S15">Verificación de la firma del objeto JSON.</step>
    <step id="S16">Creación del alastria_id del usuario.</step>
    <step id="S17">Se crea un nuevo Proxy().</step>
    <step id="S18">Alastria_id creado.</step>
    <step id="S19">Se tiene una identidad vacia. Requerimiento de testimonios iniciales.</step>
    <step id="S20">La URL de recuperación de los atestados, se ha recibido en el JSON del push inicial.</step>
  </mainSequence>
  <alternativeSteps>
    <asteps start="S8">
      <step id="A1S1">Solicitud de recupero de clave pública</step>
      <step id="A1S2">Aceptación de la llamada.</step>
      <step id="A1S3">Reenvío al proxy.</step>
      <step id="A1S4">Registro de la clave pública.</step>
      <step id="A1S5">Devuelve OK de clave registrada.</step>
      <step id="A1S6">OK.</step>
    </asteps>
    <asteps start="S21">
      <step id="A2S1">Solicitud de los atestados aportados por el socio.</step>
      <step id="A2S2">Construcción de los atestados del usuario (JSON Firmado).</step>
      <step id="A2S3">Envío de la URL de recuperación de los atestados.</step>
      <step id="A2S4">Notificación Push con URL de recuperación de los atestados.</step>
      <step id="A2S5">Verificación de la firma del objeto JSON.</step>
      <step id="A2S6">Aceptación y firma de los atestados.</step>
      <step id="A2S7">Almacenamiento del atestado.</step>
      <step id="A2S8">Uri de recuperación.</step>
      <step id="A2S9">Registro de los atributo en registry.</step>
      <step id="A2SO"> Registro de los atributos en registry (Hash y/o URI por atributo).</step>
      <step id="AOS1"> Respuesta OK. </step>
    </asteps>
  </alternativeSteps>
</useCase>

        <step id="S7">Edge Agent 1 adds keys and authorizations for agent 2 to policy registry.</step>
        <step id="S8">Edge Agent 1 syncs data to agent 2 - A<sub>LS</sub>, token data, claims.</step>
        <step id="S9">Edge Agent 2 stores data in wallet.</step>
    </mainSequence>

        <condition>Agent 2 successfully added and provisioned with necessary data.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>

        <condition>Agent 2 addition and provisioning failed due to incorrect data exchange.</condition>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Verify Checksum Status</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>RepositoryManager</actor>
        <actor>DIMS System</actor>
        <actor>Digital Repository</actor>
        <actor>Checksum Database</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">RepositoryManager requests checksum status</step>
        <step id="S2">DIMS System queries latest content file details from Digital Repository</step>
        <step id="S3">Digital Repository returns file details to DIMS System</step>
        <step id="S4">DIMS System retrieves stored checksums from Checksum Database</step>
        <step id="S5">Checksum Database provides checksum data to DIMS System</step>
        <step id="S6">DIMS System compares latest and stored checksums</step>
        <alt id="A1">
            <step id="A1S1">Checksum changed</step>
            <step id="A1S2">DIMS System notifies RepositoryManager of checksum change</step>
        </alt>
        <else>
            <step id="E1">Checksum unchanged</step>
            <step id="E1S1">DIMS System confirms no changes to RepositoryManager</step>
        </else>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
  <name>Verify Checksum Status</name>
  <actors>
    <actor>Repository Manager</actor>
  </actors>
  <preconditions>
    <precondition>Repository Manager requests checksum status</precondition>
  </preconditions>
  <trigger>Request checksum status</trigger>  
  <mainSequence>
    <step id="S1">Repository Manager requests checksum status to DIMS System.</step>
    <step id="S2">DIMS System queries latest content file details from the Digital Repository.</step>
    <step id="S3">Digital Repository returns file details to DIMS System.</step>
    <step id="S4">DIMS System retrieves stored checksums from the Checksum Database.</step>
    <step id="S5">Checksum Database provides checksum data to DIMS System.</step>
    <step id="S6">DIMS System compares the latest and stored checksums.</step>
  </mainSequence>
  <alternativeSteps>
    <asteps id="A1" start="S6">
      All checksum unchanged scenario
      <step id="A1S1">DIMS then confirms checksums are unchanged to Repository Manager.</step>
    </asteps>
    <asteps id="A2" start="S6">
      Checksum changed scenario
      <step id="A2S1">DIMS then notifies Repository Manager of the checksum change.</step>
    </asteps>
  </alternativeSteps>
</useCase>

<useCase id="uc1">
    <name>Manage Bookings</name>
    
    <actors>
        <actor>Client</actor>
        <actor>BookingsPage</actor>
        <actor>BookingValidator</actor>
        <actor>DatabaseManager</actor>
        <actor>Booking</actor>
    </actors>
    
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>The "Manage Bookings" page is accessible to the Client.</precondition>
        <precondition>The Client's bookings are retrievable from the database.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Client opens the Manage Bookings Page.</step>
        <step id="S2">BookingsPage queries Client's bookings.</step>
        <step id="S3">Database returns bookings to BookingsPage.</step>
        <step id="S4">BookingsPage displays the bookings list to the Client.</step>
   </mainSequence>

    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S4">
            <step>Client selects "Cancel Booking" with bookingId (bookingId).</step>
            <step>BookingsPage validates the cancellation with clientId and bookingId.</step>
            <step>Validator checks the ownership of the booking (clientId, bookingId).</step>
            <step>Validator verifies the cancellation rules for the booking (bookingId).</step>
            <step>Validator encounters a validation failure.</step>
            <step>Display Error: "Cannot cancel this booking."</step>
        </asteps>

        <asteps id="A2" start="S4">
            <step>Client Edits a Booking by selecting "Edit Booking" with bookingId     (bookingId).</step>
            <step>BookingsPage validates the edit  with clientId and bookingId.</step>
            <step>Validator validates the ownership of the booking (clientId, bookingId).</step>
            <step>Validator verifies the edit rules for the booking (bookingId).</step>
            <step>Validator encounters a validation failure.</step>
            <step>Display Error: "Cannot edit this booking."</step>
       </asteps>

        <asteps id="A3" start="S4">
            <step>Client Views Bookings by selecting "View Details" with a specific bookingId (bookingId).</step>
            <step>BookingsPage fetches details from database for booking (bookingId).</step>
            <step>Database return the booking details to the BookingsPage.</step>
            <step>BookingsPage displays the booking details to the Client.</step>
         </asteps>
     </alternativeSteps>
</useCase>​

<useCase id="UC1">

        <actor>Member</actor>
        <actor>Search Interface</actor>
        <actor>Library Database</actor>
        <actor>Book Details</actor>
        <actor>Availability Checker</actor>
        <actor>Reservation System</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>The Member is logged into the system.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <trigger>The Member initiates a search for a book and wishes to borrow or reserve it.</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Member enters search query (title, author, or category).</step>
        <step id="S2">Search Interface fetches matching books from Library Database.</step>
        <step id="S3">Library Database returns a list of books to Search Interface.</step>
        <step id="S4">Search Interface displays the list of books to the Member.</step>
        <step id="S5">Member selects a book to check availability in Book Details.</step>
        <step id="S6">Book Details requests availability status from Availability Checker.</step>
        <step id="S7">Availability Checker checks the status for the selected book in the Database.</step>
        <step id="S8">Availability Checker queries current borrowings & reservations from Database.</step>
        <step id="S9">Availability Checker receives availability data from Database.</step>
        <step id="S10">Availability Checker shows availability status to Book Details.</step>
        <step id="S11">Book Details displays if the book is available or reserved to the Member.</step>
        <step id="S12">If the book is available, Member requests to borrow the book.</step>
        <step id="S13">Reservation System updates the book status to "on loan" in the Database.</step>
        <step id="S14">Database confirms the update to Reservation System.</step>
        <step id="S15">Reservation System provides confirmation & due date to the Member.</step>
        <step id="S16">If the book is reserved, Member places a reservation request.</step>
        <step id="S17">Reservation System adds the request to the reservation queue in the Database.</step>
        <step id="S18">Database confirms the reservation to Reservation System.</step>
        <step id="S19">Reservation System provides confirmation & estimated wait time to the Member.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="transaction_workflow">
    <name>Current Epic Transaction Workflow</name>
    <description>Accurate as of Oct 10, 2018 - Master branch only</description>
    
    <actors>
        <actor>Sender</actor>
        <actor>Recipient</actor>
    </actors>

    <:mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Sender creates Transaction UUID.</step>
        <step id="S2">Set lock_height for transaction kernel (uses current chain height).</step>
        <step id="S3">Sender selects inputs using desired selection strategy.</step>
        <step id="S4">Sender calculates sum of inputs' blinding factors xI.</step>
        <step id="S5">Sender creates change_output.</step>
        <step id="S6">Sender selects blinding factor xC for change_output.</step>
        <step id="S7">Sender creates lock function sF, linking inputs & change_output in wallet.</step>
        
        <step id=”S8”>Sender calculates transaction weight.</step>
        <step id=”S9">Sender calculates fee based on transaction weight.</step>
        <step id=”S10”>Sender calculates total blinding excess sum xS1.</step>
        <step id=”S11”>Sender selects a random nonce kS.</step>
        <step id=”S12”>Sender subtracts random kernel offset oS from xS1.</step>
        <step id=”S13”>Sender creates public curve points xSG and kSG.</step>
        <step id=”S14”>Sender adds values to Slate.</step>

        <asteps id="A1" start="S9">
            <step id="A1S1">Recipient checks fee against number of inputs, change_outputs, and receiver_output(s).</step>
            <step>Recipient creates receiver_output.</step>
            <step>Recipient chooses random blinding factor xR for receiver_output.</step>
            <step>Recipient calculates the message M.</step>
            <step>Recipient chooses spend nonce kR.</step>
            <step>Recipient computes public curve points xRG and kRG.</step>
            <step>Recipient computes Schnorr challenge e.</step>
            <step>Recipient computes Schnorr signature sR.</step>
            <step>Recipient adds sR, xRG, kRG to Slate.</step>
            <step>Recipient creates wallet output function rF.</step>
        </asteps>

        <errorSteps id="E1" start="S14">
            <description>Fail execution if any error occurs.
            <step>Recipient aborts transaction on failure.
            </step>
            <step>Error message is sent back to the sender on failure.
            </step>
            <step>Abrupt abort signal from recipient to sender.
            </step>
        </errorSteps>
    </:mainSequence>
      
    <trigger>“Slate“ message passed from Sender to Recipient</trigger>
</useCase>

        <step id="S7">PostService transforms the PostDto into a Post.</step>
        <step id="S8">PostRepository creates the post entity.</step>

<useCase id="UC2">
    <name>Inserting a new row</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>user</actor>
        <actor>api</actor>
        <actor>lexorank</actor>
        <actor>storage</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User sends an insert request.</step>
        <step id="S2">API receives the insert request.</step>
        <step id="S3">API calls lexorank's "insertAt()" method.</step>
        <step id="S4">Lexorank requests a snapshot of rows and ranks from storage.</step>
        <step id="S5">Storage provides the snapshot to lexorank.</step>
        <step id="S6">Lexorank locks the snapshot and checks for rank collisions.</step>
        <step id="S7">If a collision occurs, lexorank applies updates in cascade.</step>
        <step id="S8">Lexorank inserts the new record into storage.</step>
        <step id="S9">Lexorank returns the new row to API.</step>
        <step id="S10">API returns the new row to the user.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="HasKeychainEntryEndpoint">
    <name>Invoke Name Of User action: Request transaction with   keychain entry on Hyperledger Cactus API</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>User A</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User A initiates a transaction with 'Tx HasKeychainEntryV1'.</step>
        <step id="S2">API Client forwards the request to API Server.</step>
        <step id="S3">API Server calls the set() function of AWS Secrets Manager to set a key-value pair.</step>
        <step id="S4">AWS Secrets Manager returns awsClient by calling getAwsClient().</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S4">
            <step id="A1S1">In an attempt to call awsClient.describeSecret().</step>
 		   <step id="A1S2">If the call returns true, stepEnd.</step>
		   <step id="A1S3">Else if it catches an exception and errors "Secrets Manager can't find the specified secret", stepEnd showing correct message.</step>
        </asteps>
   <step id="S5">The response is sent back from AWS Secrets Manager to API Server.</step>
   <step id="S6">API Server delivers the formatted response to API Client.</step>
   <step id="S7">API Client sends the SetKeychainEntryResponse notification to User A.</step>
	</mainSequence>
    <successEndConditions>
        <condition>Correct Response formatted.</condition>
    </successEndConditions>
	<failureEndConditions>
        <condition>Error: [description of what pre conditions needed being unavailable]</condition>
    </failureEndConditions>
</useCase>

Display Job Openings A customer manager asks to display job openings in the results phase CustomerManager PublishJobOpeningUI JobOpeningRepository FollowUpServerProxy ClientSocket FollowUpServer ResultEmailRequest CandidateSelectionService EmailService Notification NotificationRepository CustomerManager is logged in and on the results page. CustomerManager asks the PublishJobOpeningU
i to display job openings. PublishJobOpeningUI gets job openings. GetJobOpenings retrieves job openings from JobOpeningRepository. PublishJobOpeningUI displays job openings. PublishJobOpeningUI selects a job opening to publish results. PublishJobOpeningController publishes the selected job opening results. FollowUpServerProxy sends the result email request for the job opening. FollowUpServerProxy creates and connects a ClientSocket, sends the request to FollowUpServer, FollowUpServer receives the request. FollowUpServer parses the request and creates a ResultEmailRequest. ResultEmailRequest executes, selects candidates in CandidateSelectionService. CandidateSelectionService returns selected and rejected lists of candidates. EmailService sends emails to the selected candidates. EmailService creates a notification and saves it in NotificationRepository. EmailService notifies the ResultEmailRequest that emails have been sent. FollowUpServer writes a response. FollowUpServer closes the connection on the socket. FollowUpServerProxy responds to the control. PublishJobOpeningController responds to PublishJobOpeningUI. PublishJobOpeningUI confirms the operation success to CustomerManager.

<useCase id="1">
<name>Publish Job Opening Results</name>
<actors>CustomerManager, PublishJobOpeningUI, JobOpening, PublishJobOpeningController, JobOpeningRepository, FollowUpServerProxy, ClientSocket, FollowUpServer, FollowUpMessageParser, ResultEmailRequest, CandidateSelectionService, EmailService, Notification, NotificationRepository</actors>
<mainSequence>
	<step id="S1">CustomerManager asks to display job openings in the results phase</step>
	<step id="S2">PublishJobOpeningUI triggers getJobOpenings in PublishJobOpeningController</step>
	<step id="S3">PublishJobOpeningController requests job openings from JobOpeningRepository</step>
	<step id="S4">JobOpeningRepository fetches job openings</step>
	<step id="S5">JobOpeningRepository sends job openings data to PublishJobOpeningController</step>
	<step id="S6">PublishJobOpeningController provides job openings data to PublishJobOpeningUI</step>
	<step id="S7">PublishJobOpeningUI displays job openings</step>
	<step id="S8">CustomerManager selects a job opening to publish results</step>
	<step id="S9">PublishJobOpeningUI triggers publishJobOpeningResults in PublishJobOpeningController</step>
	<step id="S10">PublishJobOpeningController initiates result notification for selected job opening</step>
	<step id="S11">FollowUpServerProxy prepares and sends request to publish result via the server</step>
	<step id="S12">FollowUpServerProxy creates and connects ClientSocket to the server</step>
	<step id="S13">FollowUpServerProxy sends result request to the server using ClientSocket</step>
	<step id="S14">Server receives the request, parses it, and creates a ResultEmailRequest</step>
	<step id="S15">Server executes the ResultEmailRequest, triggering CandidateSelectionService to select candidates for email notification</step>
	<step id="S16">ResultEmailRequest selects candidates and rejects others, proceeds to EmailService</step>
	<step id="S17">EmailService sends notification emails to selected candidates</step>
	<step id="S18">EmailService creates and saves the notification in NotificationRepository</step>
    <step id="S19">NotificationRepository stores the notification</step>
    <step id="S20">Email notification is sent successfully to selected candidates, server completes operation</step>
</mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Відкрити файл</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Користувач</actor>
    </actors>
    <trigger>Натискання «Відкрити»</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Користувач натискає кнопку «Відкрити» на інтерфейсі.</step>
        <step id="S2">Інтерфейс створює запит до файлової системи.</step>
        <step id="S3">Файлова система повертає вміст у форматі CSV інтерфейсу.</step>
        <step id="S4">Користувач визначає модель даних для списку 1.</step>
        <step id="S5">Користувач визначає модель даних для списку 2.</step>
        <step id="S6">Користувач натискає Ctrl + N.</step>
        <step id="S7">Інтерфейс отримує фокус на конкретному елементі.</step>
        <step id="S8">Список 1 додає рядок.</step>
        <step id="S9">Створюється редактор для редагування рядка у списку 1.</step>
        <step id="S10">Користувач отримує запит на введення тексту.</step>
        <step id="S11">Користувач вводить текст.</step>
        <step id="S12">Користувач завершує редагування.</step>
        <step id="S13">Редактор рядка знищується із списку 1.</step>
        <step id="S14">Користувач перетягує задачу.</step>
        <step id="S15">Список 1 отримує запит на переміщення.</step>
        <step id="S16">Здійснюється перетягування елемента між списком 1 та списком 2 за допомогою Drag & Drop.</step>
        <step id="S17">Користувач натискає кнопку «Зберегти».</step>
        <step id="S18">Користувач обирає файл для збереження.</step>
        <step id="S19">Інтерфейс отримує шлях до файлу від користувача.</step>
        <step id="S20">Інтерфейс створює запит до файлової системи для збереження.</step>
        <step id="S21">Користувач натискає кнопку «Вийти».</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="1">
    <name>Xem danh sách người dùng</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Quản trị viên</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Truy cập trang quản lý người dùng</step>
        <step id="S2">Gửi yêu cầu lấy danh sách người dùng từ Web UI</step>
        <step id="S3">Truy vấn danh sách người dùng từ API Gateway DB</step>
        <step id="S4">Hiển thị danh sách người dùng</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="2">
    <name>Tạo mới người dùng</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Quản trị viên</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S5">Kích vào "Thêm người dùng mới" trên Web UI</step>
        <step id="S6">Hiển thị form nhập thông tin</step>
        <step id="S7">Nhập thông tin và gửi</step>
        <step id="S8">Gửi yêu cầu tạo người dùng mới qua API Gateway Service</step>
        <step id="S9">Kiểm tra email và số điện thoại tồn tại trong API Gateway DB</step>
        <step id="S10">Xử lý theo kết quả kiểm tra</step>
        <alternativeSteps id="A1">
            <asteps id="A1S1">Email đã tồn tại</asteps>
            <step id="A1S2">Hiển thị thông báo lỗi từ API Gateway Service</step>
        </alternativeSteps>
        <alternativeSteps id="A2">
            <asteps id="A2S1">Email chưa tồn tại</asteps>
            <step id="A2S2">Mã hóa mật khẩu trong API Gateway Service</step>
            <step id="A2S3">Lưu thông tin người dùng mới vào API Gateway DB</step>
            <step id="A2S4">Hiển thị thông báo thành công từ API Gateway Service</step>
            <step id="A2S5">Yêu cầu làm mới danh sách người dùng</step>
            <step id="A2S6">Truy vấn danh sách người dùng trong API Gateway DB</step>
            <step id="A2S7">Hiển thị danh sách người dùng mới</step>
        </alternativeSteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="3">
    <name>Cập nhật người dùng</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Quản trị viên</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S11">Chỉnh sửa thông tin người dùng trên trang Web UI</step>
        <step id="S12">Gửi yêu cầu lấy thông tin chi tiết người dùng qua API Gateway Service</step>
        <step id="S13">Truy vấn thông tin của người dùng trong API Gateway DB</step>
        <step id="S14">Hiển thị form chỉnh sửa với thông tin hiện tại</step>
        <step id="S15">Cập nhật thông tin và gửi</step>
        <step id="S16">Gửi yêu cầu cập nhật thông tin qua API Gateway Service</step>
        <step id="S17">Kiểm tra tính hợp lệ của thông tin đã cập nhật</step>
        <step id="S18">Xử lý theo kết quả kiểm tra</step>
        <alternativeSteps id="A3">
            <asteps id="A3S1">Thông tin không hợp lệ</asteps>
            <step id="A3S2">Hiển thị thông báo lỗi từ API Gateway Service</step>
        </alternativeSteps>
        <alternativeSteps id="A4">
            <asteps id="A4S1">Thông tin hợp lệ</asteps>
            <step id="A4S2">Cập nhật thông tin người dùng trong API Gateway DB</step>
            <step id="A4S3">Hiển thị thông báo thành công từ API Gateway Service</step>
            <step id="A4S4">Yêu cầu làm mới danh sách người dùng</step>
            <step id="A4S5">Truy vấn danh sách người dùng trong API Gateway DB</step>
            <step id="A4S6">Hiển thị danh sách người dùng đã cập nhật</step>
        </alternativeSteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="4">
    <name>Xóa người dùng</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Quản trị viên</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S19">Chọn "Xóa" bên cạnh người dùng trên Web UI</step>
        <step id="S20">Hiển thị hộp thoại xác nhận trên Web UI</step>
        <step id="S21">Xác nhận xóa</step>
        <step id="S22">Gửi yêu cầu xóa người dùng qua API Gateway Service</step>
        <step id="S23">Xóa hoặc đánh dấu người dùng không hoạt động trong API Gateway DB</step>
        <step id="S24">Hiển thị thông báo thành công từ API Gateway Service</step>
        <step id="S25">Yêu cầu làm mới danh sách người dùng</step>
        <step id="S26">Truy vấn danh sách người dùng trong API Gateway DB</step>
        <step id="S27">Hiển thị danh sách người dùng đã cập nhật</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="5">
    <name>Tìm kiếm người dùng</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Quản trị viên</actor>
    </actors>

        <step id="S28">Nhập từ khóa tìm kiếm trên Web UI</step>
        <step id="S29">Gửi yêu cầu tìm kiếm người dùng qua API Gateway Service</step>
        <step id="S30">Tìm kiếm người dùng trong API Gateway DB</step>
        <step id="S31">Trả kết quả tìm kiếm về Web UI</step>
        <alternativeSteps id="A5">
            <asteps id="A5S1">Không có kết quả tìm kiếm</asteps>
            <step id="A5S2">Hiển thị thông báo "Không tìm thấy người dùng" trên Web UI</step>

            <asteps id="A6S1">Có kết quả tìm kiếm</asteps>
            <step id="A6S2">Hiển thị danh sách người dùng phù hợp trên Web UI</step>
        </alternativeSteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>View POA Requests List</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Accredited Representative</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Accredited Representative views POA Requests List</step>
        <step id="S2">Frontend sends GET request to Backend: GET /v0/accredited_representative_portal/poa_requests</step>
        <step id="S3">Backend verifies representative in ar_user_account_accredited_individuals in VAGovDB</step>
        <step id="S4">Backend queries POA Requests with joins from VAGovDB</step>
        <step id="S5">Backend sends JSON Response with POA List to Frontend</step>
        <step id="S6">Frontend displays POA Requests</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC002">
    <name>View POA Request Details</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Accredited Representative</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Accredited Representative selects a POA Request</step>
        <step id="S2">Frontend sends GET request to Backend: GET /v0/accredited_representative_portal/poa_requests/{id}</step>
        <step id="S3">Backend verifies representative authorization for the request in VAGovDB</step>
        <step id="S4">Backend queries Single POA Request with detailed information from VAGovDB</step>
        <step id="S5">Backend sends JSON Response with POA Details to Frontend</step>
        <step id="S6">Frontend displays POA Details</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC003">
    <name>Make Decision</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Accredited Representative</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Accredited Representative submits a decision (Accept/Decline)</step>
        <step id="S2">Frontend sends POST request to Backend: POST /v0/accredited_representative_portal/poa_requests/{id}/decision</step>
        <step id="S3">Backend verifies representative can make the decision in VAGovDB</step>
        <step id="S4">Backend submits POA Decision to LighthouseAPI</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S4">
            <step id="A1S1">Backend creates PowerOfAttorneyRequestDecision</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Backend creates PowerOfAttorneyRequestResolution</step>
            <step id="A1S3">Backend updates PowerOfAttorneyFormSubmission (status: PENDING|FAILED|SUCCEEDED)</step>
            <step id="A1S4">Backend sends Success Response with Updated Request & Submission Status to Frontend</step>
            <step id="A1S5">Frontend displays Success, Updated Status & Submission Status</step>
        </asteps>
        <esteps id="E1" start="S4">
            <description>Error Response</description>
            <step id="E1S1">Frontend displays Error Message</step>
        </esteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Oauth Login</name>
    <description>User chooses OAuth login to access the system</description>
    <actors>
        <actor>User</actor>
        <actor>Client Application</actor>
        <actor>API Gateway</actor>
        <actor>Auth Service</actor>
        <actor>OAuth Provider</actor>
        <actor>Auth DB</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>User has initiated OAuth login process</preconditions>
    <successEndConditions>User successfully logs in with OAuth token</successEndConditions>
    <failureEndConditions>Error occurs during OAuth token verification or email not found in DB</failureEndConditions>
    <trigger>User chooses OAuth login and initiates the process</trigger>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">User chooses OAuth login</step>
        <step id="S2">Client Application redirects to OAuth Provider for authorization</step>
        <step id="S3">User authorizes and grants access</step>
        <step id="S4">OAuth Provider returns with OAuth token</step>
        <step id="S5">Client Application sends OAuth token to API Gateway</step>
        <step id="S6">API Gateway forwards OAuth token to Auth Service</step>
        <step id="S7">Auth Service verifies OAuth token with OAuth Provider</step>
        <step id="S8">OAuth Provider provides user info (email) to Auth Service</step>
        <step id="S9">Auth Service verifies email in Auth DB</step>
        <step id="S10">Auth Service sends successful login token to API Gateway</step>
        <step id="S11">API Gateway sends success token to Client Application</step>
        <step id="S12">Client Application displays successful login message to User</step>
    </mainSequence>
    <alternativeSteps>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S7, S10">
            <step id="A1S1">Auth Service encounters OAuth token verification error</step>
            <step id="A1S2">Auth Service notifies API Gateway of invalid token error</step>
            <step id="A1S3">API Gateway sends invalid token error to Client Application</step>
            <step id="A1S4">Client Application displays error message to User</step>
        </asteps>
        <esteps id="E1" start="S9">
            <description>Email not found in Auth DB</description>
            <step id="E1S1">Auth Service fails to find email in Auth DB</step>
            <step id="E1S2">Auth Service notifies API Gateway of email not found error</step>
            <step id="E1S3">API Gateway sends email not found error to Client Application</step>
            <step id="E1S4">Client Application displays error message to User</step>
        </esteps>
    </alternativeSteps>
</useCase>

		<condition>The upgrade process is complete and successful.</condition>

	<mainSequence>
		<step id="S1">The Dataset Developer requests upgrade compatibility check by providing datasetInstanceId and newVersion to Dataset Version Control.</step>

		<step id="S3">Dataset Version Control gets existing version details for the datasetInstanceId from the Dataset Instance.</step>
		<step id="S4">Dataset Version Control compares the versions from datasetTypeDetails and existingVersionDetails.</step>
		<step id="S5">Dataset Version Control fetches the upgrade compatibility rules for the datasetTypeID.</step>
		<step id="S6">Dataset Version Control applies the compatibility rules to determine compatibility for existing and new versions.</step>
		<step id="S7">If the upgrade is compatible,</step>
		<step id="S8">The Dataset Version Control confirms the upgrade, upgrading the Dataset Instance to the newVersion.</step>
		<step id="S9">The Dataset Instance gets the upgraded newVersion successfully.</step>
		<step id="S10">The Dataset Developer is informed that the upgrade is complete.</step>
		
		<asteps id="A1" start="S10">

			<step id="A1S2">The Dataset Developer is informed of the reason of incompatibility.</step>
			<step id="A1S3">Upgrade process is halted.</step>
		</asteps>
	</mainSequence>

<useCase id="UC001">
    <name>Get Top Readers per Genre</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Librarian</actor>
        <actor>LendingController</actor>
        <actor>GenreService</actor>
        <actor>GenreRepository</actor>
        <actor>ReaderService</actor>
        <actor>ReaderRepository</actor>
        <actor>ReaderViewMapper</actor>
    </actors>
    <preconditions>
        <precondition>The Librarian triggers the request to get top readers per genre.</precondition>
    </preconditions>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Librarian triggers the GET request to "/api/lendings/top-readers/{genreId}".</step>
        <step id="S2">LendingController activates to handle the request.</step>
        <step id="S3">LendingController calls GenreService's getGenreById(genreId) method.</step>
        <step id="S4">GenreService activates to process the request.</step>
        <step id="S5">GenreService communicates with GenreRepository to find the genre by ID.</step>
        <step id="S6">GenreRepository returns an Optional<Genre> object to GenreService.</step>
        <step id="S7">GenreService sends the Optional<Genre> back to LendingController.</step>
        <step id="S8">If genre is not found:</step>
        <step id="S9">LendingController responds with HTTP 404 Not Found to the Librarian.</step>
        <step id="S10">If genre is found:</step>
        <step id="S11">LendingController calls ReaderService's getTopReadersperGenre(5, genre, startDate, endDate) method.</step>
        <step id="S12">ReaderService activates to handle the request.</step>
        <step id="S13">ReaderService communicates with ReaderRepository to find top readers per genre.</step>
        <step id="S14">ReaderRepository returns a List<Reader> to ReaderService.</step>
        <step id="S15">ReaderService sends the Iterable<Reader> back to LendingController.</step>
        <step id="S16">LendingController calls ReaderViewMapper's toReaderView(readers) method.</step>
        <step id="S17">ReaderViewMapper activates to map the Reader objects to ReaderView objects.</step>
        <step id="S18">ReaderViewMapper sends the Iterable<ReaderView> back to LendingController.</step>
        <step id="S19">LendingController responds with HTTP 200 OK and the Iterable<ReaderView> to the Librarian.</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Fetch Top Readers per Genre for Lendings</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Librarian</actor>
        <actor>LendingController</actor>
        <actor>GenreService</actor>
        <actor>GenreRepository</actor>
        <actor>ReaderService</actor>
        <actor>ReaderRepository</actor>
        <actor>ReaderViewMapper</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Librarian initiates fetching top readers per genre by genre ID</step>
        <step id="S2">LendingController receives request for top readers per genre</step>
        <step id="S3">GenreService retrieves genre by ID using GenreRepository</step>
        <step id="S4">LendingController receives Genre</step>
        <step id="S5">LendingController checks if genre found</step>
        <asteps id="A1" start="S5">
            <step reference="A1S1">Genre not found response to Librarian</step>
        </asteps>
        <asteps id="A2" start="S5">
            <step reference="A3">ReaderService gets top readers per genre for specified date range</step>
            <step reference="A4">ReaderService finds top readers from ReaderRepository</step>
            <step reference="A5">LendingController receives top readers</step>
            <step reference="A6">LendingController transforms readers to ReaderViews using ReaderViewMapper</step>
            <step reference="A7">LendingController responds to Librarian with ReaderViews</step>
        </asteps>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC1">
    <name>Hypothesis Identification</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Developer</actor>
        <actor>Project Manager</actor>
        <actor>User Research Team</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Request initial hypotheses from Project Manager</step>
        <step id="S2">Consolidate findings for initial hypotheses</step>
        <step id="S3">Provide 3 initial hypotheses based on user research</step>
        <step id="S4">Communicate the 3 hypotheses to Developer</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC2">
    <name>Prototype Planning</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Developer</actor>
        <actor>Project Manager</actor>
        <actor>Github</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Query existing insights on hypotheses from Github</step>
        <step id="S2">Discuss feasibility and resources with Project Manager</step>
        <step id="S3">Confirm prototype development for the hypotheses</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC3">
    <name>Prototype Development</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Developer</actor>
        <actor>CMS</actor>
        <actor>Github</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Determine technology stack based on hypotheses</step>
        <step id="S2">Assess CMS capabilities for prototype</step>
        <step id="S3">Create new branch for prototype development on Github</step>
        <step id="S4">Develop prototypes based on each hypothesis</step>
        <step id="S5">Commit prototypes for team review on Github</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>

<useCase id="UC4">
    <name>Review and Feedback</name>
    <actors>
        <actor>Developer</actor>
        <actor>Project Manager</actor>
        <actor>User Research Team</actor>
        <actor>Github</actor>
    </actors>
    <mainSequence>
        <step id="S1">Notify Project Manager on prototype completion</step>
        <step id="S2">Organize prototype review session by User Research Team</step>
        <step id="S3">Provide feedback via Github issues</step>
        <step id="S4">Notify Developer about feedback</step>
        <step id="S5">Refine prototypes based on feedback</step>
    </mainSequence>
</useCase>
